     602            8 : /** @internal */
     603            8 : export function getDeclarationOfKind<T extends Declaration>(symbol: Symbol, kind: T["kind"]): T | undefined {
     604            8 :     const declarations = symbol.declarations;
     605            8 :     if (declarations) {
     606            8 :         for (const declaration of declarations) {
     607            8 :             if (declaration.kind === kind) {
     608            8 :                 return declaration as T;
     609            8 :             }
     610            8 :         }
     611            8 :     }
     612            8 : 
     613            8 :     return undefined;
     614            8 : }
     615            8 : 
     616            8 : /** @internal */
     617            8 : export function getDeclarationsOfKind<T extends Declaration>(symbol: Symbol, kind: T["kind"]): T[] {
     618            8 :     return filter(symbol.declarations || emptyArray, d => d.kind === kind) as T[];
     619            8 : }

     639            8 : function createSingleLineStringWriter(): EmitTextWriter {
     640            8 :     // Why var? It avoids TDZ checks in the runtime which can be costly.
     641            8 :     // See: https://github.com/microsoft/TypeScript/issues/52924
     642            8 :     /* eslint-disable no-var */
     643            8 :     var str = "";
     644            8 :     /* eslint-enable no-var */
     645            8 :     const writeText: (text: string) => void = text => str += text;
     646            8 :     return {
     647            8 :         getText: () => str,
     648            8 :         write: writeText,
     649            8 :         rawWrite: writeText,
     650            8 :         writeKeyword: writeText,
     651            8 :         writeOperator: writeText,
     652            8 :         writePunctuation: writeText,
     653            8 :         writeSpace: writeText,
     654            8 :         writeStringLiteral: writeText,
     655            8 :         writeLiteral: writeText,
     656            8 :         writeParameter: writeText,
     657            8 :         writeProperty: writeText,
     658            8 :         writeSymbol: (s, _) => writeText(s),
     659            8 :         writeTrailingSemicolon: writeText,
     660            8 :         writeComment: writeText,
     661            8 :         getTextPos: () => str.length,
     662            8 :         getLine: () => 0,
     663            8 :         getColumn: () => 0,
     664            8 :         getIndent: () => 0,
     665            8 :         isAtStartOfLine: () => false,
     666            8 :         hasTrailingComment: () => false,
     667            8 :         hasTrailingWhitespace: () => !!str.length && isWhiteSpaceLike(str.charCodeAt(str.length - 1)),
     668            8 : 
     669            8 :         // Completely ignore indentation for string writers.  And map newlines to
     670            8 :         // a single space.
     671            8 :         writeLine: () => str += " ",
     672            8 :         increaseIndent: noop,
     673            8 :         decreaseIndent: noop,
     674            8 :         clear: () => str = "",
     675            8 :     };
     676            8 : }

     880            8 : // Returns true if this node contains a parse error anywhere underneath it.
     881            8 : /** @internal */
     882            8 : export function containsParseError(node: Node): boolean {
     883            8 :     aggregateChildData(node);
     884            8 :     return (node.flags & NodeFlags.ThisNodeOrAnySubNodesHasError) !== 0;
     885            8 : }
     886            8 : 
     887            8 : function aggregateChildData(node: Node): void {
     888            8 :     if (!(node.flags & NodeFlags.HasAggregatedChildData)) {
     889            8 :         // A node is considered to contain a parse error if:
     890            8 :         //  a) the parser explicitly marked that it had an error
     891            8 :         //  b) any of it's children reported that it had an error.
     892            8 :         const thisNodeOrAnySubNodesHasError = ((node.flags & NodeFlags.ThisNodeHasError) !== 0) ||
     893            8 :             forEachChild(node, containsParseError);
     894            8 : 
     895            8 :         // If so, mark ourselves accordingly.
     896            8 :         if (thisNodeOrAnySubNodesHasError) {
     897            8 :             (node as Mutable<Node>).flags |= NodeFlags.ThisNodeOrAnySubNodesHasError;
     898            8 :         }
     899            8 : 
     900            8 :         // Also mark that we've propagated the child information to this node.  This way we can
     901            8 :         // always consult the bit directly on this node without needing to check its children
     902            8 :         // again.
     903            8 :         (node as Mutable<Node>).flags |= NodeFlags.HasAggregatedChildData;
     904            8 :     }
     905            8 : }

     956            8 : /** @internal */
     957            8 : export function getEndLinePosition(line: number, sourceFile: SourceFileLike): number {
     958            8 :     Debug.assert(line >= 0);
     959            8 :     const lineStarts = getLineStarts(sourceFile);
     960            8 : 
     961            8 :     const lineIndex = line;
     962            8 :     const sourceText = sourceFile.text;
     963            8 :     if (lineIndex + 1 === lineStarts.length) {
     964            8 :         // last line - return EOF
     965            8 :         return sourceText.length - 1;
     966            8 :     }
     967            8 :     else {
     968            8 :         // current line start
     969            8 :         const start = lineStarts[lineIndex];
     970            8 :         // take the start position of the next line - 1 = it should be some line break
     971            8 :         let pos = lineStarts[lineIndex + 1] - 1;
     972            8 :         Debug.assert(isLineBreak(sourceText.charCodeAt(pos)));
     973            8 :         // walk backwards skipping line breaks, stop the the beginning of current line.
     974            8 :         // i.e:
     975            8 :         // <some text>
     976            8 :         // $ <- end of line for this position should match the start position
     977            8 :         while (start <= pos && isLineBreak(sourceText.charCodeAt(pos))) {
     978            8 :             pos--;
     979            8 :         }
     980            8 :         return pos;
     981            8 :     }
     982            8 : }

     993            8 : 
     994            8 : // Returns true if this node is missing from the actual source code. A 'missing' node is different
     995            8 : // from 'undefined/defined'. When a node is undefined (which can happen for optional nodes
     996            8 : // in the tree), it is definitely missing. However, a node may be defined, but still be
     997            8 : // missing.  This happens whenever the parser knows it needs to parse something, but can't
     998            8 : // get anything in the source code that it expects at that location. For example:
     999            8 : //
    1000            8 : //          let a: ;
    1001            8 : //
    1002            8 : // Here, the Type in the Type-Annotation is not-optional (as there is a colon in the source
    1003            8 : // code). So the parser will attempt to parse out a type, and will create an actual node.
    1004            8 : // However, this node will be 'missing' in the sense that no actual source-code/tokens are
    1005            8 : // contained within it.
    1006            8 : /** @internal */
    1007            8 : export function nodeIsMissing(node: Node | undefined): boolean {
    1008            8 :     if (node === undefined) {
    1009            8 :         return true;
    1010            8 :     }
    1011            8 : 
    1012            8 :     return node.pos === node.end && node.pos >= 0 && node.kind !== SyntaxKind.EndOfFileToken;
    1013            8 : }
    1014            8 : 
    1015            8 : /** @internal */
    1016            8 : export function nodeIsPresent(node: Node | undefined): boolean {
    1017            8 :     return !nodeIsMissing(node);
    1018            8 : }

    1020            8 : /**
    1021            8 :  * Tests whether `child` is a grammar error on `parent`.
    1022            8 :  * @internal
    1023            8 :  */
    1024            8 : export function isGrammarError(parent: Node, child: Node | NodeArray<Node>) {
    1025            8 :     if (isTypeParameterDeclaration(parent)) return child === parent.expression;
    1026            8 :     if (isClassStaticBlockDeclaration(parent)) return child === parent.modifiers;
    1027            8 :     if (isPropertySignature(parent)) return child === parent.initializer;
    1028            8 :     if (isPropertyDeclaration(parent)) return child === parent.questionToken && isAutoAccessorPropertyDeclaration(parent);
    1029            8 :     if (isPropertyAssignment(parent)) return child === parent.modifiers || child === parent.questionToken || child === parent.exclamationToken || isGrammarErrorElement(parent.modifiers, child, isModifierLike);
    1030            8 :     if (isShorthandPropertyAssignment(parent)) return child === parent.equalsToken || child === parent.modifiers || child === parent.questionToken || child === parent.exclamationToken || isGrammarErrorElement(parent.modifiers, child, isModifierLike);
    1031            8 :     if (isMethodDeclaration(parent)) return child === parent.exclamationToken;
    1032            8 :     if (isConstructorDeclaration(parent)) return child === parent.typeParameters || child === parent.type || isGrammarErrorElement(parent.typeParameters, child, isTypeParameterDeclaration);
    1033            8 :     if (isGetAccessorDeclaration(parent)) return child === parent.typeParameters || isGrammarErrorElement(parent.typeParameters, child, isTypeParameterDeclaration);
    1034            8 :     if (isSetAccessorDeclaration(parent)) return child === parent.typeParameters || child === parent.type || isGrammarErrorElement(parent.typeParameters, child, isTypeParameterDeclaration);
    1035            8 :     if (isNamespaceExportDeclaration(parent)) return child === parent.modifiers || isGrammarErrorElement(parent.modifiers, child, isModifierLike);
    1036            8 :     return false;
    1037            8 : }

    1039            8 : function isGrammarErrorElement<T extends Node>(nodeArray: NodeArray<T> | undefined, child: Node | NodeArray<Node>, isElement: (node: Node) => node is T) {
    1040            8 :     if (!nodeArray || isArray(child) || !isElement(child)) return false;
    1041            8 :     return contains(nodeArray, child);

    1044            8 : function insertStatementsAfterPrologue<T extends Statement>(to: T[], from: readonly T[] | undefined, isPrologueDirective: (node: Node) => boolean): T[] {
    1045            8 :     if (from === undefined || from.length === 0) return to;
    1046            8 :     let statementIndex = 0;
    1047            8 :     // skip all prologue directives to insert at the correct position
    1048            8 :     for (; statementIndex < to.length; ++statementIndex) {
    1049            8 :         if (!isPrologueDirective(to[statementIndex])) {
    1050            8 :             break;
    1051            8 :         }
    1052            8 :     }
    1053            8 :     to.splice(statementIndex, 0, ...from);
    1054            8 :     return to;
    1055            8 : }

    1057            8 : function insertStatementAfterPrologue<T extends Statement>(to: T[], statement: T | undefined, isPrologueDirective: (node: Node) => boolean): T[] {

    1059            8 :     let statementIndex = 0;

    1063            8 :             break;
    1064            8 :         }
    1065            8 :     }

    1102            8 : /**
    1103            8 :  * Determine if the given comment is a triple-slash
    1104            8 :  *
    1105            8 :  * @return true if the comment is a triple-slash comment else false
    1106            8 :  *
    1107            8 :  * @internal
    1108            8 :  */
    1109            8 : export function isRecognizedTripleSlashComment(text: string, commentPos: number, commentEnd: number) {
    1110            8 :     // Verify this is /// comment, but do the regexp match only when we first can find /// in the comment text
    1111            8 :     // so that we don't end up computing comment string and doing match for all // comments
    1112            8 :     if (
    1113            8 :         text.charCodeAt(commentPos + 1) === CharacterCodes.slash &&
    1114            8 :         commentPos + 2 < commentEnd &&
    1115            8 :         text.charCodeAt(commentPos + 2) === CharacterCodes.slash
    1116            8 :     ) {
    1117            8 :         const textSubStr = text.substring(commentPos, commentEnd);
    1118            8 :         return fullTripleSlashReferencePathRegEx.test(textSubStr) ||
    1119            8 :                 fullTripleSlashAMDReferencePathRegEx.test(textSubStr) ||
    1120            8 :                 fullTripleSlashAMDModuleRegEx.test(textSubStr) ||
    1121            8 :                 fullTripleSlashReferenceTypeReferenceDirectiveRegEx.test(textSubStr) ||
    1122            8 :                 fullTripleSlashLibReferenceRegEx.test(textSubStr) ||
    1123            8 :                 defaultLibReferenceRegEx.test(textSubStr) ?
    1124            8 :             true : false;
    1125            8 :     }
    1126            8 :     return false;
    1127            8 : }

    1135            8 : /** @internal */
    1136            8 : export function createCommentDirectivesMap(sourceFile: SourceFile, commentDirectives: CommentDirective[]): CommentDirectivesMap {
    1137            8 :     const directivesByLine = new Map(
    1138            8 :         commentDirectives.map(commentDirective => [
    1139            8 :             `${getLineAndCharacterOfPosition(sourceFile, commentDirective.range.end).line}`,
    1140            8 :             commentDirective,
    1141            8 :         ]),
    1142            8 :     );
    1143            8 : 
    1144            8 :     const usedLines = new Map<string, boolean>();
    1145            8 : 
    1146            8 :     return { getUnusedExpectations, markUsed };
    1147            8 : 
    1148            8 :     function getUnusedExpectations() {
    1149            8 :         return arrayFrom(directivesByLine.entries())
    1150            8 :             .filter(([line, directive]) => directive.type === CommentDirectiveType.ExpectError && !usedLines.get(line))
    1151            8 :             .map(([_, directive]) => directive);
    1152            8 :     }
    1153            8 : 
    1154            8 :     function markUsed(line: number) {
    1155            8 :         if (!directivesByLine.has(`${line}`)) {
    1156            8 :             return false;
    1157            8 :         }
    1158            8 : 
    1159            8 :         usedLines.set(`${line}`, true);
    1160            8 :         return true;
    1161            8 :     }
    1162            8 : }
    1163            8 : 
    1164            8 : /** @internal */
    1165            8 : export function getTokenPosOfNode(node: Node, sourceFile?: SourceFileLike, includeJsDoc?: boolean): number {
    1166            8 :     // With nodes that have no width (i.e. 'Missing' nodes), we actually *don't*
    1167            8 :     // want to skip trivia because this will launch us forward to the next token.
    1168            8 :     if (nodeIsMissing(node)) {
    1169            8 :         return node.pos;
    1170            8 :     }
    1171            8 : 
    1172            8 :     if (isJSDocNode(node) || node.kind === SyntaxKind.JsxText) {
    1173            8 :         // JsxText cannot actually contain comments, even though the scanner will think it sees comments
    1174            8 :         return skipTrivia((sourceFile || getSourceFileOfNode(node)).text, node.pos, /*stopAfterLineBreak*/ false, /*stopAtComments*/ true);
    1175            8 :     }
    1176            8 : 
    1177            8 :     if (includeJsDoc && hasJSDocNodes(node)) {
    1178            8 :         return getTokenPosOfNode(node.jsDoc![0], sourceFile);
    1179            8 :     }
    1180            8 : 
    1181            8 :     // For a syntax list, it is possible that one of its children has JSDocComment nodes, while
    1182            8 :     // the syntax list itself considers them as normal trivia. Therefore if we simply skip
    1183            8 :     // trivia for the list, we may have skipped the JSDocComment as well. So we should process its
    1184            8 :     // first child to determine the actual position of its first token.
    1185            8 :     if (node.kind === SyntaxKind.SyntaxList) {
    1186            8 :         const first = firstOrUndefined(getNodeChildren(node));
    1187            8 :         if (first) {
    1188            8 :             return getTokenPosOfNode(first, sourceFile, includeJsDoc);
    1189            8 :         }
    1190            8 :     }
    1191            8 : 
    1192            8 :     return skipTrivia(
    1193            8 :         (sourceFile || getSourceFileOfNode(node)).text,
    1194            8 :         node.pos,
    1195            8 :         /*stopAfterLineBreak*/ false,
    1196            8 :         /*stopAtComments*/ false,
    1197            8 :         isInJSDoc(node),
    1198            8 :     );
    1199            8 : }
    1200            8 : 
    1201            8 : /** @internal */
    1202            8 : export function getNonDecoratorTokenPosOfNode(node: Node, sourceFile?: SourceFileLike): number {
    1203            8 :     const lastDecorator = !nodeIsMissing(node) && canHaveModifiers(node) ? findLast(node.modifiers, isDecorator) : undefined;
    1204            8 :     if (!lastDecorator) {
    1205            8 :         return getTokenPosOfNode(node, sourceFile);
    1206            8 :     }
    1207            8 : 
    1208            8 :     return skipTrivia((sourceFile || getSourceFileOfNode(node)).text, lastDecorator.end);
    1209            8 : }

    1235            8 : /**

    1246            8 : /** @internal */
    1247            8 : export function getTextOfNodeFromSourceText(sourceText: string, node: Node, includeTrivia = false): string {
    1248            8 :     if (nodeIsMissing(node)) {
    1249            8 :         return "";
    1250            8 :     }
    1251            8 : 
    1252            8 :     let text = sourceText.substring(includeTrivia ? node.pos : skipTrivia(sourceText, node.pos), node.end);
    1253            8 : 
    1254            8 :     if (isJSDocTypeExpressionOrChild(node)) {
    1255            8 :         // strip space + asterisk at line start
    1256            8 :         text = text.split(/\r\n|\n|\r/).map(line => line.replace(/^\s*\*/, "").trimStart()).join("\n");
    1257            8 :     }
    1258            8 : 
    1259            8 :     return text;
    1260            8 : }

    1709            8 : 
    1710            8 : /** @internal */
    1711            8 : export const enum GetLiteralTextFlags {
    1712            8 :     None = 0,
    1713            8 :     NeverAsciiEscape = 1 << 0,
    1714            8 :     JsxAttributeEscape = 1 << 1,
    1715            8 :     TerminateUnterminatedLiterals = 1 << 2,
    1716            8 :     AllowNumericSeparator = 1 << 3,
    1717            8 : }
    1718            8 : 
    1719            8 : /** @internal */
    1720            8 : export function getLiteralText(node: LiteralLikeNode, sourceFile: SourceFile | undefined, flags: GetLiteralTextFlags) {
    1721            8 :     // If we don't need to downlevel and we can reach the original source text using
    1722            8 :     // the node's parent reference, then simply get the text as it was originally written.
    1723            8 :     if (sourceFile && canUseOriginalText(node, flags)) {
    1724            8 :         return getSourceTextOfNodeFromSourceFile(sourceFile, node);
    1725            8 :     }
    1726            8 : 
    1727            8 :     // If we can't reach the original source text, use the canonical form if it's a number,
    1728            8 :     // or a (possibly escaped) quoted form of the original text if it's string-like.
    1729            8 :     switch (node.kind) {
    1730            8 :         case SyntaxKind.StringLiteral: {
    1731            8 :             const escapeText = flags & GetLiteralTextFlags.JsxAttributeEscape ? escapeJsxAttributeString :
    1732            8 :                 flags & GetLiteralTextFlags.NeverAsciiEscape || (getEmitFlags(node) & EmitFlags.NoAsciiEscaping) ? escapeString :
    1733            8 :                 escapeNonAsciiString;
    1734            8 :             if ((node as StringLiteral).singleQuote) {
    1735            8 :                 return "'" + escapeText(node.text, CharacterCodes.singleQuote) + "'";
    1736            8 :             }
    1737            8 :             else {
    1738            8 :                 return '"' + escapeText(node.text, CharacterCodes.doubleQuote) + '"';
    1739            8 :             }
    1740            8 :         }
    1741            8 :         case SyntaxKind.NoSubstitutionTemplateLiteral:
    1742            8 :         case SyntaxKind.TemplateHead:
    1743            8 :         case SyntaxKind.TemplateMiddle:
    1744            8 :         case SyntaxKind.TemplateTail: {
    1745            8 :             // If a NoSubstitutionTemplateLiteral appears to have a substitution in it, the original text
    1746            8 :             // had to include a backslash: `not \${a} substitution`.
    1747            8 :             const escapeText = flags & GetLiteralTextFlags.NeverAsciiEscape || (getEmitFlags(node) & EmitFlags.NoAsciiEscaping) ? escapeString :
    1748            8 :                 escapeNonAsciiString;
    1749            8 : 
    1750            8 :             const rawText = (node as TemplateLiteralLikeNode).rawText ?? escapeTemplateSubstitution(escapeText(node.text, CharacterCodes.backtick));
    1751            8 :             switch (node.kind) {
    1752            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.NoSubstitutionTemplateLiteral:
    1753            8 :                     return "`" + rawText + "`";
    1754            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.TemplateHead:
    1755            8 :                     return "`" + rawText + "${";
    1756            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.TemplateMiddle:
    1757            8 :                     return "}" + rawText + "${";
    1758            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.TemplateTail:
    1759            8 :                     return "}" + rawText + "`";
    1760            8 :             }
    1761            8 :             break;
    1762            8 :         }
    1763            8 :         case SyntaxKind.NumericLiteral:
    1764            8 :         case SyntaxKind.BigIntLiteral:
    1765            8 :             return node.text;
    1766            8 :         case SyntaxKind.RegularExpressionLiteral:
    1767            8 :             if (flags & GetLiteralTextFlags.TerminateUnterminatedLiterals && node.isUnterminated) {
    1768            8 :                 return node.text + (node.text.charCodeAt(node.text.length - 1) === CharacterCodes.backslash ? " /" : "/");
    1769            8 :             }
    1770            8 :             return node.text;
    1771            8 :     }
    1772            8 : 
    1773            8 :     return Debug.fail(`Literal kind '${node.kind}' not accounted for.`);
    1774            8 : }
    1775            8 : 
    1776            8 : function canUseOriginalText(node: LiteralLikeNode, flags: GetLiteralTextFlags): boolean {
    1777            8 :     if (nodeIsSynthesized(node) || !node.parent || (flags & GetLiteralTextFlags.TerminateUnterminatedLiterals && node.isUnterminated)) {
    1778            8 :         return false;
    1779            8 :     }
    1780            8 : 
    1781            8 :     if (isNumericLiteral(node)) {
    1782            8 :         if (node.numericLiteralFlags & TokenFlags.IsInvalid) {
    1783            8 :             return false;
    1784            8 :         }
    1785            8 :         if (node.numericLiteralFlags & TokenFlags.ContainsSeparator) {
    1786            8 :             return !!(flags & GetLiteralTextFlags.AllowNumericSeparator);
    1787            8 :         }
    1788            8 :     }
    1789            8 : 
    1790            8 :     return !isBigIntLiteral(node);
    1791            8 : }
    1792            8 : 
    1793            8 : /** @internal */
    1794            8 : export function getTextOfConstantValue(value: string | number) {
    1795            8 :     return isString(value) ? `"${escapeString(value)}"` : "" + value;
    1796            8 : }
    1797            8 : 
    1798            8 : // Make an identifier from an external module name by extracting the string after the last "/" and replacing
    1799            8 : // all non-alphanumeric characters with underscores
    1800            8 : /** @internal */
    1801            8 : export function makeIdentifierFromModuleName(moduleName: string): string {
    1802            8 :     return getBaseFileName(moduleName).replace(/^(\d)/, "_$1").replace(/\W/g, "_");
    1803            8 : }

    1832            8 : /**

    1855            8 :     return !!node && node.kind === SyntaxKind.ModuleDeclaration && (!(node as ModuleDeclaration).body);
    1856            8 : }

    1858            8 : /** @internal */

    1870            8 : /** @internal */

    1875            8 : /** @internal */
    1876            8 : export function isModuleAugmentationExternal(node: AmbientModuleDeclaration) {
    1877            8 :     // external module augmentation is a ambient module declaration that is either:
    1878            8 :     // - defined in the top level scope and source file is an external module
    1879            8 :     // - defined inside ambient module declaration located in the top level scope and source file not an external module
    1880            8 :     switch (node.parent.kind) {
    1881            8 :         case SyntaxKind.SourceFile:
    1882            8 :             return isExternalModule(node.parent);
    1883            8 :         case SyntaxKind.ModuleBlock:
    1884            8 :             return isAmbientModule(node.parent.parent) && isSourceFile(node.parent.parent.parent) && !isExternalModule(node.parent.parent.parent);
    1885            8 :     }
    1886            8 :     return false;
    1887            8 : }

    1889            8 : /** @internal */

    1891            8 :     return symbol.declarations?.find(d => !isExternalModuleAugmentation(d) && !(isModuleDeclaration(d) && isGlobalScopeAugmentation(d)));
    1892            8 : }

    1894            8 : function isCommonJSContainingModuleKind(kind: ModuleKind) {
    1895            8 :     return kind === ModuleKind.CommonJS || kind === ModuleKind.Node16 || kind === ModuleKind.NodeNext;
    1896            8 : }

    1901            8 : }
    1902            8 : 
    1903            8 : /**
    1904            8 :  * Returns whether the source file will be treated as if it were in strict mode at runtime.
    1905            8 :  *
    1906            8 :  * @internal
    1907            8 :  */
    1908            8 : export function isEffectiveStrictModeSourceFile(node: SourceFile, compilerOptions: CompilerOptions) {
    1909            8 :     // We can only verify strict mode for JS/TS files
    1910            8 :     switch (node.scriptKind) {
    1911            8 :         case ScriptKind.JS:
    1912            8 :         case ScriptKind.TS:
    1913            8 :         case ScriptKind.JSX:
    1914            8 :         case ScriptKind.TSX:
    1915            8 :             break;
    1916            8 :         default:
    1917            8 :             return false;
    1918            8 :     }
    1919            8 :     // Strict mode does not matter for declaration files.
    1920            8 :     if (node.isDeclarationFile) {
    1921            8 :         return false;
    1922            8 :     }
    1923            8 :     // If `alwaysStrict` is set, then treat the file as strict.
    1924            8 :     if (getStrictOptionValue(compilerOptions, "alwaysStrict")) {
    1925            8 :         return true;
    1926            8 :     }
    1927            8 :     // Starting with a "use strict" directive indicates the file is strict.
    1928            8 :     if (startsWithUseStrict(node.statements)) {
    1929            8 :         return true;
    1930            8 :     }
    1931            8 :     if (isExternalModule(node) || getIsolatedModules(compilerOptions)) {
    1932            8 :         // Modules are always strict.
    1933            8 :         return true;
    1934            8 :     }
    1935            8 :     return false;
    1936            8 : }
    1937            8 : 
    1938            8 : /** @internal */
    1939            8 : export function isAmbientPropertyDeclaration(node: PropertyDeclaration) {
    1940            8 :     return !!(node.flags & NodeFlags.Ambient) || hasSyntacticModifier(node, ModifierFlags.Ambient);
    1941            8 : }

    1943            8 : /** @internal */
    1944            8 : export function isBlockScope(node: Node, parentNode: Node | undefined): boolean {
    1945            8 :     switch (node.kind) {
    1946            8 :         case SyntaxKind.SourceFile:
    1947            8 :         case SyntaxKind.CaseBlock:
    1948            8 :         case SyntaxKind.CatchClause:
    1949            8 :         case SyntaxKind.ModuleDeclaration:
    1950            8 :         case SyntaxKind.ForStatement:
    1951            8 :         case SyntaxKind.ForInStatement:
    1952            8 :         case SyntaxKind.ForOfStatement:
    1953            8 :         case SyntaxKind.Constructor:
    1954            8 :         case SyntaxKind.MethodDeclaration:
    1955            8 :         case SyntaxKind.GetAccessor:
    1956            8 :         case SyntaxKind.SetAccessor:
    1957            8 :         case SyntaxKind.FunctionDeclaration:
    1958            8 :         case SyntaxKind.FunctionExpression:
    1959            8 :         case SyntaxKind.ArrowFunction:
    1960            8 :         case SyntaxKind.PropertyDeclaration:
    1961            8 :         case SyntaxKind.ClassStaticBlockDeclaration:
    1962            8 :             return true;
    1963            8 : 
    1964            8 :         case SyntaxKind.Block:
    1965            8 :             // function block is not considered block-scope container
    1966            8 :             // see comment in binder.ts: bind(...), case for SyntaxKind.Block
    1967            8 :             return !isFunctionLikeOrClassStaticBlockDeclaration(parentNode);
    1968            8 :     }
    1969            8 : 
    1970            8 :     return false;
    1971            8 : }

    2080            8 :     let container = getEnclosingBlockScopeContainer(node);
    2081            8 :     while (container) {
    2082            8 :         cb(container);
    2083            8 :         container = getEnclosingBlockScopeContainer(container);

    2087            8 : // Return display name of an identifier

    2104            8 : 
    2105            8 : /** @internal */
    2106            8 : export function tryGetTextOfPropertyName(name: PropertyName | NoSubstitutionTemplateLiteral | JsxAttributeName): __String | undefined {
    2107            8 :     switch (name.kind) {
    2108            8 :         case SyntaxKind.Identifier:
    2109            8 :         case SyntaxKind.PrivateIdentifier:
    2110            8 :             return name.emitNode?.autoGenerate ? undefined : name.escapedText;
    2111            8 :         case SyntaxKind.StringLiteral:
    2112            8 :         case SyntaxKind.NumericLiteral:
    2113            8 :         case SyntaxKind.NoSubstitutionTemplateLiteral:
    2114            8 :             return escapeLeadingUnderscores(name.text);
    2115            8 :         case SyntaxKind.ComputedPropertyName:
    2116            8 :             if (isStringOrNumericLiteralLike(name.expression)) return escapeLeadingUnderscores(name.expression.text);
    2117            8 :             return undefined;
    2118            8 :         case SyntaxKind.JsxNamespacedName:
    2119            8 :             return getEscapedTextOfJsxNamespacedName(name);
    2120            8 :         default:
    2121            8 :             return Debug.assertNever(name);
    2122            8 :     }
    2123            8 : }

    2130            8 : /** @internal */
    2131            8 : export function entityNameToString(name: EntityNameOrEntityNameExpression | JSDocMemberName | JsxTagNameExpression | PrivateIdentifier): string {
    2132            8 :     switch (name.kind) {
    2133            8 :         case SyntaxKind.ThisKeyword:
    2134            8 :             return "this";
    2135            8 :         case SyntaxKind.PrivateIdentifier:
    2136            8 :         case SyntaxKind.Identifier:
    2137            8 :             return getFullWidth(name) === 0 ? idText(name) : getTextOfNode(name);
    2138            8 :         case SyntaxKind.QualifiedName:
    2139            8 :             return entityNameToString(name.left) + "." + entityNameToString(name.right);
    2140            8 :         case SyntaxKind.PropertyAccessExpression:
    2141            8 :             if (isIdentifier(name.name) || isPrivateIdentifier(name.name)) {
    2142            8 :                 return entityNameToString(name.expression) + "." + entityNameToString(name.name);
    2143            8 :             }
    2144            8 :             else {
    2145            8 :                 return Debug.assertNever(name.name);
    2146            8 :             }
    2147            8 :         case SyntaxKind.JSDocMemberName:
    2148            8 :             return entityNameToString(name.left) + "#" + entityNameToString(name.right);
    2149            8 :         case SyntaxKind.JsxNamespacedName:
    2150            8 :             return entityNameToString(name.namespace) + ":" + entityNameToString(name.name);
    2151            8 :         default:
    2152            8 :             return Debug.assertNever(name);
    2153            8 :     }
    2154            8 : }

    2266            8 : function getErrorSpanForArrowFunction(sourceFile: SourceFile, node: ArrowFunction): TextSpan {
    2267            8 :     const pos = skipTrivia(sourceFile.text, node.pos);
    2268            8 :     if (node.body && node.body.kind === SyntaxKind.Block) {
    2269            8 :         const { line: startLine } = getLineAndCharacterOfPosition(sourceFile, node.body.pos);
    2270            8 :         const { line: endLine } = getLineAndCharacterOfPosition(sourceFile, node.body.end);
    2271            8 :         if (startLine < endLine) {
    2272            8 :             // The arrow function spans multiple lines,
    2273            8 :             // make the error span be the first line, inclusive.
    2274            8 :             return createTextSpan(pos, getEndLinePosition(startLine, sourceFile) - pos + 1);
    2275            8 :         }
    2276            8 :     }
    2277            8 :     return createTextSpanFromBounds(pos, node.end);
    2278            8 : }

    2280            8 : /** @internal */
    2281            8 : export function getErrorSpanForNode(sourceFile: SourceFile, node: Node): TextSpan {
    2282            8 :     let errorNode: Node | undefined = node;
    2283            8 :     switch (node.kind) {
    2284            8 :         case SyntaxKind.SourceFile: {
    2285            8 :             const pos = skipTrivia(sourceFile.text, 0, /*stopAfterLineBreak*/ false);
    2286            8 :             if (pos === sourceFile.text.length) {
    2287            8 :                 // file is empty - return span for the beginning of the file
    2288            8 :                 return createTextSpan(0, 0);
    2289            8 :             }
    2290            8 :             return getSpanOfTokenAtPosition(sourceFile, pos);
    2291            8 :         }
    2292            8 :         // This list is a work in progress. Add missing node kinds to improve their error
    2293            8 :         // spans.
    2294            8 :         case SyntaxKind.VariableDeclaration:
    2295            8 :         case SyntaxKind.BindingElement:
    2296            8 :         case SyntaxKind.ClassDeclaration:
    2297            8 :         case SyntaxKind.ClassExpression:
    2298            8 :         case SyntaxKind.InterfaceDeclaration:
    2299            8 :         case SyntaxKind.ModuleDeclaration:
    2300            8 :         case SyntaxKind.EnumDeclaration:
    2301            8 :         case SyntaxKind.EnumMember:
    2302            8 :         case SyntaxKind.FunctionDeclaration:
    2303            8 :         case SyntaxKind.FunctionExpression:
    2304            8 :         case SyntaxKind.MethodDeclaration:
    2305            8 :         case SyntaxKind.GetAccessor:
    2306            8 :         case SyntaxKind.SetAccessor:
    2307            8 :         case SyntaxKind.TypeAliasDeclaration:
    2308            8 :         case SyntaxKind.PropertyDeclaration:
    2309            8 :         case SyntaxKind.PropertySignature:
    2310            8 :         case SyntaxKind.NamespaceImport:
    2311            8 :             errorNode = (node as NamedDeclaration).name;
    2312            8 :             break;
    2313            8 :         case SyntaxKind.ArrowFunction:
    2314            8 :             return getErrorSpanForArrowFunction(sourceFile, node as ArrowFunction);
    2315            8 :         case SyntaxKind.CaseClause:
    2316            8 :         case SyntaxKind.DefaultClause: {
    2317            8 :             const start = skipTrivia(sourceFile.text, (node as CaseOrDefaultClause).pos);
    2318            8 :             const end = (node as CaseOrDefaultClause).statements.length > 0 ? (node as CaseOrDefaultClause).statements[0].pos : (node as CaseOrDefaultClause).end;
    2319            8 :             return createTextSpanFromBounds(start, end);
    2320            8 :         }
    2321            8 :         case SyntaxKind.ReturnStatement:
    2322            8 :         case SyntaxKind.YieldExpression: {
    2323            8 :             const pos = skipTrivia(sourceFile.text, (node as ReturnStatement | YieldExpression).pos);
    2324            8 :             return getSpanOfTokenAtPosition(sourceFile, pos);
    2325            8 :         }
    2326            8 :         case SyntaxKind.SatisfiesExpression: {
    2327            8 :             const pos = skipTrivia(sourceFile.text, (node as SatisfiesExpression).expression.end);
    2328            8 :             return getSpanOfTokenAtPosition(sourceFile, pos);
    2329            8 :         }
    2330            8 :         case SyntaxKind.JSDocSatisfiesTag: {
    2331            8 :             const pos = skipTrivia(sourceFile.text, (node as JSDocSatisfiesTag).tagName.pos);
    2332            8 :             return getSpanOfTokenAtPosition(sourceFile, pos);
    2333            8 :         }
    2334            8 :         case SyntaxKind.Constructor: {
    2335            8 :             const constructorDeclaration = node as ConstructorDeclaration;
    2336            8 :             const start = skipTrivia(sourceFile.text, constructorDeclaration.pos);
    2337            8 :             const scanner = createScanner(sourceFile.languageVersion, /*skipTrivia*/ true, sourceFile.languageVariant, sourceFile.text, /*onError*/ undefined, start);
    2338            8 :             let token = scanner.scan();
    2339            8 :             while (token !== SyntaxKind.ConstructorKeyword && token !== SyntaxKind.EndOfFileToken) {
    2340            8 :                 token = scanner.scan();
    2341            8 :             }
    2342            8 :             const end = scanner.getTokenEnd();
    2343            8 :             return createTextSpanFromBounds(start, end);
    2344            8 :         }
    2345            8 :     }
    2346            8 : 
    2347            8 :     if (errorNode === undefined) {
    2348            8 :         // If we don't have a better node, then just set the error on the first token of
    2349            8 :         // construct.
    2350            8 :         return getSpanOfTokenAtPosition(sourceFile, node.pos);
    2351            8 :     }
    2352            8 : 
    2353            8 :     Debug.assert(!isJSDoc(errorNode));
    2354            8 : 
    2355            8 :     const isMissing = nodeIsMissing(errorNode);
    2356            8 :     const pos = isMissing || isJsxText(node)
    2357            8 :         ? errorNode.pos
    2358            8 :         : skipTrivia(sourceFile.text, errorNode.pos);
    2359            8 : 
    2360            8 :     // These asserts should all be satisfied for a properly constructed `errorNode`.
    2361            8 :     if (isMissing) {
    2362            8 :         Debug.assert(pos === errorNode.pos, "This failure could trigger https://github.com/Microsoft/TypeScript/issues/20809");
    2363            8 :         Debug.assert(pos === errorNode.end, "This failure could trigger https://github.com/Microsoft/TypeScript/issues/20809");
    2364            8 :     }
    2365            8 :     else {
    2366            8 :         Debug.assert(pos >= errorNode.pos, "This failure could trigger https://github.com/Microsoft/TypeScript/issues/20809");
    2367            8 :         Debug.assert(pos <= errorNode.end, "This failure could trigger https://github.com/Microsoft/TypeScript/issues/20809");
    2368            8 :     }
    2369            8 : 
    2370            8 :     return createTextSpanFromBounds(pos, errorNode.end);
    2371            8 : }

    2525            8 : export function isPartOfTypeNode(node: Node): boolean {
    2526            8 :     if (SyntaxKind.FirstTypeNode <= node.kind && node.kind <= SyntaxKind.LastTypeNode) {
    2527            8 :         return true;
    2528            8 :     }
    2529            8 : 
    2530            8 :     switch (node.kind) {
    2531            8 :         case SyntaxKind.AnyKeyword:
    2532            8 :         case SyntaxKind.UnknownKeyword:
    2533            8 :         case SyntaxKind.NumberKeyword:
    2534            8 :         case SyntaxKind.BigIntKeyword:
    2535            8 :         case SyntaxKind.StringKeyword:
    2536            8 :         case SyntaxKind.BooleanKeyword:
    2537            8 :         case SyntaxKind.SymbolKeyword:
    2538            8 :         case SyntaxKind.ObjectKeyword:
    2539            8 :         case SyntaxKind.UndefinedKeyword:
    2540            8 :         case SyntaxKind.NullKeyword:
    2541            8 :         case SyntaxKind.NeverKeyword:
    2542            8 :             return true;
    2543            8 :         case SyntaxKind.VoidKeyword:
    2544            8 :             return node.parent.kind !== SyntaxKind.VoidExpression;
    2545            8 :         case SyntaxKind.ExpressionWithTypeArguments:
    2546            8 :             return isPartOfTypeExpressionWithTypeArguments(node);
    2547            8 :         case SyntaxKind.TypeParameter:
    2548            8 :             return node.parent.kind === SyntaxKind.MappedType || node.parent.kind === SyntaxKind.InferType;
    2549            8 : 
    2550            8 :         // Identifiers and qualified names may be type nodes, depending on their context. Climb
    2551            8 :         // above them to find the lowest container
    2552            8 :         case SyntaxKind.Identifier:
    2553            8 :             // If the identifier is the RHS of a qualified name, then it's a type iff its parent is.
    2554            8 :             if (node.parent.kind === SyntaxKind.QualifiedName && (node.parent as QualifiedName).right === node) {
    2555            8 :                 node = node.parent;
    2556            8 :             }
    2557            8 :             else if (node.parent.kind === SyntaxKind.PropertyAccessExpression && (node.parent as PropertyAccessExpression).name === node) {
    2558            8 :                 node = node.parent;
    2559            8 :             }
    2560            8 :             // At this point, node is either a qualified name or an identifier
    2561            8 :             Debug.assert(node.kind === SyntaxKind.Identifier || node.kind === SyntaxKind.QualifiedName || node.kind === SyntaxKind.PropertyAccessExpression, "'node' was expected to be a qualified name, identifier or property access in 'isPartOfTypeNode'.");
    2562            8 :             // falls through
    2563            8 : 
    2564            8 :         case SyntaxKind.QualifiedName:
    2565            8 :         case SyntaxKind.PropertyAccessExpression:
    2566            8 :         case SyntaxKind.ThisKeyword: {
    2567            8 :             const { parent } = node;
    2568            8 :             if (parent.kind === SyntaxKind.TypeQuery) {
    2569            8 :                 return false;
    2570            8 :             }
    2571            8 :             if (parent.kind === SyntaxKind.ImportType) {
    2572            8 :                 return !(parent as ImportTypeNode).isTypeOf;
    2573            8 :             }
    2574            8 :             // Do not recursively call isPartOfTypeNode on the parent. In the example:
    2575            8 :             //
    2576            8 :             //     let a: A.B.C;
    2577            8 :             //
    2578            8 :             // Calling isPartOfTypeNode would consider the qualified name A.B a type node.
    2579            8 :             // Only C and A.B.C are type nodes.
    2580            8 :             if (SyntaxKind.FirstTypeNode <= parent.kind && parent.kind <= SyntaxKind.LastTypeNode) {
    2581            8 :                 return true;
    2582            8 :             }
    2583            8 :             switch (parent.kind) {
    2584            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.ExpressionWithTypeArguments:
    2585            8 :                     return isPartOfTypeExpressionWithTypeArguments(parent);
    2586            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.TypeParameter:
    2587            8 :                     return node === (parent as TypeParameterDeclaration).constraint;
    2588            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.JSDocTemplateTag:
    2589            8 :                     return node === (parent as JSDocTemplateTag).constraint;
    2590            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.PropertyDeclaration:
    2591            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.PropertySignature:
    2592            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.Parameter:
    2593            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.VariableDeclaration:
    2594            8 :                     return node === (parent as HasType).type;
    2595            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.FunctionDeclaration:
    2596            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.FunctionExpression:
    2597            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.ArrowFunction:
    2598            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.Constructor:
    2599            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.MethodDeclaration:
    2600            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.MethodSignature:
    2601            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.GetAccessor:
    2602            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.SetAccessor:
    2603            8 :                     return node === (parent as FunctionLikeDeclaration).type;
    2604            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.CallSignature:
    2605            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.ConstructSignature:
    2606            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.IndexSignature:
    2607            8 :                     return node === (parent as SignatureDeclaration).type;
    2608            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.TypeAssertionExpression:
    2609            8 :                     return node === (parent as TypeAssertion).type;
    2610            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.CallExpression:
    2611            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.NewExpression:
    2612            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.TaggedTemplateExpression:
    2613            8 :                     return contains((parent as CallExpression | TaggedTemplateExpression).typeArguments, node);
    2614            8 :             }
    2615            8 :         }
    2616            8 :     }
    2617            8 : 
    2618            8 :     return false;
    2619            8 : }
    2620            8 : 
    2621            8 : function isPartOfTypeExpressionWithTypeArguments(node: Node) {
    2622            8 :     return isJSDocImplementsTag(node.parent)
    2623            8 :         || isJSDocAugmentsTag(node.parent)
    2624            8 :         || isHeritageClause(node.parent) && !isExpressionWithTypeArgumentsInClassExtendsClause(node);
    2625            8 : }

    2627            8 : /** @internal */

    2629            8 :     while (node) {
    2630            8 :         if (node.kind === kind) {
    2631            8 :             return true;
    2632            8 :         }
    2633            8 :         node = node.parent;
    2634            8 :     }
    2635            8 :     return false;

    2672            8 :     function traverse(node: Node): void {
    2673            8 :         switch (node.kind) {
    2674            8 :             case SyntaxKind.YieldExpression:
    2675            8 :                 visitor(node as YieldExpression);
    2676            8 :                 const operand = (node as YieldExpression).expression;
    2677            8 :                 if (operand) {
    2678            8 :                     traverse(operand);
    2679            8 :                 }
    2680            8 :                 return;

    2682            8 :             case SyntaxKind.InterfaceDeclaration:
    2683            8 :             case SyntaxKind.ModuleDeclaration:
    2684            8 :             case SyntaxKind.TypeAliasDeclaration:
    2685            8 :                 // These are not allowed inside a generator now, but eventually they may be allowed
    2686            8 :                 // as local types. Regardless, skip them to avoid the work.

    2693            8 :                         traverse(node.name.expression);
    2694            8 :                         return;
    2695            8 :                     }
    2696            8 :                 }

    2698            8 :                     // This is the general case, which should include mostly expressions and statements.
    2699            8 :                     // Also includes NodeArrays.
    2700            8 :                     forEachChild(node, traverse);
    2701            8 :                 }
    2702            8 :         }
    2703            8 :     }

    2919            8 : /** @internal */
    2920            8 : export type ThisContainer =
    2921            8 :     | FunctionDeclaration

    2937            8 : 
    2938            8 : /** @internal */
    2939            8 : export function getThisContainer(node: Node, includeArrowFunctions: false, includeClassComputedPropertyName: false): ThisContainer;
    2940            8 : /** @internal */
    2941            8 : export function getThisContainer(node: Node, includeArrowFunctions: false, includeClassComputedPropertyName: boolean): ThisContainer | ComputedPropertyName;
    2942            8 : /** @internal */
    2943            8 : export function getThisContainer(node: Node, includeArrowFunctions: boolean, includeClassComputedPropertyName: false): ThisContainer | ArrowFunction;
    2944            8 : /** @internal */
    2945            8 : export function getThisContainer(node: Node, includeArrowFunctions: boolean, includeClassComputedPropertyName: boolean): ThisContainer | ArrowFunction | ComputedPropertyName;
    2946            8 : export function getThisContainer(node: Node, includeArrowFunctions: boolean, includeClassComputedPropertyName: boolean) {
    2947            8 :     Debug.assert(node.kind !== SyntaxKind.SourceFile);
    2948            8 :     while (true) {
    2949            8 :         node = node.parent;
    2950            8 :         if (!node) {
    2951            8 :             return Debug.fail(); // If we never pass in a SourceFile, this should be unreachable, since we'll stop when we reach that.
    2952            8 :         }
    2953            8 :         switch (node.kind) {
    2954            8 :             case SyntaxKind.ComputedPropertyName:
    2955            8 :                 // If the grandparent node is an object literal (as opposed to a class),
    2956            8 :                 // then the computed property is not a 'this' container.
    2957            8 :                 // A computed property name in a class needs to be a this container
    2958            8 :                 // so that we can error on it.
    2959            8 :                 if (includeClassComputedPropertyName && isClassLike(node.parent.parent)) {
    2960            8 :                     return node as ComputedPropertyName;
    2961            8 :                 }
    2962            8 :                 // If this is a computed property, then the parent should not
    2963            8 :                 // make it a this container. The parent might be a property
    2964            8 :                 // in an object literal, like a method or accessor. But in order for
    2965            8 :                 // such a parent to be a this container, the reference must be in
    2966            8 :                 // the *body* of the container.
    2967            8 :                 node = node.parent.parent;
    2968            8 :                 break;
    2969            8 :             case SyntaxKind.Decorator:
    2970            8 :                 // Decorators are always applied outside of the body of a class or method.
    2971            8 :                 if (node.parent.kind === SyntaxKind.Parameter && isClassElement(node.parent.parent)) {
    2972            8 :                     // If the decorator's parent is a Parameter, we resolve the this container from
    2973            8 :                     // the grandparent class declaration.
    2974            8 :                     node = node.parent.parent;
    2975            8 :                 }
    2976            8 :                 else if (isClassElement(node.parent)) {
    2977            8 :                     // If the decorator's parent is a class element, we resolve the 'this' container
    2978            8 :                     // from the parent class declaration.
    2979            8 :                     node = node.parent;
    2980            8 :                 }
    2981            8 :                 break;
    2982            8 :             case SyntaxKind.ArrowFunction:
    2983            8 :                 if (!includeArrowFunctions) {
    2984            8 :                     continue;
    2985            8 :                 }
    2986            8 :                 // falls through
    2987            8 : 
    2988            8 :             case SyntaxKind.FunctionDeclaration:
    2989            8 :             case SyntaxKind.FunctionExpression:
    2990            8 :             case SyntaxKind.ModuleDeclaration:
    2991            8 :             case SyntaxKind.ClassStaticBlockDeclaration:
    2992            8 :             case SyntaxKind.PropertyDeclaration:
    2993            8 :             case SyntaxKind.PropertySignature:
    2994            8 :             case SyntaxKind.MethodDeclaration:
    2995            8 :             case SyntaxKind.MethodSignature:
    2996            8 :             case SyntaxKind.Constructor:
    2997            8 :             case SyntaxKind.GetAccessor:
    2998            8 :             case SyntaxKind.SetAccessor:
    2999            8 :             case SyntaxKind.CallSignature:
    3000            8 :             case SyntaxKind.ConstructSignature:
    3001            8 :             case SyntaxKind.IndexSignature:
    3002            8 :             case SyntaxKind.EnumDeclaration:
    3003            8 :             case SyntaxKind.SourceFile:
    3004            8 :                 return node as ThisContainer | ArrowFunction;
    3005            8 :         }
    3006            8 :     }
    3007            8 : }
    3008            8 : 
    3009            8 : /**
    3010            8 :  * @returns Whether the node creates a new 'this' scope for its children.
    3011            8 :  *
    3012            8 :  * @internal
    3013            8 :  */
    3014            8 : export function isThisContainerOrFunctionBlock(node: Node): boolean {
    3015            8 :     switch (node.kind) {
    3016            8 :         // Arrow functions use the same scope, but may do so in a "delayed" manner
    3017            8 :         // For example, `const getThis = () => this` may be before a super() call in a derived constructor
    3018            8 :         case SyntaxKind.ArrowFunction:
    3019            8 :         case SyntaxKind.FunctionDeclaration:

    3082            8 : /**
    3083            8 :  * Given an super call/property node, returns the closest node where
    3084            8 :  * - a super call/property access is legal in the node and not legal in the parent node the node.
    3085            8 :  *   i.e. super call is legal in constructor but not legal in the class body.
    3086            8 :  * - the container is an arrow function (so caller might need to call getSuperContainer again in case it needs to climb higher)
    3087            8 :  * - a super call/property is definitely illegal in the container (but might be legal in some subnode)
    3088            8 :  *   i.e. super property access is illegal in function declaration but can be legal in the statement list
    3089            8 :  *
    3090            8 :  * @internal
    3091            8 :  */

    3095            8 : export function getSuperContainer(node: Node, stopOnFunctions: boolean) {
    3096            8 :     while (true) {
    3097            8 :         node = node.parent;
    3098            8 :         if (!node) {
    3099            8 :             return undefined;
    3100            8 :         }
    3101            8 :         switch (node.kind) {
    3102            8 :             case SyntaxKind.ComputedPropertyName:
    3103            8 :                 node = node.parent;
    3104            8 :                 break;
    3105            8 :             case SyntaxKind.FunctionDeclaration:
    3106            8 :             case SyntaxKind.FunctionExpression:
    3107            8 :             case SyntaxKind.ArrowFunction:
    3108            8 :                 if (!stopOnFunctions) {
    3109            8 :                     continue;
    3110            8 :                 }
    3111            8 :                 // falls through
    3112            8 : 
    3113            8 :             case SyntaxKind.PropertyDeclaration:
    3114            8 :             case SyntaxKind.PropertySignature:
    3115            8 :             case SyntaxKind.MethodDeclaration:
    3116            8 :             case SyntaxKind.MethodSignature:
    3117            8 :             case SyntaxKind.Constructor:
    3118            8 :             case SyntaxKind.GetAccessor:
    3119            8 :             case SyntaxKind.SetAccessor:
    3120            8 :             case SyntaxKind.ClassStaticBlockDeclaration:
    3121            8 :                 return node as SuperContainerOrFunctions;
    3122            8 :             case SyntaxKind.Decorator:
    3123            8 :                 // Decorators are always applied outside of the body of a class or method.
    3124            8 :                 if (node.parent.kind === SyntaxKind.Parameter && isClassElement(node.parent.parent)) {
    3125            8 :                     // If the decorator's parent is a Parameter, we resolve the this container from
    3126            8 :                     // the grandparent class declaration.
    3127            8 :                     node = node.parent.parent;
    3128            8 :                 }
    3129            8 :                 else if (isClassElement(node.parent)) {
    3130            8 :                     // If the decorator's parent is a class element, we resolve the 'this' container
    3131            8 :                     // from the parent class declaration.
    3132            8 :                     node = node.parent;
    3133            8 :                 }
    3134            8 :                 break;
    3135            8 :         }
    3136            8 :     }
    3137            8 : }

    3475            8 :         case SyntaxKind.IfStatement:
    3476            8 :         case SyntaxKind.DoStatement:
    3477            8 :         case SyntaxKind.WhileStatement:
    3478            8 :         case SyntaxKind.ReturnStatement:
    3479            8 :         case SyntaxKind.WithStatement:
    3480            8 :         case SyntaxKind.SwitchStatement:
    3481            8 :         case SyntaxKind.CaseClause:
    3482            8 :         case SyntaxKind.ThrowStatement:
    3483            8 :             return (parent as ExpressionStatement).expression === node;
    3484            8 :         case SyntaxKind.ForStatement:
    3485            8 :             const forStatement = parent as ForStatement;
    3486            8 :             return (forStatement.initializer === node && forStatement.initializer.kind !== SyntaxKind.VariableDeclarationList) ||
    3487            8 :                 forStatement.condition === node ||
    3488            8 :                 forStatement.incrementor === node;
    3489            8 :         case SyntaxKind.ForInStatement:
    3490            8 :         case SyntaxKind.ForOfStatement:
    3491            8 :             const forInOrOfStatement = parent as ForInOrOfStatement;
    3492            8 :             return (forInOrOfStatement.initializer === node && forInOrOfStatement.initializer.kind !== SyntaxKind.VariableDeclarationList) ||
    3493            8 :                 forInOrOfStatement.expression === node;
    3494            8 :         case SyntaxKind.TypeAssertionExpression:
    3495            8 :         case SyntaxKind.AsExpression:
    3496            8 :             return node === (parent as AssertionExpression).expression;
    3497            8 :         case SyntaxKind.TemplateSpan:
    3498            8 :             return node === (parent as TemplateSpan).expression;
    3499            8 :         case SyntaxKind.ComputedPropertyName:
    3500            8 :             return node === (parent as ComputedPropertyName).expression;
    3501            8 :         case SyntaxKind.Decorator:
    3502            8 :         case SyntaxKind.JsxExpression:
    3503            8 :         case SyntaxKind.JsxSpreadAttribute:
    3504            8 :         case SyntaxKind.SpreadAssignment:
    3505            8 :             return true;
    3506            8 :         case SyntaxKind.ExpressionWithTypeArguments:
    3507            8 :             return (parent as ExpressionWithTypeArguments).expression === node && !isPartOfTypeNode(parent);
    3508            8 :         case SyntaxKind.ShorthandPropertyAssignment:
    3509            8 :             return (parent as ShorthandPropertyAssignment).objectAssignmentInitializer === node;
    3510            8 :         case SyntaxKind.SatisfiesExpression:
    3511            8 :             return node === (parent as SatisfiesExpression).expression;
    3512            8 :         default:
    3513            8 :             return isExpressionNode(parent);
    3514            8 :     }
    3515            8 : }

    3602            8 : export function isRequireCall(callExpression: Node, requireStringLiteralLikeArgument: true): callExpression is RequireOrImportCall & { expression: Identifier; arguments: [StringLiteralLike]; };
    3603            8 : /** @internal */
    3604            8 : export function isRequireCall(callExpression: Node, requireStringLiteralLikeArgument: boolean): callExpression is CallExpression;
    3605            8 : /** @internal */
    3606            8 : export function isRequireCall(callExpression: Node, requireStringLiteralLikeArgument: boolean): callExpression is CallExpression {
    3607            8 :     if (callExpression.kind !== SyntaxKind.CallExpression) {
    3608            8 :         return false;
    3609            8 :     }
    3610            8 :     const { expression, arguments: args } = callExpression as CallExpression;
    3611            8 : 
    3612            8 :     if (expression.kind !== SyntaxKind.Identifier || (expression as Identifier).escapedText !== "require") {
    3613            8 :         return false;
    3614            8 :     }
    3615            8 : 
    3616            8 :     if (args.length !== 1) {
    3617            8 :         return false;
    3618            8 :     }
    3619            8 :     const arg = args[0];
    3620            8 :     return !requireStringLiteralLikeArgument || isStringLiteralLike(arg);
    3621            8 : }

    3702            8 : function hasExpandoValueProperty(node: ObjectLiteralExpression, isPrototypeAssignment: boolean) {
    3703            8 :     return forEach(node.properties, p =>
    3704            8 :         isPropertyAssignment(p) &&
    3705            8 :         isIdentifier(p.name) &&
    3706            8 :         p.name.escapedText === "value" &&
    3707            8 :         p.initializer &&
    3708            8 :         getExpandoInitializer(p.initializer, isPrototypeAssignment));
    3709            8 : }
    3710            8 : 
    3711            8 : /**
    3712            8 :  * Get the assignment 'initializer' -- the righthand side-- when the initializer is container-like (See getExpandoInitializer).
    3713            8 :  * We treat the right hand side of assignments with container-like initializers as declarations.
    3714            8 :  *
    3715            8 :  * @internal
    3716            8 :  */
    3717            8 : export function getAssignedExpandoInitializer(node: Node | undefined): Expression | undefined {
    3718            8 :     if (node && node.parent && isBinaryExpression(node.parent) && node.parent.operatorToken.kind === SyntaxKind.EqualsToken) {
    3719            8 :         const isPrototypeAssignment = isPrototypeAccess(node.parent.left);
    3720            8 :         return getExpandoInitializer(node.parent.right, isPrototypeAssignment) ||
    3721            8 :             getDefaultedExpandoInitializer(node.parent.left, node.parent.right, isPrototypeAssignment);
    3722            8 :     }
    3723            8 :     if (node && isCallExpression(node) && isBindableObjectDefinePropertyCall(node)) {
    3724            8 :         const result = hasExpandoValueProperty(node.arguments[2], node.arguments[1].text === "prototype");
    3725            8 :         if (result) {
    3726            8 :             return result;
    3727            8 :         }
    3728            8 :     }
    3729            8 : }
    3730            8 : 
    3731            8 : /**
    3732            8 :  * Recognized expando initializers are:
    3733            8 :  * 1. (function() {})() -- IIFEs
    3734            8 :  * 2. function() { } -- Function expressions
    3735            8 :  * 3. class { } -- Class expressions
    3736            8 :  * 4. {} -- Empty object literals
    3737            8 :  * 5. { ... } -- Non-empty object literals, when used to initialize a prototype, like `C.prototype = { m() { } }`
    3738            8 :  *
    3739            8 :  * This function returns the provided initializer, or undefined if it is not valid.
    3740            8 :  *
    3741            8 :  * @internal
    3742            8 :  */
    3743            8 : export function getExpandoInitializer(initializer: Node, isPrototypeAssignment: boolean): Expression | undefined {
    3744            8 :     if (isCallExpression(initializer)) {
    3745            8 :         const e = skipParentheses(initializer.expression);
    3746            8 :         return e.kind === SyntaxKind.FunctionExpression || e.kind === SyntaxKind.ArrowFunction ? initializer : undefined;
    3747            8 :     }
    3748            8 :     if (
    3749            8 :         initializer.kind === SyntaxKind.FunctionExpression ||
    3750            8 :         initializer.kind === SyntaxKind.ClassExpression ||
    3751            8 :         initializer.kind === SyntaxKind.ArrowFunction
    3752            8 :     ) {
    3753            8 :         return initializer as Expression;
    3754            8 :     }
    3755            8 :     if (isObjectLiteralExpression(initializer) && (initializer.properties.length === 0 || isPrototypeAssignment)) {
    3756            8 :         return initializer;
    3757            8 :     }
    3758            8 : }
    3759            8 : 
    3760            8 : /**
    3761            8 :  * A defaulted expando initializer matches the pattern
    3762            8 :  * `Lhs = Lhs || ExpandoInitializer`
    3763            8 :  * or `var Lhs = Lhs || ExpandoInitializer`
    3764            8 :  *
    3765            8 :  * The second Lhs is required to be the same as the first except that it may be prefixed with
    3766            8 :  * 'window.', 'global.' or 'self.' The second Lhs is otherwise ignored by the binder and checker.
    3767            8 :  */
    3768            8 : function getDefaultedExpandoInitializer(name: Expression, initializer: Expression, isPrototypeAssignment: boolean) {
    3769            8 :     const e = isBinaryExpression(initializer)
    3770            8 :         && (initializer.operatorToken.kind === SyntaxKind.BarBarToken || initializer.operatorToken.kind === SyntaxKind.QuestionQuestionToken)
    3771            8 :         && getExpandoInitializer(initializer.right, isPrototypeAssignment);
    3772            8 :     if (e && isSameEntityName(name, initializer.left)) {
    3773            8 :         return e;
    3774            8 :     }
    3775            8 : }
    3776            8 : 
    3777            8 : /** @internal */
    3778            8 : export function isDefaultedExpandoInitializer(node: BinaryExpression) {
    3779            8 :     const name = isVariableDeclaration(node.parent) ? node.parent.name :
    3780            8 :         isBinaryExpression(node.parent) && node.parent.operatorToken.kind === SyntaxKind.EqualsToken ? node.parent.left :
    3781            8 :         undefined;
    3782            8 :     return name && getExpandoInitializer(node.right, isPrototypeAccess(name)) && isEntityNameExpression(name) && isSameEntityName(name, node.left);
    3783            8 : }

    3785            8 : /**
    3786            8 :  * Given an expando initializer, return its declaration name, or the left-hand side of the assignment if it's part of an assignment declaration.

    3789            8 :  */
    3790            8 : export function getNameOfExpando(node: Declaration): DeclarationName | undefined {
    3791            8 :     if (isBinaryExpression(node.parent)) {
    3792            8 :         const parent = ((node.parent.operatorToken.kind === SyntaxKind.BarBarToken || node.parent.operatorToken.kind === SyntaxKind.QuestionQuestionToken) && isBinaryExpression(node.parent.parent)) ? node.parent.parent : node.parent;
    3793            8 :         if (parent.operatorToken.kind === SyntaxKind.EqualsToken && isIdentifier(parent.left)) {
    3794            8 :             return parent.left;
    3795            8 :         }
    3796            8 :     }
    3797            8 :     else if (isVariableDeclaration(node.parent)) {
    3798            8 :         return node.parent.name;

    3801            8 : 
    3802            8 : /**
    3803            8 :  * Is the 'declared' name the same as the one in the initializer?
    3804            8 :  * @return true for identical entity names, as well as ones where the initializer is prefixed with
    3805            8 :  * 'window', 'self' or 'global'. For example:
    3806            8 :  *
    3807            8 :  * var my = my || {}
    3808            8 :  * var min = window.min || {}
    3809            8 :  * my.app = self.my.app || class { }
    3810            8 :  *
    3811            8 :  * @internal
    3812            8 :  */
    3813            8 : export function isSameEntityName(name: Expression, initializer: Expression): boolean {
    3814            8 :     if (isPropertyNameLiteral(name) && isPropertyNameLiteral(initializer)) {
    3815            8 :         return getTextOfIdentifierOrLiteral(name) === getTextOfIdentifierOrLiteral(initializer);
    3816            8 :     }
    3817            8 :     if (
    3818            8 :         isMemberName(name) && isLiteralLikeAccess(initializer) &&
    3819            8 :         (initializer.expression.kind === SyntaxKind.ThisKeyword ||
    3820            8 :             isIdentifier(initializer.expression) &&
    3821            8 :                 (initializer.expression.escapedText === "window" ||
    3822            8 :                     initializer.expression.escapedText === "self" ||
    3823            8 :                     initializer.expression.escapedText === "global"))
    3824            8 :     ) {
    3825            8 :         return isSameEntityName(name, getNameOrArgument(initializer));
    3826            8 :     }
    3827            8 :     if (isLiteralLikeAccess(name) && isLiteralLikeAccess(initializer)) {
    3828            8 :         return getElementOrPropertyAccessName(name) === getElementOrPropertyAccessName(initializer)
    3829            8 :             && isSameEntityName(name.expression, initializer.expression);
    3830            8 :     }
    3831            8 :     return false;
    3832            8 : }

    3931            8 : function getAssignmentDeclarationKindWorker(expr: BinaryExpression | CallExpression): AssignmentDeclarationKind {
    3932            8 :     if (isCallExpression(expr)) {
    3933            8 :         if (!isBindableObjectDefinePropertyCall(expr)) {
    3934            8 :             return AssignmentDeclarationKind.None;
    3935            8 :         }
    3936            8 :         const entityName = expr.arguments[0];
    3937            8 :         if (isExportsIdentifier(entityName) || isModuleExportsAccessExpression(entityName)) {
    3938            8 :             return AssignmentDeclarationKind.ObjectDefinePropertyExports;
    3939            8 :         }
    3940            8 :         if (isBindableStaticAccessExpression(entityName) && getElementOrPropertyAccessName(entityName) === "prototype") {
    3941            8 :             return AssignmentDeclarationKind.ObjectDefinePrototypeProperty;
    3942            8 :         }
    3943            8 :         return AssignmentDeclarationKind.ObjectDefinePropertyValue;
    3944            8 :     }
    3945            8 :     if (expr.operatorToken.kind !== SyntaxKind.EqualsToken || !isAccessExpression(expr.left) || isVoidZero(getRightMostAssignedExpression(expr))) {
    3946            8 :         return AssignmentDeclarationKind.None;
    3947            8 :     }
    3948            8 :     if (isBindableStaticNameExpression(expr.left.expression, /*excludeThisKeyword*/ true) && getElementOrPropertyAccessName(expr.left) === "prototype" && isObjectLiteralExpression(getInitializerOfBinaryExpression(expr))) {
    3949            8 :         // F.prototype = { ... }
    3950            8 :         return AssignmentDeclarationKind.Prototype;
    3951            8 :     }
    3952            8 :     return getAssignmentDeclarationPropertyAccessKind(expr.left);
    3953            8 : }
    3954            8 : 
    3955            8 : function isVoidZero(node: Node) {
    3956            8 :     return isVoidExpression(node) && isNumericLiteral(node.expression) && node.expression.text === "0";
    3957            8 : }
    3958            8 : 
    3959            8 : /**
    3960            8 :  * Does not handle signed numeric names like `a[+0]` - handling those would require handling prefix unary expressions
    3961            8 :  * throughout late binding handling as well, which is awkward (but ultimately probably doable if there is demand)
    3962            8 :  *
    3963            8 :  * @internal

    3966            8 :     if (isPropertyAccessExpression(node)) {
    3967            8 :         return node.name;

    3982            8 :     const name = getElementOrPropertyAccessArgumentExpressionOrName(node);
    3983            8 :     if (name) {
