    3994            8 : /** @internal */
    3995            8 : export function getAssignmentDeclarationPropertyAccessKind(lhs: AccessExpression): AssignmentDeclarationKind {
    3996            8 :     if (lhs.expression.kind === SyntaxKind.ThisKeyword) {
    3997            8 :         return AssignmentDeclarationKind.ThisProperty;
    3998            8 :     }
    3999            8 :     else if (isModuleExportsAccessExpression(lhs)) {
    4000            8 :         // module.exports = expr
    4001            8 :         return AssignmentDeclarationKind.ModuleExports;
    4002            8 :     }
    4003            8 :     else if (isBindableStaticNameExpression(lhs.expression, /*excludeThisKeyword*/ true)) {
    4004            8 :         if (isPrototypeAccess(lhs.expression)) {
    4005            8 :             // F.G....prototype.x = expr
    4006            8 :             return AssignmentDeclarationKind.PrototypeProperty;
    4007            8 :         }
    4008            8 : 
    4009            8 :         let nextToLast = lhs;
    4010            8 :         while (!isIdentifier(nextToLast.expression)) {
    4011            8 :             nextToLast = nextToLast.expression as Exclude<BindableStaticNameExpression, Identifier>;
    4012            8 :         }
    4013            8 :         const id = nextToLast.expression;
    4014            8 :         if (
    4015            8 :             (id.escapedText === "exports" ||
    4016            8 :                 id.escapedText === "module" && getElementOrPropertyAccessName(nextToLast) === "exports") &&
    4017            8 :             // ExportsProperty does not support binding with computed names
    4018            8 :             isBindableStaticAccessExpression(lhs)
    4019            8 :         ) {
    4020            8 :             // exports.name = expr OR module.exports.name = expr OR exports["name"] = expr ...
    4021            8 :             return AssignmentDeclarationKind.ExportsProperty;
    4022            8 :         }
    4023            8 :         if (isBindableStaticNameExpression(lhs, /*excludeThisKeyword*/ true) || (isElementAccessExpression(lhs) && isDynamicName(lhs))) {
    4024            8 :             // F.G...x = expr
    4025            8 :             return AssignmentDeclarationKind.Property;
    4026            8 :         }
    4027            8 :     }
    4028            8 : 
    4029            8 :     return AssignmentDeclarationKind.None;
    4030            8 : }
    4031            8 : 
    4032            8 : /** @internal */

    4034            8 :     while (isBinaryExpression(expr.right)) {
    4035            8 :         expr = expr.right;
    4036            8 :     }
    4037            8 :     return expr.right;
    4038            8 : }

    4386            8 :  * This function checks multiple locations for JSDoc comments that apply to a host node.
    4387            8 :  * At each location, the whole comment may apply to the node, or only a specific tag in
    4388            8 :  * the comment. In the first case, location adds the entire {@link JSDoc} object. In the
    4389            8 :  * second case, it adds the applicable {@link JSDocTag}.
    4390            8 :  *
    4391            8 :  * For example, a JSDoc comment before a parameter adds the entire {@link JSDoc}. But a
    4392            8 :  * `@param` tag on the parent function only adds the {@link JSDocTag} for the `@param`.
    4393            8 :  *
    4394            8 :  * ```ts
    4395            8 :  * /** JSDoc will be returned for `a` *\/
    4396            8 :  * const a = 0
    4397            8 :  * /**
    4398            8 :  *  * Entire JSDoc will be returned for `b`
    4399            8 :  *  * @param c JSDocTag will be returned for `c`
    4400            8 :  *  *\/
    4401            8 :  * function b(/** JSDoc will be returned for `c` *\/ c) {}
    4402            8 :  * ```
    4403            8 :  */
    4404            8 : export function getJSDocCommentsAndTags(hostNode: Node): readonly (JSDoc | JSDocTag)[];
    4405            8 : /** @internal separate signature so that stripInternal can remove noCache from the public API */
    4406            8 : // eslint-disable-next-line @typescript-eslint/unified-signatures
    4407            8 : export function getJSDocCommentsAndTags(hostNode: Node, noCache?: boolean): readonly (JSDoc | JSDocTag)[];
    4408            8 : export function getJSDocCommentsAndTags(hostNode: Node, noCache?: boolean): readonly (JSDoc | JSDocTag)[] {
    4409            8 :     let result: (JSDoc | JSDocTag)[] | undefined;
    4410            8 :     // Pull parameter comments from declaring function as well
    4411            8 :     if (isVariableLike(hostNode) && hasInitializer(hostNode) && hasJSDocNodes(hostNode.initializer!)) {
    4412            8 :         result = addRange(result, filterOwnedJSDocTags(hostNode, hostNode.initializer.jsDoc!));
    4413            8 :     }
    4414            8 : 
    4415            8 :     let node: Node | undefined = hostNode;
    4416            8 :     while (node && node.parent) {
    4417            8 :         if (hasJSDocNodes(node)) {
    4418            8 :             result = addRange(result, filterOwnedJSDocTags(hostNode, node.jsDoc!));
    4419            8 :         }
    4420            8 : 
    4421            8 :         if (node.kind === SyntaxKind.Parameter) {
    4422            8 :             result = addRange(result, (noCache ? getJSDocParameterTagsNoCache : getJSDocParameterTags)(node as ParameterDeclaration));
    4423            8 :             break;
    4424            8 :         }
    4425            8 :         if (node.kind === SyntaxKind.TypeParameter) {
    4426            8 :             result = addRange(result, (noCache ? getJSDocTypeParameterTagsNoCache : getJSDocTypeParameterTags)(node as TypeParameterDeclaration));
    4427            8 :             break;
    4428            8 :         }
    4429            8 :         node = getNextJSDocCommentLocation(node);
    4430            8 :     }
    4431            8 :     return result || emptyArray;
    4432            8 : }
    4433            8 : 
    4434            8 : function filterOwnedJSDocTags(hostNode: Node, comments: JSDocArray) {
    4435            8 :     const lastJsDoc = last(comments);
    4436            8 :     return flatMap<JSDoc, JSDoc | JSDocTag>(comments, jsDoc => {
    4437            8 :         if (jsDoc === lastJsDoc) {
    4438            8 :             const ownedTags = filter(jsDoc.tags, tag => ownsJSDocTag(hostNode, tag));
    4439            8 :             return jsDoc.tags === ownedTags ? [jsDoc] : ownedTags;
    4440            8 :         }
    4441            8 :         else {
    4442            8 :             return filter(jsDoc.tags, isJSDocOverloadTag);
    4443            8 :         }
    4444            8 :     });
    4445            8 : }

    4447            8 : /**
    4448            8 :  * Determines whether a host node owns a jsDoc tag. A `@type`/`@satisfies` tag attached to a
    4449            8 :  * a ParenthesizedExpression belongs only to the ParenthesizedExpression.
    4450            8 :  */
    4451            8 : function ownsJSDocTag(hostNode: Node, tag: JSDocTag) {
    4452            8 :     return !(isJSDocTypeTag(tag) || isJSDocSatisfiesTag(tag))
    4453            8 :         || !tag.parent
    4454            8 :         || !isJSDoc(tag.parent)
    4455            8 :         || !isParenthesizedExpression(tag.parent.parent)
    4456            8 :         || tag.parent.parent === hostNode;
    4457            8 : }

    4460            8 : export function getNextJSDocCommentLocation(node: Node) {

    4462            8 :     if (
    4463            8 :         parent.kind === SyntaxKind.PropertyAssignment ||
    4464            8 :         parent.kind === SyntaxKind.ExportAssignment ||
    4465            8 :         parent.kind === SyntaxKind.PropertyDeclaration ||

    4467            8 :         parent.kind === SyntaxKind.ReturnStatement ||

    4594            8 :     Definite,
    4595            8 :     Compound,

    4597            8 : 
    4598            8 : type AssignmentTarget =
    4599            8 :     | BinaryExpression
    4600            8 :     | PrefixUnaryExpression
    4601            8 :     | PostfixUnaryExpression
    4602            8 :     | ForInOrOfStatement;
    4603            8 : 
    4604            8 : function getAssignmentTarget(node: Node): AssignmentTarget | undefined {
    4605            8 :     let parent = node.parent;
    4606            8 :     while (true) {
    4607            8 :         switch (parent.kind) {
    4608            8 :             case SyntaxKind.BinaryExpression:
    4609            8 :                 const binaryExpression = parent as BinaryExpression;
    4610            8 :                 const binaryOperator = binaryExpression.operatorToken.kind;
    4611            8 :                 return isAssignmentOperator(binaryOperator) && binaryExpression.left === node ? binaryExpression : undefined;
    4612            8 :             case SyntaxKind.PrefixUnaryExpression:
    4613            8 :             case SyntaxKind.PostfixUnaryExpression:
    4614            8 :                 const unaryExpression = parent as PrefixUnaryExpression | PostfixUnaryExpression;
    4615            8 :                 const unaryOperator = unaryExpression.operator;
    4616            8 :                 return unaryOperator === SyntaxKind.PlusPlusToken || unaryOperator === SyntaxKind.MinusMinusToken ? unaryExpression : undefined;
    4617            8 :             case SyntaxKind.ForInStatement:
    4618            8 :             case SyntaxKind.ForOfStatement:
    4619            8 :                 const forInOrOfStatement = parent as ForInOrOfStatement;
    4620            8 :                 return forInOrOfStatement.initializer === node ? forInOrOfStatement : undefined;
    4621            8 :             case SyntaxKind.ParenthesizedExpression:
    4622            8 :             case SyntaxKind.ArrayLiteralExpression:
    4623            8 :             case SyntaxKind.SpreadElement:
    4624            8 :             case SyntaxKind.NonNullExpression:
    4625            8 :                 node = parent;
    4626            8 :                 break;
    4627            8 :             case SyntaxKind.SpreadAssignment:
    4628            8 :                 node = parent.parent;
    4629            8 :                 break;
    4630            8 :             case SyntaxKind.ShorthandPropertyAssignment:
    4631            8 :                 if ((parent as ShorthandPropertyAssignment).name !== node) {
    4632            8 :                     return undefined;
    4633            8 :                 }
    4634            8 :                 node = parent.parent;
    4635            8 :                 break;
    4636            8 :             case SyntaxKind.PropertyAssignment:
    4637            8 :                 if ((parent as PropertyAssignment).name === node) {
    4638            8 :                     return undefined;
    4639            8 :                 }
    4640            8 :                 node = parent.parent;
    4641            8 :                 break;
    4642            8 :             default:
    4643            8 :                 return undefined;
    4644            8 :         }
    4645            8 :         parent = node.parent;
    4646            8 :     }
    4647            8 : }
    4648            8 : 
    4649            8 : /** @internal */
    4650            8 : export function getAssignmentTargetKind(node: Node): AssignmentKind {
    4651            8 :     const target = getAssignmentTarget(node);
    4652            8 :     if (!target) {
    4653            8 :         return AssignmentKind.None;
    4654            8 :     }
    4655            8 :     switch (target.kind) {
    4656            8 :         case SyntaxKind.BinaryExpression:
    4657            8 :             const binaryOperator = target.operatorToken.kind;
    4658            8 :             return binaryOperator === SyntaxKind.EqualsToken || isLogicalOrCoalescingAssignmentOperator(binaryOperator) ?
    4659            8 :                 AssignmentKind.Definite :
    4660            8 :                 AssignmentKind.Compound;
    4661            8 :         case SyntaxKind.PrefixUnaryExpression:
    4662            8 :         case SyntaxKind.PostfixUnaryExpression:
    4663            8 :             return AssignmentKind.Compound;
    4664            8 :         case SyntaxKind.ForInStatement:
    4665            8 :         case SyntaxKind.ForOfStatement:
    4666            8 :             return AssignmentKind.Definite;
    4667            8 :     }
    4668            8 : }
    4669            8 : 
    4670            8 : // A node is an assignment target if it is on the left hand side of an '=' token, if it is parented by a property
    4671            8 : // assignment in an object literal that is an assignment target, or if it is parented by an array literal that is
    4672            8 : // an assignment target. Examples include 'a = xxx', '{ p: a } = xxx', '[{ a }] = xxx'.
    4673            8 : // (Note that `p` is not a target in the above examples, only `a`.)
    4674            8 : /** @internal */
    4675            8 : export function isAssignmentTarget(node: Node): boolean {
    4676            8 :     return !!getAssignmentTarget(node);
    4677            8 : }
    4678            8 : 
    4679            8 : function isCompoundLikeAssignment(assignment: AssignmentExpression<EqualsToken>): boolean {
    4680            8 :     const right = skipParentheses(assignment.right);
    4681            8 :     return right.kind === SyntaxKind.BinaryExpression && isShiftOperatorOrHigher((right as BinaryExpression).operatorToken.kind);
    4682            8 : }

    4687            8 :     return !!target && isAssignmentExpression(target, /*excludeCompoundAssignment*/ true) && isCompoundLikeAssignment(target);
    4688            8 : }

    4827            8 : // See GH#16030
    4828            8 : /** @internal */
    4829            8 : export function getDeclarationFromName(name: Node): Declaration | undefined {
    4830            8 :     const parent = name.parent;
    4831            8 :     switch (name.kind) {
    4832            8 :         case SyntaxKind.StringLiteral:
    4833            8 :         case SyntaxKind.NoSubstitutionTemplateLiteral:
    4834            8 :         case SyntaxKind.NumericLiteral:
    4835            8 :             if (isComputedPropertyName(parent)) return parent.parent;
    4836            8 :             // falls through
    4837            8 :         case SyntaxKind.Identifier:
    4838            8 :             if (isDeclaration(parent)) {
    4839            8 :                 return parent.name === name ? parent : undefined;
    4840            8 :             }
    4841            8 :             else if (isQualifiedName(parent)) {
    4842            8 :                 const tag = parent.parent;
    4843            8 :                 return isJSDocParameterTag(tag) && tag.name === parent ? tag : undefined;
    4844            8 :             }
    4845            8 :             else {
    4846            8 :                 const binExp = parent.parent;
    4847            8 :                 return isBinaryExpression(binExp) &&
    4848            8 :                         getAssignmentDeclarationKind(binExp) !== AssignmentDeclarationKind.None &&
    4849            8 :                         ((binExp.left as BindableStaticNameExpression).symbol || binExp.symbol) &&
    4850            8 :                         getNameOfDeclaration(binExp) === name
    4851            8 :                     ? binExp
    4852            8 :                     : undefined;
    4853            8 :             }
    4854            8 :         case SyntaxKind.PrivateIdentifier:
    4855            8 :             return isDeclaration(parent) && parent.name === name ? parent : undefined;
    4856            8 :         default:
    4857            8 :             return undefined;
    4858            8 :     }
    4859            8 : }

    4863            8 :     return isStringOrNumericLiteralLike(node) &&
    4864            8 :         node.parent.kind === SyntaxKind.ComputedPropertyName &&

    4868            8 : // Return true if the given identifier is classified as an IdentifierName
    4869            8 : /** @internal */
    4870            8 : export function isIdentifierName(node: Identifier): boolean {
    4871            8 :     const parent = node.parent;
    4872            8 :     switch (parent.kind) {
    4873            8 :         case SyntaxKind.PropertyDeclaration:
    4874            8 :         case SyntaxKind.PropertySignature:
    4875            8 :         case SyntaxKind.MethodDeclaration:
    4876            8 :         case SyntaxKind.MethodSignature:
    4877            8 :         case SyntaxKind.GetAccessor:
    4878            8 :         case SyntaxKind.SetAccessor:
    4879            8 :         case SyntaxKind.EnumMember:
    4880            8 :         case SyntaxKind.PropertyAssignment:
    4881            8 :         case SyntaxKind.PropertyAccessExpression:
    4882            8 :             // Name in member declaration or property name in property access
    4883            8 :             return (parent as NamedDeclaration | PropertyAccessExpression).name === node;
    4884            8 :         case SyntaxKind.QualifiedName:
    4885            8 :             // Name on right hand side of dot in a type query or type reference
    4886            8 :             return (parent as QualifiedName).right === node;
    4887            8 :         case SyntaxKind.BindingElement:
    4888            8 :         case SyntaxKind.ImportSpecifier:
    4889            8 :             // Property name in binding element or import specifier
    4890            8 :             return (parent as BindingElement | ImportSpecifier).propertyName === node;
    4891            8 :         case SyntaxKind.ExportSpecifier:
    4892            8 :         case SyntaxKind.JsxAttribute:
    4893            8 :         case SyntaxKind.JsxSelfClosingElement:
    4894            8 :         case SyntaxKind.JsxOpeningElement:
    4895            8 :         case SyntaxKind.JsxClosingElement:
    4896            8 :             // Any name in an export specifier or JSX Attribute or Jsx Element
    4897            8 :             return true;
    4898            8 :     }
    4899            8 :     return false;
    4900            8 : }

    4902            8 : // An alias symbol is created by one of the following declarations:
    4903            8 : // import <symbol> = ...
    4904            8 : // import <symbol> from ...
    4905            8 : // import * as <symbol> from ...
    4906            8 : // import { x as <symbol> } from ...

    4908            8 : // export * as ns <symbol> from ...

    4910            8 : // export default <EntityNameExpression>
    4911            8 : // module.exports = <EntityNameExpression>
    4912            8 : // module.exports.x = <EntityNameExpression>
    4913            8 : // const x = require("...")
    4914            8 : // const { x } = require("...")
    4915            8 : // const x = require("...").y
    4916            8 : // const { x } = require("...").y

    4918            8 : export function isAliasSymbolDeclaration(node: Node): boolean {
    4919            8 :     if (
    4920            8 :         node.kind === SyntaxKind.ImportEqualsDeclaration ||
    4921            8 :         node.kind === SyntaxKind.NamespaceExportDeclaration ||
    4922            8 :         node.kind === SyntaxKind.ImportClause && !!(node as ImportClause).name ||
    4923            8 :         node.kind === SyntaxKind.NamespaceImport ||
    4924            8 :         node.kind === SyntaxKind.NamespaceExport ||
    4925            8 :         node.kind === SyntaxKind.ImportSpecifier ||
    4926            8 :         node.kind === SyntaxKind.ExportSpecifier ||
    4927            8 :         node.kind === SyntaxKind.ExportAssignment && exportAssignmentIsAlias(node as ExportAssignment)
    4928            8 :     ) {
    4929            8 :         return true;
    4930            8 :     }
    4931            8 : 
    4932            8 :     return isInJSFile(node) && (
    4933            8 :         isBinaryExpression(node) && getAssignmentDeclarationKind(node) === AssignmentDeclarationKind.ModuleExports && exportAssignmentIsAlias(node) ||
    4934            8 :         isPropertyAccessExpression(node)
    4935            8 :             && isBinaryExpression(node.parent)
    4936            8 :             && node.parent.left === node
    4937            8 :             && node.parent.operatorToken.kind === SyntaxKind.EqualsToken
    4938            8 :             && isAliasableExpression(node.parent.right)
    4939            8 :     );
    4940            8 : }

    5110            8 : export const enum FunctionFlags {
    5111            8 :     Normal = 0,             // Function is a normal function
    5112            8 :     Generator = 1 << 0,     // Function is a generator function or async generator function
    5113            8 :     Async = 1 << 1,         // Function is an async function or an async generator function
    5114            8 :     Invalid = 1 << 2,       // Function is a signature or overload and does not have a body.
    5115            8 :     AsyncGenerator = Async | Generator, // Function is an async generator function

    5118            8 : /** @internal */
    5119            8 : export function getFunctionFlags(node: SignatureDeclaration | undefined) {
    5120            8 :     if (!node) {
    5121            8 :         return FunctionFlags.Invalid;
    5122            8 :     }
    5123            8 : 
    5124            8 :     let flags = FunctionFlags.Normal;
    5125            8 :     switch (node.kind) {
    5126            8 :         case SyntaxKind.FunctionDeclaration:
    5127            8 :         case SyntaxKind.FunctionExpression:
    5128            8 :         case SyntaxKind.MethodDeclaration:
    5129            8 :             if (node.asteriskToken) {
    5130            8 :                 flags |= FunctionFlags.Generator;
    5131            8 :             }
    5132            8 :             // falls through
    5133            8 : 
    5134            8 :         case SyntaxKind.ArrowFunction:
    5135            8 :             if (hasSyntacticModifier(node, ModifierFlags.Async)) {
    5136            8 :                 flags |= FunctionFlags.Async;
    5137            8 :             }
    5138            8 :             break;
    5139            8 :     }
    5140            8 : 
    5141            8 :     if (!(node as FunctionLikeDeclaration).body) {
    5142            8 :         flags |= FunctionFlags.Invalid;
    5143            8 :     }
    5144            8 : 
    5145            8 :     return flags;
    5146            8 : }

    5172            8 : /**
    5173            8 :  * A declaration has a dynamic name if all of the following are true:
    5174            8 :  *   1. The declaration has a computed property name.
    5175            8 :  *   2. The computed name is *not* expressed as a StringLiteral.
    5176            8 :  *   3. The computed name is *not* expressed as a NumericLiteral.
    5177            8 :  *   4. The computed name is *not* expressed as a PlusToken or MinusToken
    5178            8 :  *      immediately followed by a NumericLiteral.
    5179            8 :  *
    5180            8 :  * @internal
    5181            8 :  */

    5187            8 : /** @internal */
    5188            8 : export function isDynamicName(name: DeclarationName): boolean {
    5189            8 :     if (!(name.kind === SyntaxKind.ComputedPropertyName || name.kind === SyntaxKind.ElementAccessExpression)) {
    5190            8 :         return false;
    5191            8 :     }
    5192            8 :     const expr = isElementAccessExpression(name) ? skipParentheses(name.argumentExpression) : name.expression;
    5193            8 :     return !isStringOrNumericLiteralLike(expr) &&
    5194            8 :         !isSignedNumericLiteral(expr);

    5197            8 : /** @internal */
    5198            8 : export function getPropertyNameForPropertyNameNode(name: PropertyName | JsxAttributeName): __String | undefined {
    5199            8 :     switch (name.kind) {
    5200            8 :         case SyntaxKind.Identifier:
    5201            8 :         case SyntaxKind.PrivateIdentifier:
    5202            8 :             return name.escapedText;
    5203            8 :         case SyntaxKind.StringLiteral:
    5204            8 :         case SyntaxKind.NoSubstitutionTemplateLiteral:
    5205            8 :         case SyntaxKind.NumericLiteral:
    5206            8 :             return escapeLeadingUnderscores(name.text);
    5207            8 :         case SyntaxKind.ComputedPropertyName:
    5208            8 :             const nameExpression = name.expression;
    5209            8 :             if (isStringOrNumericLiteralLike(nameExpression)) {
    5210            8 :                 return escapeLeadingUnderscores(nameExpression.text);
    5211            8 :             }
    5212            8 :             else if (isSignedNumericLiteral(nameExpression)) {
    5213            8 :                 if (nameExpression.operator === SyntaxKind.MinusToken) {
    5214            8 :                     return tokenToString(nameExpression.operator) + nameExpression.operand.text as __String;
    5215            8 :                 }
    5216            8 :                 return nameExpression.operand.text as __String;
    5217            8 :             }
    5218            8 :             return undefined;
    5219            8 :         case SyntaxKind.JsxNamespacedName:
    5220            8 :             return getEscapedTextOfJsxNamespacedName(name);
    5221            8 :         default:
    5222            8 :             return Debug.assertNever(name);
    5223            8 :     }
    5224            8 : }

    5296            8 : /**
    5297            8 :  * Indicates whether an expression is an anonymous function definition.

    5300            8 :  * @internal
    5301            8 :  */
    5302            8 : export function isAnonymousFunctionDefinition(node: Expression, cb?: (node: AnonymousFunctionDefinition) => boolean): node is WrappedExpression<AnonymousFunctionDefinition> {
    5303            8 :     node = skipOuterExpressions(node);
    5304            8 :     switch (node.kind) {
    5305            8 :         case SyntaxKind.ClassExpression:
    5306            8 :             if (classHasDeclaredOrExplicitlyAssignedName(node as ClassExpression)) {
    5307            8 :                 return false;
    5308            8 :             }

    5339            8 : export function isNamedEvaluationSource(node: Node): node is NamedEvaluationSource {
    5340            8 :     switch (node.kind) {
    5341            8 :         case SyntaxKind.PropertyAssignment:
    5342            8 :             return !isProtoSetter((node as PropertyAssignment).name);
    5343            8 :         case SyntaxKind.ShorthandPropertyAssignment:
    5344            8 :             return !!(node as ShorthandPropertyAssignment).objectAssignmentInitializer;
    5345            8 :         case SyntaxKind.VariableDeclaration:
    5346            8 :             return isIdentifier((node as VariableDeclaration).name) && !!(node as VariableDeclaration).initializer;
    5347            8 :         case SyntaxKind.Parameter:
    5348            8 :             return isIdentifier((node as ParameterDeclaration).name) && !!(node as VariableDeclaration).initializer && !(node as BindingElement).dotDotDotToken;
    5349            8 :         case SyntaxKind.BindingElement:
    5350            8 :             return isIdentifier((node as BindingElement).name) && !!(node as VariableDeclaration).initializer && !(node as BindingElement).dotDotDotToken;
    5351            8 :         case SyntaxKind.PropertyDeclaration:
    5352            8 :             return !!(node as PropertyDeclaration).initializer;
    5353            8 :         case SyntaxKind.BinaryExpression:
    5354            8 :             switch ((node as BinaryExpression).operatorToken.kind) {
    5355            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.EqualsToken:
    5356            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.AmpersandAmpersandEqualsToken:
    5357            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.BarBarEqualsToken:
    5358            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.QuestionQuestionEqualsToken:
    5359            8 :                     return isIdentifier((node as BinaryExpression).left);
    5360            8 :             }
    5361            8 :             break;
    5362            8 :         case SyntaxKind.ExportAssignment:
    5363            8 :             return true;
    5364            8 :     }
    5365            8 :     return false;
    5366            8 : }
    5367            8 : 
    5368            8 : /** @internal */
    5369            8 : export type NamedEvaluation =
    5370            8 :     | PropertyAssignment & { readonly name: Identifier; readonly initializer: WrappedExpression<AnonymousFunctionDefinition>; }
    5371            8 :     | ShorthandPropertyAssignment & { readonly objectAssignmentInitializer: WrappedExpression<AnonymousFunctionDefinition>; }
    5372            8 :     | VariableDeclaration & { readonly name: Identifier; readonly initializer: WrappedExpression<AnonymousFunctionDefinition>; }
    5373            8 :     | ParameterDeclaration & { readonly name: Identifier; readonly dotDotDotToken: undefined; readonly initializer: WrappedExpression<AnonymousFunctionDefinition>; }
    5374            8 :     | BindingElement & { readonly name: Identifier; readonly dotDotDotToken: undefined; readonly initializer: WrappedExpression<AnonymousFunctionDefinition>; }
    5375            8 :     | PropertyDeclaration & { readonly initializer: WrappedExpression<AnonymousFunctionDefinition>; }
    5376            8 :     | AssignmentExpression<EqualsToken> & { readonly left: Identifier; readonly right: WrappedExpression<AnonymousFunctionDefinition>; }
    5377            8 :     | AssignmentExpression<AmpersandAmpersandEqualsToken | BarBarEqualsToken | QuestionQuestionEqualsToken> & { readonly left: Identifier; readonly right: WrappedExpression<AnonymousFunctionDefinition>; }
    5378            8 :     | ExportAssignment & { readonly expression: WrappedExpression<AnonymousFunctionDefinition>; };
    5379            8 : 
    5380            8 : /** @internal */
    5381            8 : export function isNamedEvaluation(node: Node, cb?: (node: AnonymousFunctionDefinition) => boolean): node is NamedEvaluation {
    5382            8 :     if (!isNamedEvaluationSource(node)) return false;
    5383            8 :     switch (node.kind) {
    5384            8 :         case SyntaxKind.PropertyAssignment:
    5385            8 :             return isAnonymousFunctionDefinition(node.initializer, cb);
    5386            8 :         case SyntaxKind.ShorthandPropertyAssignment:
    5387            8 :             return isAnonymousFunctionDefinition(node.objectAssignmentInitializer, cb);
    5388            8 :         case SyntaxKind.VariableDeclaration:
    5389            8 :         case SyntaxKind.Parameter:
    5390            8 :         case SyntaxKind.BindingElement:
    5391            8 :         case SyntaxKind.PropertyDeclaration:
    5392            8 :             return isAnonymousFunctionDefinition(node.initializer, cb);
    5393            8 :         case SyntaxKind.BinaryExpression:
    5394            8 :             return isAnonymousFunctionDefinition(node.right, cb);
    5395            8 :         case SyntaxKind.ExportAssignment:
    5396            8 :             return isAnonymousFunctionDefinition(node.expression, cb);
    5397            8 :     }
    5398            8 : }

    5465            8 : /** @internal */
    5466            8 : export function getOperatorAssociativity(kind: SyntaxKind, operator: SyntaxKind, hasArguments?: boolean) {
    5467            8 :     switch (kind) {
    5468            8 :         case SyntaxKind.NewExpression:
    5469            8 :             return hasArguments ? Associativity.Left : Associativity.Right;
    5470            8 : 
    5471            8 :         case SyntaxKind.PrefixUnaryExpression:
    5472            8 :         case SyntaxKind.TypeOfExpression:
    5473            8 :         case SyntaxKind.VoidExpression:
    5474            8 :         case SyntaxKind.DeleteExpression:
    5475            8 :         case SyntaxKind.AwaitExpression:
    5476            8 :         case SyntaxKind.ConditionalExpression:
    5477            8 :         case SyntaxKind.YieldExpression:
    5478            8 :             return Associativity.Right;
    5479            8 : 
    5480            8 :         case SyntaxKind.BinaryExpression:
    5481            8 :             switch (operator) {
    5482            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.AsteriskAsteriskToken:
    5483            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.EqualsToken:
    5484            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.PlusEqualsToken:
    5485            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.MinusEqualsToken:
    5486            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.AsteriskAsteriskEqualsToken:
    5487            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.AsteriskEqualsToken:
    5488            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.SlashEqualsToken:
    5489            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.PercentEqualsToken:
    5490            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.LessThanLessThanEqualsToken:
    5491            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.GreaterThanGreaterThanEqualsToken:
    5492            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.GreaterThanGreaterThanGreaterThanEqualsToken:
    5493            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.AmpersandEqualsToken:
    5494            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.CaretEqualsToken:
    5495            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.BarEqualsToken:
    5496            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.BarBarEqualsToken:
    5497            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.AmpersandAmpersandEqualsToken:
    5498            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.QuestionQuestionEqualsToken:
    5499            8 :                     return Associativity.Right;
    5500            8 :             }
    5501            8 :     }
    5502            8 :     return Associativity.Left;
    5503            8 : }

    5506            8 : export function getExpressionPrecedence(expression: Expression) {

    5508            8 :     const hasArguments = expression.kind === SyntaxKind.NewExpression && (expression as NewExpression).arguments !== undefined;

    5512            8 : /** @internal */
    5513            8 : export function getOperator(expression: Expression): SyntaxKind {
    5514            8 :     if (expression.kind === SyntaxKind.BinaryExpression) {
    5515            8 :         return (expression as BinaryExpression).operatorToken.kind;
    5516            8 :     }
    5517            8 :     else if (expression.kind === SyntaxKind.PrefixUnaryExpression || expression.kind === SyntaxKind.PostfixUnaryExpression) {
    5518            8 :         return (expression as PrefixUnaryExpression | PostfixUnaryExpression).operator;
    5519            8 :     }
    5520            8 :     else {
    5521            8 :         return expression.kind;
    5522            8 :     }
    5523            8 : }

    5525            8 : /** @internal */
    5526            8 : export const enum OperatorPrecedence {
    5527            8 :     // Expression:
    5528            8 :     //     AssignmentExpression
    5529            8 :     //     Expression `,` AssignmentExpression
    5530            8 :     Comma,
    5531            8 : 
    5532            8 :     // NOTE: `Spread` is higher than `Comma` due to how it is parsed in |ElementList|
    5533            8 :     // SpreadElement:
    5534            8 :     //     `...` AssignmentExpression
    5535            8 :     Spread,
    5536            8 : 
    5537            8 :     // AssignmentExpression:
    5538            8 :     //     ConditionalExpression
    5539            8 :     //     YieldExpression
    5540            8 :     //     ArrowFunction
    5541            8 :     //     AsyncArrowFunction
    5542            8 :     //     LeftHandSideExpression `=` AssignmentExpression
    5543            8 :     //     LeftHandSideExpression AssignmentOperator AssignmentExpression
    5544            8 :     //
    5545            8 :     // NOTE: AssignmentExpression is broken down into several precedences due to the requirements
    5546            8 :     //       of the parenthesizer rules.
    5547            8 : 
    5548            8 :     // AssignmentExpression: YieldExpression
    5549            8 :     // YieldExpression:
    5550            8 :     //     `yield`
    5551            8 :     //     `yield` AssignmentExpression
    5552            8 :     //     `yield` `*` AssignmentExpression
    5553            8 :     Yield,
    5554            8 : 
    5555            8 :     // AssignmentExpression: LeftHandSideExpression `=` AssignmentExpression
    5556            8 :     // AssignmentExpression: LeftHandSideExpression AssignmentOperator AssignmentExpression
    5557            8 :     // AssignmentOperator: one of
    5558            8 :     //     `*=` `/=` `%=` `+=` `-=` `<<=` `>>=` `>>>=` `&=` `^=` `|=` `**=`
    5559            8 :     Assignment,
    5560            8 : 
    5561            8 :     // NOTE: `Conditional` is considered higher than `Assignment` here, but in reality they have
    5562            8 :     //       the same precedence.
    5563            8 :     // AssignmentExpression: ConditionalExpression
    5564            8 :     // ConditionalExpression:
    5565            8 :     //     ShortCircuitExpression
    5566            8 :     //     ShortCircuitExpression `?` AssignmentExpression `:` AssignmentExpression
    5567            8 :     // ShortCircuitExpression:
    5568            8 :     //     LogicalORExpression
    5569            8 :     //     CoalesceExpression
    5570            8 :     Conditional,
    5571            8 : 
    5572            8 :     // CoalesceExpression:
    5573            8 :     //     CoalesceExpressionHead `??` BitwiseORExpression
    5574            8 :     // CoalesceExpressionHead:
    5575            8 :     //     CoalesceExpression
    5576            8 :     //     BitwiseORExpression
    5577            8 :     Coalesce = Conditional, // NOTE: This is wrong
    5578            8 : 
    5579            8 :     // LogicalORExpression:
    5580            8 :     //     LogicalANDExpression
    5581            8 :     //     LogicalORExpression `||` LogicalANDExpression
    5582            8 :     LogicalOR,
    5583            8 : 
    5584            8 :     // LogicalANDExpression:
    5585            8 :     //     BitwiseORExpression
    5586            8 :     //     LogicalANDExprerssion `&&` BitwiseORExpression
    5587            8 :     LogicalAND,
    5588            8 : 
    5589            8 :     // BitwiseORExpression:
    5590            8 :     //     BitwiseXORExpression
    5591            8 :     //     BitwiseORExpression `^` BitwiseXORExpression
    5592            8 :     BitwiseOR,
    5593            8 : 
    5594            8 :     // BitwiseXORExpression:
    5595            8 :     //     BitwiseANDExpression
    5596            8 :     //     BitwiseXORExpression `^` BitwiseANDExpression
    5597            8 :     BitwiseXOR,
    5598            8 : 
    5599            8 :     // BitwiseANDExpression:
    5600            8 :     //     EqualityExpression
    5601            8 :     //     BitwiseANDExpression `^` EqualityExpression
    5602            8 :     BitwiseAND,
    5603            8 : 
    5604            8 :     // EqualityExpression:
    5605            8 :     //     RelationalExpression
    5606            8 :     //     EqualityExpression `==` RelationalExpression
    5607            8 :     //     EqualityExpression `!=` RelationalExpression
    5608            8 :     //     EqualityExpression `===` RelationalExpression
    5609            8 :     //     EqualityExpression `!==` RelationalExpression
    5610            8 :     Equality,
    5611            8 : 
    5612            8 :     // RelationalExpression:
    5613            8 :     //     ShiftExpression
    5614            8 :     //     RelationalExpression `<` ShiftExpression
    5615            8 :     //     RelationalExpression `>` ShiftExpression
    5616            8 :     //     RelationalExpression `<=` ShiftExpression
    5617            8 :     //     RelationalExpression `>=` ShiftExpression
    5618            8 :     //     RelationalExpression `instanceof` ShiftExpression
    5619            8 :     //     RelationalExpression `in` ShiftExpression
    5620            8 :     //     [+TypeScript] RelationalExpression `as` Type
    5621            8 :     Relational,
    5622            8 : 
    5623            8 :     // ShiftExpression:
    5624            8 :     //     AdditiveExpression
    5625            8 :     //     ShiftExpression `<<` AdditiveExpression
    5626            8 :     //     ShiftExpression `>>` AdditiveExpression
    5627            8 :     //     ShiftExpression `>>>` AdditiveExpression
    5628            8 :     Shift,
    5629            8 : 
    5630            8 :     // AdditiveExpression:
    5631            8 :     //     MultiplicativeExpression
    5632            8 :     //     AdditiveExpression `+` MultiplicativeExpression
    5633            8 :     //     AdditiveExpression `-` MultiplicativeExpression
    5634            8 :     Additive,
    5635            8 : 
    5636            8 :     // MultiplicativeExpression:
    5637            8 :     //     ExponentiationExpression
    5638            8 :     //     MultiplicativeExpression MultiplicativeOperator ExponentiationExpression
    5639            8 :     // MultiplicativeOperator: one of `*`, `/`, `%`
    5640            8 :     Multiplicative,
    5641            8 : 
    5642            8 :     // ExponentiationExpression:
    5643            8 :     //     UnaryExpression
    5644            8 :     //     UpdateExpression `**` ExponentiationExpression
    5645            8 :     Exponentiation,
    5646            8 : 
    5647            8 :     // UnaryExpression:
    5648            8 :     //     UpdateExpression
    5649            8 :     //     `delete` UnaryExpression
    5650            8 :     //     `void` UnaryExpression
    5651            8 :     //     `typeof` UnaryExpression
    5652            8 :     //     `+` UnaryExpression
    5653            8 :     //     `-` UnaryExpression
    5654            8 :     //     `~` UnaryExpression
    5655            8 :     //     `!` UnaryExpression
    5656            8 :     //     AwaitExpression
    5657            8 :     // UpdateExpression:            // TODO: Do we need to investigate the precedence here?
    5658            8 :     //     `++` UnaryExpression
    5659            8 :     //     `--` UnaryExpression
    5660            8 :     Unary,
    5661            8 : 
    5662            8 :     // UpdateExpression:
    5663            8 :     //     LeftHandSideExpression
    5664            8 :     //     LeftHandSideExpression `++`
    5665            8 :     //     LeftHandSideExpression `--`
    5666            8 :     Update,
    5667            8 : 
    5668            8 :     // LeftHandSideExpression:
    5669            8 :     //     NewExpression
    5670            8 :     //     CallExpression
    5671            8 :     // NewExpression:
    5672            8 :     //     MemberExpression
    5673            8 :     //     `new` NewExpression
    5674            8 :     LeftHandSide,
    5675            8 : 
    5676            8 :     // CallExpression:
    5677            8 :     //     CoverCallExpressionAndAsyncArrowHead
    5678            8 :     //     SuperCall
    5679            8 :     //     ImportCall
    5680            8 :     //     CallExpression Arguments
    5681            8 :     //     CallExpression `[` Expression `]`
    5682            8 :     //     CallExpression `.` IdentifierName
    5683            8 :     //     CallExpression TemplateLiteral
    5684            8 :     // MemberExpression:
    5685            8 :     //     PrimaryExpression
    5686            8 :     //     MemberExpression `[` Expression `]`
    5687            8 :     //     MemberExpression `.` IdentifierName
    5688            8 :     //     MemberExpression TemplateLiteral
    5689            8 :     //     SuperProperty
    5690            8 :     //     MetaProperty
    5691            8 :     //     `new` MemberExpression Arguments
    5692            8 :     Member,
    5693            8 : 
    5694            8 :     // TODO: JSXElement?
    5695            8 :     // PrimaryExpression:
    5696            8 :     //     `this`
    5697            8 :     //     IdentifierReference
    5698            8 :     //     Literal
    5699            8 :     //     ArrayLiteral
    5700            8 :     //     ObjectLiteral
    5701            8 :     //     FunctionExpression
    5702            8 :     //     ClassExpression
    5703            8 :     //     GeneratorExpression
    5704            8 :     //     AsyncFunctionExpression
    5705            8 :     //     AsyncGeneratorExpression
    5706            8 :     //     RegularExpressionLiteral
    5707            8 :     //     TemplateLiteral
    5708            8 :     //     CoverParenthesizedExpressionAndArrowParameterList
    5709            8 :     Primary,
    5710            8 : 
    5711            8 :     Highest = Primary,
    5712            8 :     Lowest = Comma,
    5713            8 :     // -1 is lower than all other precedences. Returning it will cause binary expression
    5714            8 :     // parsing to stop.
    5715            8 :     Invalid = -1,
    5716            8 : }
    5717            8 : 
    5718            8 : /** @internal */
    5719            8 : export function getOperatorPrecedence(nodeKind: SyntaxKind, operatorKind: SyntaxKind, hasArguments?: boolean) {
    5720            8 :     switch (nodeKind) {
    5721            8 :         case SyntaxKind.CommaListExpression:
    5722            8 :             return OperatorPrecedence.Comma;
    5723            8 : 
    5724            8 :         case SyntaxKind.SpreadElement:
    5725            8 :             return OperatorPrecedence.Spread;
    5726            8 : 
    5727            8 :         case SyntaxKind.YieldExpression:
    5728            8 :             return OperatorPrecedence.Yield;
    5729            8 : 
    5730            8 :         case SyntaxKind.ConditionalExpression:
    5731            8 :             return OperatorPrecedence.Conditional;
    5732            8 : 
    5733            8 :         case SyntaxKind.BinaryExpression:
    5734            8 :             switch (operatorKind) {
    5735            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.CommaToken:
    5736            8 :                     return OperatorPrecedence.Comma;
    5737            8 : 
    5738            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.EqualsToken:
    5739            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.PlusEqualsToken:
    5740            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.MinusEqualsToken:
    5741            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.AsteriskAsteriskEqualsToken:
    5742            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.AsteriskEqualsToken:
    5743            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.SlashEqualsToken:
    5744            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.PercentEqualsToken:
    5745            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.LessThanLessThanEqualsToken:
    5746            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.GreaterThanGreaterThanEqualsToken:
    5747            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.GreaterThanGreaterThanGreaterThanEqualsToken:
    5748            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.AmpersandEqualsToken:
    5749            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.CaretEqualsToken:
    5750            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.BarEqualsToken:
    5751            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.BarBarEqualsToken:
    5752            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.AmpersandAmpersandEqualsToken:
    5753            8 :                 case SyntaxKind.QuestionQuestionEqualsToken:
    5754            8 :                     return OperatorPrecedence.Assignment;
    5755            8 : 
    5756            8 :                 default:
    5757            8 :                     return getBinaryOperatorPrecedence(operatorKind);
    5758            8 :             }
    5759            8 : 
    5760            8 :         // TODO: Should prefix `++` and `--` be moved to the `Update` precedence?
    5761            8 :         case SyntaxKind.TypeAssertionExpression:
    5762            8 :         case SyntaxKind.NonNullExpression:
    5763            8 :         case SyntaxKind.PrefixUnaryExpression:
    5764            8 :         case SyntaxKind.TypeOfExpression:
    5765            8 :         case SyntaxKind.VoidExpression:
    5766            8 :         case SyntaxKind.DeleteExpression:
    5767            8 :         case SyntaxKind.AwaitExpression:
    5768            8 :             return OperatorPrecedence.Unary;
    5769            8 : 
    5770            8 :         case SyntaxKind.PostfixUnaryExpression:
    5771            8 :             return OperatorPrecedence.Update;
    5772            8 : 
    5773            8 :         case SyntaxKind.CallExpression:
    5774            8 :             return OperatorPrecedence.LeftHandSide;
    5775            8 : 
    5776            8 :         case SyntaxKind.NewExpression:
    5777            8 :             return hasArguments ? OperatorPrecedence.Member : OperatorPrecedence.LeftHandSide;
    5778            8 : 
    5779            8 :         case SyntaxKind.TaggedTemplateExpression:
    5780            8 :         case SyntaxKind.PropertyAccessExpression:
    5781            8 :         case SyntaxKind.ElementAccessExpression:
    5782            8 :         case SyntaxKind.MetaProperty:
    5783            8 :             return OperatorPrecedence.Member;
    5784            8 : 
    5785            8 :         case SyntaxKind.AsExpression:
    5786            8 :         case SyntaxKind.SatisfiesExpression:
    5787            8 :             return OperatorPrecedence.Relational;
    5788            8 : 
    5789            8 :         case SyntaxKind.ThisKeyword:
    5790            8 :         case SyntaxKind.SuperKeyword:
    5791            8 :         case SyntaxKind.Identifier:
    5792            8 :         case SyntaxKind.PrivateIdentifier:
    5793            8 :         case SyntaxKind.NullKeyword:
    5794            8 :         case SyntaxKind.TrueKeyword:
    5795            8 :         case SyntaxKind.FalseKeyword:
    5796            8 :         case SyntaxKind.NumericLiteral:
    5797            8 :         case SyntaxKind.BigIntLiteral:
    5798            8 :         case SyntaxKind.StringLiteral:
    5799            8 :         case SyntaxKind.ArrayLiteralExpression:
    5800            8 :         case SyntaxKind.ObjectLiteralExpression:
    5801            8 :         case SyntaxKind.FunctionExpression:
    5802            8 :         case SyntaxKind.ArrowFunction:
    5803            8 :         case SyntaxKind.ClassExpression:
    5804            8 :         case SyntaxKind.RegularExpressionLiteral:
    5805            8 :         case SyntaxKind.NoSubstitutionTemplateLiteral:
    5806            8 :         case SyntaxKind.TemplateExpression:
    5807            8 :         case SyntaxKind.ParenthesizedExpression:
    5808            8 :         case SyntaxKind.OmittedExpression:
    5809            8 :         case SyntaxKind.JsxElement:
    5810            8 :         case SyntaxKind.JsxSelfClosingElement:
    5811            8 :         case SyntaxKind.JsxFragment:
    5812            8 :             return OperatorPrecedence.Primary;
    5813            8 : 
    5814            8 :         default:
    5815            8 :             return OperatorPrecedence.Invalid;
    5816            8 :     }
    5817            8 : }
    5818            8 : 
    5819            8 : /** @internal */
    5820            8 : export function getBinaryOperatorPrecedence(kind: SyntaxKind): OperatorPrecedence {
    5821            8 :     switch (kind) {
    5822            8 :         case SyntaxKind.QuestionQuestionToken:
    5823            8 :             return OperatorPrecedence.Coalesce;
    5824            8 :         case SyntaxKind.BarBarToken:
    5825            8 :             return OperatorPrecedence.LogicalOR;
    5826            8 :         case SyntaxKind.AmpersandAmpersandToken:
    5827            8 :             return OperatorPrecedence.LogicalAND;
    5828            8 :         case SyntaxKind.BarToken:
    5829            8 :             return OperatorPrecedence.BitwiseOR;
    5830            8 :         case SyntaxKind.CaretToken:
    5831            8 :             return OperatorPrecedence.BitwiseXOR;
    5832            8 :         case SyntaxKind.AmpersandToken:
    5833            8 :             return OperatorPrecedence.BitwiseAND;
    5834            8 :         case SyntaxKind.EqualsEqualsToken:
    5835            8 :         case SyntaxKind.ExclamationEqualsToken:
    5836            8 :         case SyntaxKind.EqualsEqualsEqualsToken:
    5837            8 :         case SyntaxKind.ExclamationEqualsEqualsToken:
    5838            8 :             return OperatorPrecedence.Equality;
    5839            8 :         case SyntaxKind.LessThanToken:
    5840            8 :         case SyntaxKind.GreaterThanToken:
    5841            8 :         case SyntaxKind.LessThanEqualsToken:
    5842            8 :         case SyntaxKind.GreaterThanEqualsToken:
    5843            8 :         case SyntaxKind.InstanceOfKeyword:
    5844            8 :         case SyntaxKind.InKeyword:
    5845            8 :         case SyntaxKind.AsKeyword:
    5846            8 :         case SyntaxKind.SatisfiesKeyword:
    5847            8 :             return OperatorPrecedence.Relational;
    5848            8 :         case SyntaxKind.LessThanLessThanToken:
    5849            8 :         case SyntaxKind.GreaterThanGreaterThanToken:
    5850            8 :         case SyntaxKind.GreaterThanGreaterThanGreaterThanToken:
    5851            8 :             return OperatorPrecedence.Shift;
    5852            8 :         case SyntaxKind.PlusToken:
    5853            8 :         case SyntaxKind.MinusToken:
    5854            8 :             return OperatorPrecedence.Additive;
    5855            8 :         case SyntaxKind.AsteriskToken:
    5856            8 :         case SyntaxKind.SlashToken:
    5857            8 :         case SyntaxKind.PercentToken:
    5858            8 :             return OperatorPrecedence.Multiplicative;
    5859            8 :         case SyntaxKind.AsteriskAsteriskToken:
    5860            8 :             return OperatorPrecedence.Exponentiation;
    5861            8 :     }
    5862            8 : 
    5863            8 :     // -1 is lower than all other precedences.  Returning it will cause binary expression
    5864            8 :     // parsing to stop.
    5865            8 :     return -1;
    5866            8 : }

    5896            8 :     function lookup(diagnostic: Diagnostic): Diagnostic | undefined {
    5897            8 :         let diagnostics: SortedArray<Diagnostic> | undefined;
    5898            8 :         if (diagnostic.file) {
    5899            8 :             diagnostics = fileDiagnostics.get(diagnostic.file.fileName);
    5900            8 :         }

    5902            8 :             diagnostics = nonFileDiagnostics;

    5912            8 :             return diagnostics[~result - 1];

    5978            8 : // This consists of the first 19 unprintable ASCII characters, canonical escapes, lineSeparator,
    5979            8 : // paragraphSeparator, and nextLine. The latter three are just desirable to suppress new lines in
    5980            8 : // the language service. These characters should be escaped when printing, and if any characters are added,
    5981            8 : // the map below must be updated. Note that this regexp *does not* include the 'delete' character.
    5982            8 : // There is no reason for this other than that JSON.stringify does not handle it either.
    5983            8 : const doubleQuoteEscapedCharsRegExp = /[\\"\u0000-\u001f\t\v\f\b\r\n\u2028\u2029\u0085]/g;

    5985            8 : // Template strings preserve simple LF newlines, still encode CRLF (or CR)
    5986            8 : const backtickQuoteEscapedCharsRegExp = /\r\n|[\\`\u0000-\u001f\t\v\f\b\r\u2028\u2029\u0085]/g;
    5987            8 : const escapedCharsMap = new Map(Object.entries({
    5988            8 :     "\t": "\\t",

    5990            8 :     "\f": "\\f",
    5991            8 :     "\b": "\\b",

    6004            8 : function encodeUtf16EscapeSequence(charCode: number): string {
    6005            8 :     const hexCharCode = charCode.toString(16).toUpperCase();
    6006            8 :     const paddedHexCode = ("0000" + hexCharCode).slice(-4);
    6007            8 :     return "\\u" + paddedHexCode;
    6008            8 : }

    6010            8 : function getReplacement(c: string, offset: number, input: string) {
    6011            8 :     if (c.charCodeAt(0) === CharacterCodes.nullCharacter) {
    6012            8 :         const lookAhead = input.charCodeAt(offset + c.length);
    6013            8 :         if (lookAhead >= CharacterCodes._0 && lookAhead <= CharacterCodes._9) {
    6014            8 :             // If the null character is followed by digits, print as a hex escape to prevent the result from parsing as an octal (which is forbidden in strict mode)
    6015            8 :             return "\\x00";
    6016            8 :         }
    6017            8 :         // Otherwise, keep printing a literal \0 for the null character
    6018            8 :         return "\\0";
    6019            8 :     }
    6020            8 :     return escapedCharsMap.get(c) || encodeUtf16EscapeSequence(c.charCodeAt(0));
    6021            8 : }

    6023            8 : /**
    6024            8 :  * Based heavily on the abstract 'Quote'/'QuoteJSONString' operation from ECMA-262 (24.3.2.2),
    6025            8 :  * but augmented for a few select characters (e.g. lineSeparator, paragraphSeparator, nextLine)

    6031            8 :     const escapedCharsRegExp = quoteChar === CharacterCodes.backtick ? backtickQuoteEscapedCharsRegExp :
    6032            8 :         quoteChar === CharacterCodes.singleQuote ? singleQuoteEscapedCharsRegExp :
    6033            8 :         doubleQuoteEscapedCharsRegExp;
    6034            8 :     return s.replace(escapedCharsRegExp, getReplacement);
    6035            8 : }

    6040            8 :     s = escapeString(s, quoteChar);

    6121            8 : /** @internal */
    6122            8 : export function createTextWriter(newLine: string): EmitTextWriter {
    6123            8 :     // Why var? It avoids TDZ checks in the runtime which can be costly.
    6124            8 :     // See: https://github.com/microsoft/TypeScript/issues/52924
    6125            8 :     /* eslint-disable no-var */
    6126            8 :     var output: string;
    6127            8 :     var indent: number;
    6128            8 :     var lineStart: boolean;
    6129            8 :     var lineCount: number;
    6130            8 :     var linePos: number;
    6131            8 :     var hasTrailingComment = false;
    6132            8 :     /* eslint-enable no-var */
    6133            8 : 
    6134            8 :     function updateLineCountAndPosFor(s: string) {
    6135            8 :         const lineStartsOfS = computeLineStarts(s);
    6136            8 :         if (lineStartsOfS.length > 1) {
    6137            8 :             lineCount = lineCount + lineStartsOfS.length - 1;
    6138            8 :             linePos = output.length - s.length + last(lineStartsOfS);
    6139            8 :             lineStart = (linePos - output.length) === 0;
    6140            8 :         }
    6141            8 :         else {
    6142            8 :             lineStart = false;
    6143            8 :         }
    6144            8 :     }
    6145            8 : 
    6146            8 :     function writeText(s: string) {
    6147            8 :         if (s && s.length) {
    6148            8 :             if (lineStart) {
    6149            8 :                 s = getIndentString(indent) + s;
    6150            8 :                 lineStart = false;
    6151            8 :             }
    6152            8 :             output += s;
    6153            8 :             updateLineCountAndPosFor(s);
    6154            8 :         }
    6155            8 :     }
    6156            8 : 
    6157            8 :     function write(s: string) {
    6158            8 :         if (s) hasTrailingComment = false;
    6159            8 :         writeText(s);
    6160            8 :     }
    6161            8 : 
    6162            8 :     function writeComment(s: string) {
    6163            8 :         if (s) hasTrailingComment = true;
    6164            8 :         writeText(s);
    6165            8 :     }
    6166            8 : 
    6167            8 :     function reset(): void {
    6168            8 :         output = "";
    6169            8 :         indent = 0;
    6170            8 :         lineStart = true;
    6171            8 :         lineCount = 0;
    6172            8 :         linePos = 0;
    6173            8 :         hasTrailingComment = false;
    6174            8 :     }
    6175            8 : 
    6176            8 :     function rawWrite(s: string) {
    6177            8 :         if (s !== undefined) {
    6178            8 :             output += s;
    6179            8 :             updateLineCountAndPosFor(s);
    6180            8 :             hasTrailingComment = false;
    6181            8 :         }
    6182            8 :     }
    6183            8 : 
    6184            8 :     function writeLiteral(s: string) {
    6185            8 :         if (s && s.length) {
    6186            8 :             write(s);
    6187            8 :         }
    6188            8 :     }
    6189            8 : 
    6190            8 :     function writeLine(force?: boolean) {
    6191            8 :         if (!lineStart || force) {
    6192            8 :             output += newLine;
    6193            8 :             lineCount++;
    6194            8 :             linePos = output.length;
    6195            8 :             lineStart = true;
    6196            8 :             hasTrailingComment = false;
    6197            8 :         }
    6198            8 :     }
    6199            8 : 
    6200            8 :     reset();
    6201            8 : 
    6202            8 :     return {
    6203            8 :         write,
    6204            8 :         rawWrite,
    6205            8 :         writeLiteral,
    6206            8 :         writeLine,
    6207            8 :         increaseIndent: () => {
    6208            8 :             indent++;
    6209            8 :         },
    6210            8 :         decreaseIndent: () => {
    6211            8 :             indent--;
    6212            8 :         },
    6213            8 :         getIndent: () => indent,
    6214            8 :         getTextPos: () => output.length,
    6215            8 :         getLine: () => lineCount,
    6216            8 :         getColumn: () => lineStart ? indent * getIndentSize() : output.length - linePos,
    6217            8 :         getText: () => output,
    6218            8 :         isAtStartOfLine: () => lineStart,
    6219            8 :         hasTrailingComment: () => hasTrailingComment,
    6220            8 :         hasTrailingWhitespace: () => !!output.length && isWhiteSpaceLike(output.charCodeAt(output.length - 1)),
    6221            8 :         clear: reset,
    6222            8 :         writeKeyword: write,
    6223            8 :         writeOperator: write,
    6224            8 :         writeParameter: write,
    6225            8 :         writeProperty: write,
    6226            8 :         writePunctuation: write,
    6227            8 :         writeSpace: write,
    6228            8 :         writeStringLiteral: write,
    6229            8 :         writeSymbol: (s, _) => write(s),
    6230            8 :         writeTrailingSemicolon: write,
    6231            8 :         writeComment,
    6232            8 :     };
    6233            8 : }

    6432            8 : /**
    6433            8 :  * Gets the source files that are expected to have an emit output.
    6434            8 :  *
    6435            8 :  * Originally part of `forEachExpectedEmitFile`, this functionality was extracted to support
    6436            8 :  * transformations.
    6437            8 :  *
    6438            8 :  * @param host An EmitHost.
    6439            8 :  * @param targetSourceFile An optional target source file to emit.
    6440            8 :  *
    6441            8 :  * @internal
    6442            8 :  */
    6443            8 : export function getSourceFilesToEmit(host: EmitHost, targetSourceFile?: SourceFile, forceDtsEmit?: boolean): readonly SourceFile[] {
    6444            8 :     const options = host.getCompilerOptions();
    6445            8 :     if (options.outFile) {
    6446            8 :         const moduleKind = getEmitModuleKind(options);
    6447            8 :         const moduleEmitEnabled = options.emitDeclarationOnly || moduleKind === ModuleKind.AMD || moduleKind === ModuleKind.System;
    6448            8 :         // Can emit only sources that are not declaration file and are either non module code or module with --module or --target es6 specified
    6449            8 :         return filter(
    6450            8 :             host.getSourceFiles(),
    6451            8 :             sourceFile =>
    6452            8 :                 (moduleEmitEnabled || !isExternalModule(sourceFile)) &&
    6453            8 :                 sourceFileMayBeEmitted(sourceFile, host, forceDtsEmit),
    6454            8 :         );
    6455            8 :     }
    6456            8 :     else {
    6457            8 :         const sourceFiles = targetSourceFile === undefined ? host.getSourceFiles() : [targetSourceFile];
    6458            8 :         return filter(
    6459            8 :             sourceFiles,
    6460            8 :             sourceFile => sourceFileMayBeEmitted(sourceFile, host, forceDtsEmit),
    6461            8 :         );
    6462            8 :     }
    6463            8 : }
    6464            8 : 
    6465            8 : /**
    6466            8 :  * Don't call this for `--outFile`, just for `--outDir` or plain emit. `--outFile` needs additional checks.
    6467            8 :  *
    6468            8 :  * @internal
    6469            8 :  */
    6470            8 : export function sourceFileMayBeEmitted(sourceFile: SourceFile, host: SourceFileMayBeEmittedHost, forceDtsEmit?: boolean) {
    6471            8 :     const options = host.getCompilerOptions();
    6472            8 :     // Js files are emitted only if option is enabled
    6473            8 :     if (options.noEmitForJsFiles && isSourceFileJS(sourceFile)) return false;
    6474            8 :     // Declaration files are not emitted
    6475            8 :     if (sourceFile.isDeclarationFile) return false;
    6476            8 :     // Source file from node_modules are not emitted
    6477            8 :     if (host.isSourceFileFromExternalLibrary(sourceFile)) return false;
    6478            8 :     // forcing dts emit => file needs to be emitted
    6479            8 :     if (forceDtsEmit) return true;
    6480            8 :     // Check other conditions for file emit
    6481            8 :     // Source files from referenced projects are not emitted
    6482            8 :     if (host.isSourceOfProjectReferenceRedirect(sourceFile.fileName)) return false;
    6483            8 :     // Any non json file should be emitted
    6484            8 :     if (!isJsonSourceFile(sourceFile)) return true;
    6485            8 :     if (host.getResolvedProjectReferenceToRedirect(sourceFile.fileName)) return false;
    6486            8 :     // Emit json file if outFile is specified
    6487            8 :     if (options.outFile) return true;
    6488            8 :     // Json file is not emitted if outDir is not specified
    6489            8 :     if (!options.outDir) return false;
    6490            8 :     // Otherwise if rootDir or composite config file, we know common sourceDir and can check if file would be emitted in same location
    6491            8 :     if (options.rootDir || (options.composite && options.configFilePath)) {
    6492            8 :         const commonDir = getNormalizedAbsolutePath(getCommonSourceDirectory(options, () => [], host.getCurrentDirectory(), host.getCanonicalFileName), host.getCurrentDirectory());
    6493            8 :         const outputPath = getSourceFilePathInNewDirWorker(sourceFile.fileName, options.outDir, host.getCurrentDirectory(), commonDir, host.getCanonicalFileName);
    6494            8 :         if (comparePaths(sourceFile.fileName, outputPath, host.getCurrentDirectory(), !host.useCaseSensitiveFileNames()) === Comparison.EqualTo) return false;
    6495            8 :     }
    6496            8 :     return true;
    6497            8 : }

    6613            8 : /** @internal */
    6614            8 : export function isInTypeQuery(node: Node): boolean {
    6615            8 :     // TypeScript 1.0 spec (April 2014): 3.6.3
    6616            8 :     // A type query consists of the keyword typeof followed by an expression.
    6617            8 :     // The expression is restricted to a single identifier or a sequence of identifiers separated by periods
    6618            8 :     return !!findAncestor(
    6619            8 :         node,
    6620            8 :         n => n.kind === SyntaxKind.TypeQuery ? true : n.kind === SyntaxKind.Identifier || n.kind === SyntaxKind.QualifiedName ? false : "quit",
    6621            8 :     );
    6622            8 : }
    6623            8 : 
    6624            8 : /** @internal */
    6625            8 : export function isThisInTypeQuery(node: Node): boolean {
    6626            8 :     if (!isThisIdentifier(node)) {
    6627            8 :         return false;
    6628            8 :     }
    6629            8 : 
    6630            8 :     while (isQualifiedName(node.parent) && node.parent.left === node) {
    6631            8 :         node = node.parent;
    6632            8 :     }
    6633            8 : 
    6634            8 :     return node.parent.kind === SyntaxKind.TypeQuery;
    6635            8 : }

    6642            8 : /** @internal */
    6643            8 : export function getAllAccessorDeclarations(declarations: readonly Declaration[] | undefined, accessor: AccessorDeclaration): AllAccessorDeclarations {
    6644            8 :     // TODO: GH#18217
    6645            8 :     let firstAccessor!: AccessorDeclaration;
    6646            8 :     let secondAccessor!: AccessorDeclaration;
    6647            8 :     let getAccessor!: GetAccessorDeclaration;
    6648            8 :     let setAccessor!: SetAccessorDeclaration;
    6649            8 :     if (hasDynamicName(accessor)) {
    6650            8 :         firstAccessor = accessor;
    6651            8 :         if (accessor.kind === SyntaxKind.GetAccessor) {
    6652            8 :             getAccessor = accessor;
    6653            8 :         }
    6654            8 :         else if (accessor.kind === SyntaxKind.SetAccessor) {
    6655            8 :             setAccessor = accessor;
    6656            8 :         }
    6657            8 :         else {
    6658            8 :             Debug.fail("Accessor has wrong kind");
    6659            8 :         }
    6660            8 :     }
    6661            8 :     else {
    6662            8 :         forEach(declarations, member => {
    6663            8 :             if (
    6664            8 :                 isAccessor(member)
    6665            8 :                 && isStatic(member) === isStatic(accessor)
    6666            8 :             ) {
    6667            8 :                 const memberName = getPropertyNameForPropertyNameNode(member.name);
    6668            8 :                 const accessorName = getPropertyNameForPropertyNameNode(accessor.name);
    6669            8 :                 if (memberName === accessorName) {
    6670            8 :                     if (!firstAccessor) {
    6671            8 :                         firstAccessor = member;
    6672            8 :                     }
    6673            8 :                     else if (!secondAccessor) {
    6674            8 :                         secondAccessor = member;
    6675            8 :                     }
    6676            8 : 
    6677            8 :                     if (member.kind === SyntaxKind.GetAccessor && !getAccessor) {
    6678            8 :                         getAccessor = member;
    6679            8 :                     }
    6680            8 : 
    6681            8 :                     if (member.kind === SyntaxKind.SetAccessor && !setAccessor) {
    6682            8 :                         setAccessor = member;
    6683            8 :                     }
    6684            8 :                 }
    6685            8 :             }
    6686            8 :         });
    6687            8 :     }
    6688            8 :     return {
    6689            8 :         firstAccessor,
    6690            8 :         secondAccessor,
    6691            8 :         getAccessor,
    6692            8 :         setAccessor,
    6693            8 :     };
    6694            8 : }

    6696            8 : /**
    6697            8 :  * Gets the effective type annotation of a variable, parameter, or property. If the node was

    6699            8 :  * functions only the JSDoc case.

    6703            8 : export function getEffectiveTypeAnnotationNode(node: Node): TypeNode | undefined {
    6704            8 :     if (!isInJSFile(node) && isFunctionDeclaration(node)) return undefined;

    6834            8 :         // removeComments is false, just get detached as normal and bypass the process to filter comment

    6851            8 :                     break;
    6852            8 :                 }

    6855            8 :             detachedComments.push(comment);
    6856            8 :             lastComment = comment;
    6857            8 :         }
