    6881            8 : /** @internal */
    6882            8 : export function writeCommentRange(text: string, lineMap: readonly number[], writer: EmitTextWriter, commentPos: number, commentEnd: number, newLine: string) {
    6883            8 :     if (text.charCodeAt(commentPos + 1) === CharacterCodes.asterisk) {
    6884            8 :         const firstCommentLineAndCharacter = computeLineAndCharacterOfPosition(lineMap, commentPos);
    6885            8 :         const lineCount = lineMap.length;
    6886            8 :         let firstCommentLineIndent: number | undefined;
    6887            8 :         for (let pos = commentPos, currentLine = firstCommentLineAndCharacter.line; pos < commentEnd; currentLine++) {
    6888            8 :             const nextLineStart = (currentLine + 1) === lineCount
    6889            8 :                 ? text.length + 1
    6890            8 :                 : lineMap[currentLine + 1];
    6891            8 : 
    6892            8 :             if (pos !== commentPos) {
    6893            8 :                 // If we are not emitting first line, we need to write the spaces to adjust the alignment
    6894            8 :                 if (firstCommentLineIndent === undefined) {
    6895            8 :                     firstCommentLineIndent = calculateIndent(text, lineMap[firstCommentLineAndCharacter.line], commentPos);
    6896            8 :                 }
    6897            8 : 
    6898            8 :                 // These are number of spaces writer is going to write at current indent
    6899            8 :                 const currentWriterIndentSpacing = writer.getIndent() * getIndentSize();
    6900            8 : 
    6901            8 :                 // Number of spaces we want to be writing
    6902            8 :                 // eg: Assume writer indent
    6903            8 :                 // module m {
    6904            8 :                 //         /* starts at character 9 this is line 1
    6905            8 :                 //    * starts at character pos 4 line                        --1  = 8 - 8 + 3
    6906            8 :                 //   More left indented comment */                            --2  = 8 - 8 + 2
    6907            8 :                 //     class c { }
    6908            8 :                 // }
    6909            8 :                 // module m {
    6910            8 :                 //     /* this is line 1 -- Assume current writer indent 8
    6911            8 :                 //      * line                                                --3 = 8 - 4 + 5
    6912            8 :                 //            More right indented comment */                  --4 = 8 - 4 + 11
    6913            8 :                 //     class c { }
    6914            8 :                 // }
    6915            8 :                 const spacesToEmit = currentWriterIndentSpacing - firstCommentLineIndent + calculateIndent(text, pos, nextLineStart);
    6916            8 :                 if (spacesToEmit > 0) {
    6917            8 :                     let numberOfSingleSpacesToEmit = spacesToEmit % getIndentSize();
    6918            8 :                     const indentSizeSpaceString = getIndentString((spacesToEmit - numberOfSingleSpacesToEmit) / getIndentSize());
    6919            8 : 
    6920            8 :                     // Write indent size string ( in eg 1: = "", 2: "" , 3: string with 8 spaces 4: string with 12 spaces
    6921            8 :                     writer.rawWrite(indentSizeSpaceString);
    6922            8 : 
    6923            8 :                     // Emit the single spaces (in eg: 1: 3 spaces, 2: 2 spaces, 3: 1 space, 4: 3 spaces)
    6924            8 :                     while (numberOfSingleSpacesToEmit) {
    6925            8 :                         writer.rawWrite(" ");
    6926            8 :                         numberOfSingleSpacesToEmit--;
    6927            8 :                     }
    6928            8 :                 }
    6929            8 :                 else {
    6930            8 :                     // No spaces to emit write empty string
    6931            8 :                     writer.rawWrite("");
    6932            8 :                 }
    6933            8 :             }
    6934            8 : 
    6935            8 :             // Write the comment line text
    6936            8 :             writeTrimmedCurrentLine(text, commentEnd, writer, newLine, pos, nextLineStart);
    6937            8 : 
    6938            8 :             pos = nextLineStart;
    6939            8 :         }
    6940            8 :     }
    6941            8 :     else {
    6942            8 :         // Single line comment of style //....
    6943            8 :         writer.writeComment(text.substring(commentPos, commentEnd));
    6944            8 :     }

    6947            8 : function writeTrimmedCurrentLine(text: string, commentEnd: number, writer: EmitTextWriter, newLine: string, pos: number, nextLineStart: number) {
    6948            8 :     const end = Math.min(commentEnd, nextLineStart - 1);
    6949            8 :     const currentLineText = text.substring(pos, end).trim();

    6951            8 :         // trimmed forward and ending spaces text
    6952            8 :         writer.writeComment(currentLineText);
    6953            8 :         if (end !== commentEnd) {
    6954            8 :             writer.writeLine();
    6955            8 :         }
    6956            8 :     }
    6957            8 :     else {
    6958            8 :         // Empty string - make sure we write empty line
    6959            8 :         writer.rawWrite(newLine);
    6960            8 :     }

    6963            8 : function calculateIndent(text: string, pos: number, end: number) {
    6964            8 :     let currentLineIndent = 0;
    6965            8 :     for (; pos < end && isWhiteSpaceSingleLine(text.charCodeAt(pos)); pos++) {
    6966            8 :         if (text.charCodeAt(pos) === CharacterCodes.tab) {
    6967            8 :             // Tabs = TabSize = indent size and go to next tabStop
    6968            8 :             currentLineIndent += getIndentSize() - (currentLineIndent % getIndentSize());
    6969            8 :         }
    6970            8 :         else {
    6971            8 :             // Single space
    6972            8 :             currentLineIndent++;
    6973            8 :         }
    6974            8 :     }
    6975            8 :

    7431            8 : /**
    7432            8 :  * Replace each instance of non-ascii characters by one, two, three, or four escape sequences
    7433            8 :  * representing the UTF-8 encoding of the character, and return the expanded char code list.
    7434            8 :  */
    7435            8 : function getExpandedCharCodes(input: string): number[] {
    7436            8 :     const output: number[] = [];
    7437            8 :     const length = input.length;
    7438            8 : 
    7439            8 :     for (let i = 0; i < length; i++) {
    7440            8 :         const charCode = input.charCodeAt(i);
    7441            8 : 
    7442            8 :         // handle utf8
    7443            8 :         if (charCode < 0x80) {
    7444            8 :             output.push(charCode);
    7445            8 :         }
    7446            8 :         else if (charCode < 0x800) {
    7447            8 :             output.push((charCode >> 6) | 0B11000000);
    7448            8 :             output.push((charCode & 0B00111111) | 0B10000000);
    7449            8 :         }
    7450            8 :         else if (charCode < 0x10000) {
    7451            8 :             output.push((charCode >> 12) | 0B11100000);
    7452            8 :             output.push(((charCode >> 6) & 0B00111111) | 0B10000000);
    7453            8 :             output.push((charCode & 0B00111111) | 0B10000000);
    7454            8 :         }
    7455            8 :         else if (charCode < 0x20000) {
    7456            8 :             output.push((charCode >> 18) | 0B11110000);
    7457            8 :             output.push(((charCode >> 12) & 0B00111111) | 0B10000000);
    7458            8 :             output.push(((charCode >> 6) & 0B00111111) | 0B10000000);
    7459            8 :             output.push((charCode & 0B00111111) | 0B10000000);
    7460            8 :         }
    7461            8 :         else {
    7462            8 :             Debug.assert(false, "Unexpected code point");
    7463            8 :         }
    7464            8 :     }
    7465            8 : 
    7466            8 :     return output;
    7467            8 : }
    7468            8 : 
    7469            8 : const base64Digits = "ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZabcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz0123456789+/=";
    7470            8 : 
    7471            8 : /**
    7472            8 :  * Converts a string to a base-64 encoded ASCII string.
    7473            8 :  *
    7474            8 :  * @internal
    7475            8 :  */
    7476            8 : export function convertToBase64(input: string): string {
    7477            8 :     let result = "";
    7478            8 :     const charCodes = getExpandedCharCodes(input);
    7479            8 :     let i = 0;
    7480            8 :     const length = charCodes.length;
    7481            8 :     let byte1: number, byte2: number, byte3: number, byte4: number;
    7482            8 : 
    7483            8 :     while (i < length) {
    7484            8 :         // Convert every 6-bits in the input 3 character points
    7485            8 :         // into a base64 digit
    7486            8 :         byte1 = charCodes[i] >> 2;
    7487            8 :         byte2 = (charCodes[i] & 0B00000011) << 4 | charCodes[i + 1] >> 4;
    7488            8 :         byte3 = (charCodes[i + 1] & 0B00001111) << 2 | charCodes[i + 2] >> 6;
    7489            8 :         byte4 = charCodes[i + 2] & 0B00111111;
    7490            8 : 
    7491            8 :         // We are out of characters in the input, set the extra
    7492            8 :         // digits to 64 (padding character).
    7493            8 :         if (i + 1 >= length) {
    7494            8 :             byte3 = byte4 = 64;
    7495            8 :         }
    7496            8 :         else if (i + 2 >= length) {
    7497            8 :             byte4 = 64;
    7498            8 :         }
    7499            8 : 
    7500            8 :         // Write to the output
    7501            8 :         result += base64Digits.charAt(byte1) + base64Digits.charAt(byte2) + base64Digits.charAt(byte3) + base64Digits.charAt(byte4);
    7502            8 : 
    7503            8 :         i += 3;
    7504            8 :     }
    7505            8 : 
    7506            8 :     return result;
    7507            8 : }
    7508            8 : 
    7509            8 : function getStringFromExpandedCharCodes(codes: number[]): string {
    7510            8 :     let output = "";
    7511            8 :     let i = 0;
    7512            8 :     const length = codes.length;
    7513            8 :     while (i < length) {
    7514            8 :         const charCode = codes[i];
    7515            8 : 
    7516            8 :         if (charCode < 0x80) {
    7517            8 :             output += String.fromCharCode(charCode);
    7518            8 :             i++;
    7519            8 :         }
    7520            8 :         else if ((charCode & 0B11000000) === 0B11000000) {
    7521            8 :             let value = charCode & 0B00111111;
    7522            8 :             i++;
    7523            8 :             let nextCode: number = codes[i];
    7524            8 :             while ((nextCode & 0B11000000) === 0B10000000) {
    7525            8 :                 value = (value << 6) | (nextCode & 0B00111111);
    7526            8 :                 i++;
    7527            8 :                 nextCode = codes[i];
    7528            8 :             }
    7529            8 :             // `value` may be greater than 10FFFF (the maximum unicode codepoint) - JS will just make this into an invalid character for us
    7530            8 :             output += String.fromCharCode(value);
    7531            8 :         }
    7532            8 :         else {
    7533            8 :             // We don't want to kill the process when decoding fails (due to a following char byte not
    7534            8 :             // following a leading char), so we just print the (bad) value
    7535            8 :             output += String.fromCharCode(charCode);
    7536            8 :             i++;
    7537            8 :         }
    7538            8 :     }
    7539            8 :     return output;
    7540            8 : }
    7541            8 : 
    7542            8 : /** @internal */
    7543            8 : export function base64encode(host: { base64encode?(input: string): string; } | undefined, input: string): string {
    7544            8 :     if (host && host.base64encode) {
    7545            8 :         return host.base64encode(input);
    7546            8 :     }
    7547            8 :     return convertToBase64(input);
    7548            8 : }
    7549            8 : 
    7550            8 : export const branch_coverage = new Map<string, boolean>();
    7551            8 : /** @internal */
    7552            8 : export function base64decode(host: { base64decode?(input: string): string; } | undefined, input: string): string {
    7553            8 :     if (host && host.base64decode) {
    7554            8 :         branch_coverage.set('base64_1', true);
    7555            8 :         return host.base64decode(input);
    7556            8 :     }
    7557            8 :     branch_coverage.set('base64_2', true);
    7558            8 :     const length = input.length;
    7559            8 :     const expandedCharCodes: number[] = [];
    7560            8 :     let i = 0;
    7561            8 :     while (i < length) {
    7562            8 :         // Stop decoding once padding characters are present
    7563            8 :         if (input.charCodeAt(i) === base64Digits.charCodeAt(64)) {
    7564            8 :             break;
    7565            8 :         }
    7566            8 :         // convert 4 input digits into three characters, ignoring padding characters at the end
    7567            8 :         const ch1 = base64Digits.indexOf(input[i]);
    7568            8 :         const ch2 = base64Digits.indexOf(input[i + 1]);
    7569            8 :         const ch3 = base64Digits.indexOf(input[i + 2]);
    7570            8 :         const ch4 = base64Digits.indexOf(input[i + 3]);
    7571            8 : 
    7572            8 :         const code1 = ((ch1 & 0B00111111) << 2) | ((ch2 >> 4) & 0B00000011);
    7573            8 :         const code2 = ((ch2 & 0B00001111) << 4) | ((ch3 >> 2) & 0B00001111);
    7574            8 :         const code3 = ((ch3 & 0B00000011) << 6) | (ch4 & 0B00111111);
    7575            8 : 
    7576            8 :         if (code2 === 0 && ch3 !== 0) { // code2 decoded to zero, but ch3 was padding - elide code2 and code3
    7577            8 :             expandedCharCodes.push(code1);
    7578            8 :         }
    7579            8 :         else if (code3 === 0 && ch4 !== 0) { // code3 decoded to zero, but ch4 was padding, elide code3
    7580            8 :             expandedCharCodes.push(code1, code2);
    7581            8 :         }
    7582            8 :         else {
    7583            8 :             expandedCharCodes.push(code1, code2, code3);
    7584            8 :         }
    7585            8 :         i += 4;
    7586            8 :     }
    7587            8 :     return getStringFromExpandedCharCodes(expandedCharCodes);
    7588            8 : }

    7841            8 : /** @internal */
    7842            8 : export function getDeclarationModifierFlagsFromSymbol(s: Symbol, isWrite = false): ModifierFlags {
    7843            8 :     if (s.valueDeclaration) {
    7844            8 :         const declaration = (isWrite && s.declarations && find(s.declarations, isSetAccessorDeclaration))
    7845            8 :             || (s.flags & SymbolFlags.GetAccessor && find(s.declarations, isGetAccessorDeclaration)) || s.valueDeclaration;

    7883            8 : /** @internal */
    7884            8 : export function isWriteAccess(node: Node) {
    7885            8 :     return accessKind(node) !== AccessKind.Read;
    7886            8 : }
    7887            8 : 
    7888            8 : const enum AccessKind {
    7889            8 :     /** Only reads from a variable. */
    7890            8 :     Read,
    7891            8 :     /** Only writes to a variable without ever reading it. E.g.: `x=1;`. */
    7892            8 :     Write,
    7893            8 :     /** Reads from and writes to a variable. E.g.: `f(x++);`, `x/=1`. */
    7894            8 :     ReadWrite,
    7895            8 : }
    7896            8 : function accessKind(node: Node): AccessKind {
    7897            8 :     const { parent } = node;
    7898            8 : 
    7899            8 :     switch (parent?.kind) {
    7900            8 :         case SyntaxKind.ParenthesizedExpression:
    7901            8 :             return accessKind(parent);
    7902            8 :         case SyntaxKind.PostfixUnaryExpression:
    7903            8 :         case SyntaxKind.PrefixUnaryExpression:
    7904            8 :             const { operator } = parent as PrefixUnaryExpression | PostfixUnaryExpression;
    7905            8 :             return operator === SyntaxKind.PlusPlusToken || operator === SyntaxKind.MinusMinusToken ? AccessKind.ReadWrite : AccessKind.Read;
    7906            8 :         case SyntaxKind.BinaryExpression:
    7907            8 :             const { left, operatorToken } = parent as BinaryExpression;
    7908            8 :             return left === node && isAssignmentOperator(operatorToken.kind) ?
    7909            8 :                 operatorToken.kind === SyntaxKind.EqualsToken ? AccessKind.Write : AccessKind.ReadWrite
    7910            8 :                 : AccessKind.Read;
    7911            8 :         case SyntaxKind.PropertyAccessExpression:
    7912            8 :             return (parent as PropertyAccessExpression).name !== node ? AccessKind.Read : accessKind(parent);
    7913            8 :         case SyntaxKind.PropertyAssignment: {
    7914            8 :             const parentAccess = accessKind(parent.parent);
    7915            8 :             // In `({ x: varname }) = { x: 1 }`, the left `x` is a read, the right `x` is a write.
    7916            8 :             return node === (parent as PropertyAssignment).name ? reverseAccessKind(parentAccess) : parentAccess;
    7917            8 :         }
    7918            8 :         case SyntaxKind.ShorthandPropertyAssignment:
    7919            8 :             // Assume it's the local variable being accessed, since we don't check public properties for --noUnusedLocals.
    7920            8 :             return node === (parent as ShorthandPropertyAssignment).objectAssignmentInitializer ? AccessKind.Read : accessKind(parent.parent);
    7921            8 :         case SyntaxKind.ArrayLiteralExpression:
    7922            8 :             return accessKind(parent);
    7923            8 :         default:
    7924            8 :             return AccessKind.Read;
    7925            8 :     }
    7926            8 : }
    7927            8 : function reverseAccessKind(a: AccessKind): AccessKind {
    7928            8 :     switch (a) {
    7929            8 :         case AccessKind.Read:
    7930            8 :             return AccessKind.Write;
    7931            8 :         case AccessKind.Write:
    7932            8 :             return AccessKind.Read;
    7933            8 :         case AccessKind.ReadWrite:
    7934            8 :             return AccessKind.ReadWrite;
    7935            8 :         default:
    7936            8 :             return Debug.assertNever(a);
    7937            8 :     }
    7938            8 : }
    7939            8 : 
    7940            8 : /** @internal */
    7941            8 : export function compareDataObjects(dst: any, src: any): boolean {
    7942            8 :     if (!dst || !src || Object.keys(dst).length !== Object.keys(src).length) {
    7943            8 :         return false;
    7944            8 :     }
    7945            8 : 
    7946            8 :     for (const e in dst) {
    7947            8 :         if (typeof dst[e] === "object") {
    7948            8 :             if (!compareDataObjects(dst[e], src[e])) {
    7949            8 :                 return false;
    7950            8 :             }
    7951            8 :         }
    7952            8 :         else if (typeof dst[e] !== "function") {
    7953            8 :             if (dst[e] !== src[e]) {
    7954            8 :                 return false;
    7955            8 :             }
    7956            8 :         }
    7957            8 :     }
    7958            8 :     return true;
    7959            8 : }

    7980            8 :      * If present this is called with the key when there is value for that key both in new map as well as existing map provided

    8004            8 : export function mutateMapSkippingNewValues<K, T, U>(
    8005            8 :     map: Map<K, T>,
    8006            8 :     newMap: ReadonlyMap<K, U> | ReadonlySet<K> | undefined,
    8007            8 :     options: MutateMapSkippingNewValuesOptions<K, T, U>,
    8008            8 : ) {
    8009            8 :     const { onDeleteValue, onExistingValue } = options;
    8010            8 :     // Needs update
    8011            8 :     map.forEach((existingValue, key) => {
    8012            8 :         // Not present any more in new map, remove it
    8013            8 :         if (!newMap?.has(key)) {
    8014            8 :             map.delete(key);
    8015            8 :             onDeleteValue(existingValue, key);
    8016            8 :         }
    8017            8 :         // If present notify about existing values
    8018            8 :         else if (onExistingValue) {
    8019            8 :             onExistingValue(existingValue, (newMap as Map<K, U>).get?.(key)!, key);
    8020            8 :         }
    8021            8 :     });
    8022            8 : }

    8094            8 : export function getLastChild(node: Node): Node | undefined {
    8095            8 :     let lastChild: Node | undefined;
    8096            8 :     forEachChild(node, child => {
    8097            8 :         if (nodeIsPresent(child)) lastChild = child;
    8098            8 :     }, children => {
    8099            8 :         // As an optimization, jump straight to the end of the list.
    8100            8 :         for (let i = children.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
    8101            8 :             if (nodeIsPresent(children[i])) {
    8102            8 :                 lastChild = children[i];
    8103            8 :                 break;
    8104            8 :             }
    8105            8 :         }
    8106            8 :     });
    8107            8 :     return lastChild;
    8108            8 : }

    8184            8 : /** @internal */
    8185            8 : export function forEachNameInAccessChainWalkingLeft<T>(name: MemberName | StringLiteralLike, action: (name: MemberName | StringLiteralLike) => T | undefined): T | undefined {
    8186            8 :     if (isAccessExpression(name.parent) && isRightSideOfAccessExpression(name)) {
    8187            8 :         return walkAccessExpression(name.parent);
    8188            8 :     }
    8189            8 : 
    8190            8 :     function walkAccessExpression(access: AccessExpression): T | undefined {
    8191            8 :         if (access.kind === SyntaxKind.PropertyAccessExpression) {
    8192            8 :             const res = action(access.name);
    8193            8 :             if (res !== undefined) {
    8194            8 :                 return res;
    8195            8 :             }
    8196            8 :         }
    8197            8 :         else if (access.kind === SyntaxKind.ElementAccessExpression) {
    8198            8 :             if (isIdentifier(access.argumentExpression) || isStringLiteralLike(access.argumentExpression)) {
    8199            8 :                 const res = action(access.argumentExpression);
    8200            8 :                 if (res !== undefined) {
    8201            8 :                     return res;
    8202            8 :                 }
    8203            8 :             }
    8204            8 :             else {
    8205            8 :                 // Chain interrupted by non-static-name access 'x[expr()].y.z'
    8206            8 :                 return undefined;
    8207            8 :             }
    8208            8 :         }
    8209            8 : 
    8210            8 :         if (isAccessExpression(access.expression)) {
    8211            8 :             return walkAccessExpression(access.expression);
    8212            8 :         }
    8213            8 :         if (isIdentifier(access.expression)) {
    8214            8 :             // End of chain at Identifier 'x.y.z'
    8215            8 :             return action(access.expression);
    8216            8 :         }
    8217            8 :         // End of chain at non-Identifier 'x().y.z'
    8218            8 :         return undefined;
    8219            8 :     }
    8220            8 : }
    8221            8 : 
    8222            8 : /** @internal */
    8223            8 : export function getLeftmostExpression(node: Expression, stopAtCallExpressions: boolean) {
    8224            8 :     while (true) {
    8225            8 :         switch (node.kind) {
    8226            8 :             case SyntaxKind.PostfixUnaryExpression:
    8227            8 :                 node = (node as PostfixUnaryExpression).operand;
    8228            8 :                 continue;
    8229            8 : 
    8230            8 :             case SyntaxKind.BinaryExpression:
    8231            8 :                 node = (node as BinaryExpression).left;
    8232            8 :                 continue;
    8233            8 : 
    8234            8 :             case SyntaxKind.ConditionalExpression:
    8235            8 :                 node = (node as ConditionalExpression).condition;
    8236            8 :                 continue;
    8237            8 : 
    8238            8 :             case SyntaxKind.TaggedTemplateExpression:
    8239            8 :                 node = (node as TaggedTemplateExpression).tag;
    8240            8 :                 continue;
    8241            8 : 
    8242            8 :             case SyntaxKind.CallExpression:
    8243            8 :                 if (stopAtCallExpressions) {
    8244            8 :                     return node;
    8245            8 :                 }
    8246            8 :                 // falls through
    8247            8 :             case SyntaxKind.AsExpression:
    8248            8 :             case SyntaxKind.ElementAccessExpression:
    8249            8 :             case SyntaxKind.PropertyAccessExpression:
    8250            8 :             case SyntaxKind.NonNullExpression:
    8251            8 :             case SyntaxKind.PartiallyEmittedExpression:
    8252            8 :             case SyntaxKind.SatisfiesExpression:
    8253            8 :                 node = (node as CallExpression | PropertyAccessExpression | ElementAccessExpression | AsExpression | NonNullExpression | PartiallyEmittedExpression | SatisfiesExpression).expression;
    8254            8 :                 continue;
    8255            8 :         }
    8256            8 : 
    8257            8 :         return node;
    8258            8 :     }
    8259            8 : }

    8443            8 : function attachFileToDiagnostic(diagnostic: DiagnosticWithDetachedLocation, file: SourceFile): DiagnosticWithLocation {

    8592            8 :     const code2 = getDiagnosticCode(d2);
    8593            8 :     return compareStringsCaseSensitive(getDiagnosticFilePath(d1), getDiagnosticFilePath(d2)) ||
    8594            8 :         compareValues(d1.start, d2.start) ||

    8600            8 : 
    8601            8 : // A diagnostic with more elaboration should be considered *less than* a diagnostic
    8602            8 : // with less elaboration that is otherwise similar.
    8603            8 : function compareRelatedInformation(d1: Diagnostic, d2: Diagnostic): Comparison {
    8604            8 :     if (!d1.relatedInformation && !d2.relatedInformation) {
    8605            8 :         return Comparison.EqualTo;
    8606            8 :     }
    8607            8 :     if (d1.relatedInformation && d2.relatedInformation) {
    8608            8 :         return compareValues(d2.relatedInformation.length, d1.relatedInformation.length) || forEach(d1.relatedInformation, (d1i, index) => {
    8609            8 :             const d2i = d2.relatedInformation![index];
    8610            8 :             return compareDiagnostics(d1i, d2i); // EqualTo is 0, so falsy, and will cause the next item to be compared
    8611            8 :         }) || Comparison.EqualTo;
    8612            8 :     }
    8613            8 :     return d1.relatedInformation ? Comparison.LessThan : Comparison.GreaterThan;
    8614            8 : }
    8615            8 : 
    8616            8 : // An diagnostic message with more elaboration should be considered *less than* a diagnostic message
    8617            8 : // with less elaboration that is otherwise similar.
    8618            8 : function compareMessageText(
    8619            8 :     d1: Diagnostic,
    8620            8 :     d2: Diagnostic,
    8621            8 : ): Comparison {
    8622            8 :     let headMsg1 = getDiagnosticMessage(d1);
    8623            8 :     let headMsg2 = getDiagnosticMessage(d2);
    8624            8 :     if (typeof headMsg1 !== "string") {
    8625            8 :         headMsg1 = headMsg1.messageText;
    8626            8 :     }
    8627            8 :     if (typeof headMsg2 !== "string") {
    8628            8 :         headMsg2 = headMsg2.messageText;
    8629            8 :     }
    8630            8 :     const chain1 = typeof d1.messageText !== "string" ? d1.messageText.next : undefined;
    8631            8 :     const chain2 = typeof d2.messageText !== "string" ? d2.messageText.next : undefined;
    8632            8 : 
    8633            8 :     let res = compareStringsCaseSensitive(headMsg1, headMsg2);
    8634            8 :     if (res) {
    8635            8 :         return res;
    8636            8 :     }
    8637            8 : 
    8638            8 :     res = compareMessageChain(chain1, chain2);
    8639            8 :     if (res) {
    8640            8 :         return res;
    8641            8 :     }
    8642            8 : 
    8643            8 :     if (d1.canonicalHead && !d2.canonicalHead) {
    8644            8 :         return Comparison.LessThan;
    8645            8 :     }
    8646            8 :     if (d2.canonicalHead && !d1.canonicalHead) {
    8647            8 :         return Comparison.GreaterThan;
    8648            8 :     }
    8649            8 : 
    8650            8 :     return Comparison.EqualTo;
    8651            8 : }
    8652            8 : 
    8653            8 : // First compare by size of the message chain,
    8654            8 : // then compare by content of the message chain.
    8655            8 : function compareMessageChain(
    8656            8 :     c1: DiagnosticMessageChain[] | undefined,
    8657            8 :     c2: DiagnosticMessageChain[] | undefined,
    8658            8 : ): Comparison {
    8659            8 :     if (c1 === undefined && c2 === undefined) {
    8660            8 :         return Comparison.EqualTo;
    8661            8 :     }
    8662            8 :     if (c1 === undefined) {
    8663            8 :         return Comparison.GreaterThan;
    8664            8 :     }
    8665            8 :     if (c2 === undefined) {
    8666            8 :         return Comparison.LessThan;
    8667            8 :     }
    8668            8 : 
    8669            8 :     return compareMessageChainSize(c1, c2) || compareMessageChainContent(c1, c2);
    8670            8 : }
    8671            8 : 
    8672            8 : function compareMessageChainSize(
    8673            8 :     c1: DiagnosticMessageChain[] | undefined,
    8674            8 :     c2: DiagnosticMessageChain[] | undefined,
    8675            8 : ): Comparison {
    8676            8 :     if (c1 === undefined && c2 === undefined) {
    8677            8 :         return Comparison.EqualTo;
    8678            8 :     }
    8679            8 :     if (c1 === undefined) {
    8680            8 :         return Comparison.GreaterThan;
    8681            8 :     }
    8682            8 :     if (c2 === undefined) {
    8683            8 :         return Comparison.LessThan;
    8684            8 :     }
    8685            8 : 
    8686            8 :     let res = compareValues(c2.length, c1.length);
    8687            8 :     if (res) {
    8688            8 :         return res;
    8689            8 :     }
    8690            8 : 
    8691            8 :     for (let i = 0; i < c2.length; i++) {
    8692            8 :         res = compareMessageChainSize(c1[i].next, c2[i].next);
    8693            8 :         if (res) {
    8694            8 :             return res;
    8695            8 :         }
    8696            8 :     }
    8697            8 : 
    8698            8 :     return Comparison.EqualTo;
    8699            8 : }
    8700            8 : 
    8701            8 : // Assumes the two chains have the same shape.
    8702            8 : function compareMessageChainContent(
    8703            8 :     c1: DiagnosticMessageChain[],
    8704            8 :     c2: DiagnosticMessageChain[],
    8705            8 : ): Comparison {
    8706            8 :     let res;
    8707            8 :     for (let i = 0; i < c2.length; i++) {
    8708            8 :         res = compareStringsCaseSensitive(c1[i].messageText, c2[i].messageText);
    8709            8 :         if (res) {
    8710            8 :             return res;
    8711            8 :         }
    8712            8 :         if (c1[i].next === undefined) {
    8713            8 :             continue;
    8714            8 :         }
    8715            8 :         res = compareMessageChainContent(c1[i].next!, c2[i].next!);
    8716            8 :         if (res) {
    8717            8 :             return res;
    8718            8 :         }
    8719            8 :     }
    8720            8 :     return Comparison.EqualTo;
    8721            8 : }
    8722            8 : 
    8723            8 : /** @internal */
    8724            8 : export function diagnosticsEqualityComparer(d1: Diagnostic, d2: Diagnostic): boolean {
    8725            8 :     const code1 = getDiagnosticCode(d1);
    8726            8 :     const code2 = getDiagnosticCode(d2);
    8727            8 :     const msg1 = getDiagnosticMessage(d1);
    8728            8 :     const msg2 = getDiagnosticMessage(d2);
    8729            8 :     return compareStringsCaseSensitive(getDiagnosticFilePath(d1), getDiagnosticFilePath(d2)) === Comparison.EqualTo &&
    8730            8 :         compareValues(d1.start, d2.start) === Comparison.EqualTo &&
    8731            8 :         compareValues(d1.length, d2.length) === Comparison.EqualTo &&
    8732            8 :         compareValues(code1, code2) === Comparison.EqualTo &&
    8733            8 :         messageTextEqualityComparer(msg1, msg2);
    8734            8 : }
    8735            8 : 
    8736            8 : function getDiagnosticCode(d: Diagnostic): number {

    8738            8 : }
    8739            8 : 
    8740            8 : function getDiagnosticMessage(d: Diagnostic): string | DiagnosticMessageChain {

    8744            8 : function messageTextEqualityComparer(m1: string | DiagnosticMessageChain, m2: string | DiagnosticMessageChain): boolean {
    8745            8 :     const t1 = typeof m1 === "string" ? m1 : m1.messageText;
    8746            8 :     const t2 = typeof m2 === "string" ? m2 : m2.messageText;
    8747            8 :     return compareStringsCaseSensitive(t1, t2) === Comparison.EqualTo;
    8748            8 : }

    8751            8 : export function getLanguageVariant(scriptKind: ScriptKind) {
    8752            8 :     // .tsx and .jsx files are treated as jsx language variant.
    8753            8 :     return scriptKind === ScriptKind.TSX || scriptKind === ScriptKind.JSX || scriptKind === ScriptKind.JS || scriptKind === ScriptKind.JSON ? LanguageVariant.JSX : LanguageVariant.Standard;
    8754            8 : }
    8755            8 : 
    8756            8 : /**
    8757            8 :  * This is a somewhat unavoidable full tree walk to locate a JSX tag - `import.meta` requires the same,
    8758            8 :  * but we avoid that walk (or parts of it) if at all possible using the `PossiblyContainsImportMeta` node flag.
    8759            8 :  * Unfortunately, there's no `NodeFlag` space to do the same for JSX.
    8760            8 :  */
    8761            8 : function walkTreeForJSXTags(node: Node): Node | undefined {
    8762            8 :     if (!(node.transformFlags & TransformFlags.ContainsJsx)) return undefined;
    8763            8 :     return isJsxOpeningLikeElement(node) || isJsxFragment(node) ? node : forEachChild(node, walkTreeForJSXTags);
    8764            8 : }

    8766            8 : function isFileModuleFromUsingJSXTag(file: SourceFile): Node | undefined {
    8767            8 :     // Excludes declaration files - they still require an explicit `export {}` or the like
    8768            8 :     // for back compat purposes. (not that declaration files should contain JSX tags!)
    8769            8 :     return !file.isDeclarationFile ? walkTreeForJSXTags(file) : undefined;
    8770            8 : }
    8771            8 : 
    8772            8 : /**
    8773            8 :  * Note that this requires file.impliedNodeFormat be set already; meaning it must be set very early on
    8774            8 :  * in SourceFile construction.
    8775            8 :  */
    8776            8 : function isFileForcedToBeModuleByFormat(file: SourceFile, options: CompilerOptions): true | undefined {
    8777            8 :     // Excludes declaration files - they still require an explicit `export {}` or the like
    8778            8 :     // for back compat purposes. The only non-declaration files _not_ forced to be a module are `.js` files
    8779            8 :     // that aren't esm-mode (meaning not in a `type: module` scope).
    8780            8 :     //
    8781            8 :     // TODO: extension check never considered compilerOptions; should impliedNodeFormat?
    8782            8 :     return (getImpliedNodeFormatForEmitWorker(file, options) === ModuleKind.ESNext || (fileExtensionIsOneOf(file.fileName, [Extension.Cjs, Extension.Cts, Extension.Mjs, Extension.Mts]))) && !file.isDeclarationFile ? true : undefined;
    8783            8 : }

    8785            8 : /** @internal */
    8786            8 : export function getSetExternalModuleIndicator(options: CompilerOptions): (file: SourceFile) => void {
    8787            8 :     // TODO: Should this callback be cached?
    8788            8 :     switch (getEmitModuleDetectionKind(options)) {
    8789            8 :         case ModuleDetectionKind.Force:
    8790            8 :             // All non-declaration files are modules, declaration files still do the usual isFileProbablyExternalModule
    8791            8 :             return (file: SourceFile) => {
    8792            8 :                 file.externalModuleIndicator = isFileProbablyExternalModule(file) || !file.isDeclarationFile || undefined;
    8793            8 :             };
    8794            8 :         case ModuleDetectionKind.Legacy:
    8795            8 :             // Files are modules if they have imports, exports, or import.meta
    8796            8 :             return (file: SourceFile) => {
    8797            8 :                 file.externalModuleIndicator = isFileProbablyExternalModule(file);
    8798            8 :             };
    8799            8 :         case ModuleDetectionKind.Auto:
    8800            8 :             // If module is nodenext or node16, all esm format files are modules
    8801            8 :             // If jsx is react-jsx or react-jsxdev then jsx tags force module-ness
    8802            8 :             // otherwise, the presence of import or export statments (or import.meta) implies module-ness
    8803            8 :             const checks: ((file: SourceFile, options: CompilerOptions) => Node | true | undefined)[] = [isFileProbablyExternalModule];
    8804            8 :             if (options.jsx === JsxEmit.ReactJSX || options.jsx === JsxEmit.ReactJSXDev) {
    8805            8 :                 checks.push(isFileModuleFromUsingJSXTag);
    8806            8 :             }
    8807            8 :             checks.push(isFileForcedToBeModuleByFormat);
    8808            8 :             const combined = or(...checks);
    8809            8 :             const callback = (file: SourceFile) => void (file.externalModuleIndicator = combined(file, options));
    8810            8 :             return callback;
    8811            8 :     }
    8812            8 : }

    9239            8 :      * Uses resolvedTypeReferenceDirectives from program instead of from files, since files

    9241            8 :      * `hasProcessedResolutions` returns false (once per cache instance).
    9242            8 :      */
    9243            8 :     setSymlinksFromResolutions(
    9244            8 :         forEachResolvedModule: (

    9246            8 :         ) => void,

    9249            8 :         ) => void,
    9250            8 :         typeReferenceDirectives: ModeAwareCache<ResolvedTypeReferenceDirectiveWithFailedLookupLocations>,
    9251            8 :     ): void;
    9252            8 :     setSymlinksFromResolution(resolution: ResolvedModuleFull | undefined): void;
    9253            8 :     /**
    9254            8 :      * @internal
    9255            8 :      * Whether `setSymlinksFromResolutions` has already been called.
    9256            8 :      */
    9257            8 :     hasProcessedResolutions(): boolean;
    9258            8 : }
    9259            8 : 
    9260            8 : /** @internal */
    9261            8 : export function createSymlinkCache(cwd: string, getCanonicalFileName: GetCanonicalFileName): SymlinkCache {
    9262            8 :     let symlinkedDirectories: Map<Path, SymlinkedDirectory | false> | undefined;
    9263            8 :     let symlinkedDirectoriesByRealpath: MultiMap<Path, string> | undefined;
    9264            8 :     let symlinkedFiles: Map<Path, string> | undefined;
    9265            8 :     let hasProcessedResolutions = false;
    9266            8 :     return {
    9267            8 :         getSymlinkedFiles: () => symlinkedFiles,
    9268            8 :         getSymlinkedDirectories: () => symlinkedDirectories,
    9269            8 :         getSymlinkedDirectoriesByRealpath: () => symlinkedDirectoriesByRealpath,
    9270            8 :         setSymlinkedFile: (path, real) => (symlinkedFiles || (symlinkedFiles = new Map())).set(path, real),
    9271            8 :         setSymlinkedDirectory: (symlink, real) => {
    9272            8 :             // Large, interconnected dependency graphs in pnpm will have a huge number of symlinks
    9273            8 :             // where both the realpath and the symlink path are inside node_modules/.pnpm. Since
    9274            8 :             // this path is never a candidate for a module specifier, we can ignore it entirely.
    9275            8 :             let symlinkPath = toPath(symlink, cwd, getCanonicalFileName);
    9276            8 :             if (!containsIgnoredPath(symlinkPath)) {
    9277            8 :                 symlinkPath = ensureTrailingDirectorySeparator(symlinkPath);
    9278            8 :                 if (real !== false && !symlinkedDirectories?.has(symlinkPath)) {
    9279            8 :                     (symlinkedDirectoriesByRealpath ||= createMultiMap()).add(real.realPath, symlink);
    9280            8 :                 }
    9281            8 :                 (symlinkedDirectories || (symlinkedDirectories = new Map())).set(symlinkPath, real);
    9282            8 :             }
    9283            8 :         },
    9284            8 :         setSymlinksFromResolutions(forEachResolvedModule, forEachResolvedTypeReferenceDirective, typeReferenceDirectives) {
    9285            8 :             Debug.assert(!hasProcessedResolutions);
    9286            8 :             hasProcessedResolutions = true;
    9287            8 :             forEachResolvedModule(resolution => processResolution(this, resolution.resolvedModule));
    9288            8 :             forEachResolvedTypeReferenceDirective(resolution => processResolution(this, resolution.resolvedTypeReferenceDirective));
    9289            8 :             typeReferenceDirectives.forEach(resolution => processResolution(this, resolution.resolvedTypeReferenceDirective));
    9290            8 :         },
    9291            8 :         hasProcessedResolutions: () => hasProcessedResolutions,
    9292            8 :         setSymlinksFromResolution(resolution) {
    9293            8 :             processResolution(this, resolution);
    9294            8 :         },
    9295            8 :         hasAnySymlinks,
    9296            8 :     };
    9297            8 : 
    9298            8 :     function hasAnySymlinks() {
    9299            8 :         return !!symlinkedFiles?.size || (!!symlinkedDirectories && !!forEachEntry(symlinkedDirectories, value => !!value));
    9300            8 :     }
    9301            8 : 
    9302            8 :     function processResolution(cache: SymlinkCache, resolution: ResolvedModuleFull | ResolvedTypeReferenceDirective | undefined) {
    9303            8 :         if (!resolution || !resolution.originalPath || !resolution.resolvedFileName) return;
    9304            8 :         const { resolvedFileName, originalPath } = resolution;
    9305            8 :         cache.setSymlinkedFile(toPath(originalPath, cwd, getCanonicalFileName), resolvedFileName);
    9306            8 :         const [commonResolved, commonOriginal] = guessDirectorySymlink(resolvedFileName, originalPath, cwd, getCanonicalFileName) || emptyArray;
    9307            8 :         if (commonResolved && commonOriginal) {
    9308            8 :             cache.setSymlinkedDirectory(
    9309            8 :                 commonOriginal,
    9310            8 :                 {
    9311            8 :                     real: ensureTrailingDirectorySeparator(commonResolved),
    9312            8 :                     realPath: ensureTrailingDirectorySeparator(toPath(commonResolved, cwd, getCanonicalFileName)),
    9313            8 :                 },
    9314            8 :             );
    9315            8 :         }
    9316            8 :     }
    9317            8 : }
    9318            8 : 
    9319            8 : function guessDirectorySymlink(a: string, b: string, cwd: string, getCanonicalFileName: GetCanonicalFileName): [string, string] | undefined {
    9320            8 :     const aParts = getPathComponents(getNormalizedAbsolutePath(a, cwd));
    9321            8 :     const bParts = getPathComponents(getNormalizedAbsolutePath(b, cwd));
    9322            8 :     let isDirectory = false;
    9323            8 :     while (
    9324            8 :         aParts.length >= 2 && bParts.length >= 2 &&
    9325            8 :         !isNodeModulesOrScopedPackageDirectory(aParts[aParts.length - 2], getCanonicalFileName) &&
    9326            8 :         !isNodeModulesOrScopedPackageDirectory(bParts[bParts.length - 2], getCanonicalFileName) &&
    9327            8 :         getCanonicalFileName(aParts[aParts.length - 1]) === getCanonicalFileName(bParts[bParts.length - 1])
    9328            8 :     ) {
    9329            8 :         aParts.pop();
    9330            8 :         bParts.pop();
    9331            8 :         isDirectory = true;
    9332            8 :     }
    9333            8 :     return isDirectory ? [getPathFromPathComponents(aParts), getPathFromPathComponents(bParts)] : undefined;
    9334            8 : }
    9335            8 : 
    9336            8 : // KLUDGE: Don't assume one 'node_modules' links to another. More likely a single directory inside the node_modules is the symlink.
    9337            8 : // ALso, don't assume that an `@foo` directory is linked. More likely the contents of that are linked.
    9338            8 : function isNodeModulesOrScopedPackageDirectory(s: string | undefined, getCanonicalFileName: GetCanonicalFileName): boolean {
    9339            8 :     return s !== undefined && (getCanonicalFileName(s) === "node_modules" || startsWith(s, "@"));
    9340            8 : }

    9351            8 : 
    9352            8 : // Reserved characters, forces escaping of any non-word (or digit), non-whitespace character.
    9353            8 : // It may be inefficient (we could just match (/[-[\]{}()*+?.,\\^$|#\s]/g), but this is future
    9354            8 : // proof.
    9355            8 : const reservedCharacterPattern = /[^\w\s/]/g;
    9356            8 : 
    9357            8 : /** @internal */
    9358            8 : export function regExpEscape(text: string) {

    9360            8 : }
    9361            8 : 
    9362            8 : function escapeRegExpCharacter(match: string) {
    9363            8 :     return "\\" + match;
    9364            8 : }
    9365            8 : 
    9366            8 : const wildcardCharCodes = [CharacterCodes.asterisk, CharacterCodes.question];
    9367            8 : 
    9368            8 : /** @internal */
    9369            8 : export const commonPackageFolders: readonly string[] = ["node_modules", "bower_components", "jspm_packages"];
    9370            8 : 
    9371            8 : const implicitExcludePathRegexPattern = `(?!(${commonPackageFolders.join("|")})(/|$))`;
    9372            8 : 
    9373            8 : /** @internal */
    9374            8 : export interface WildcardMatcher {
    9375            8 :     singleAsteriskRegexFragment: string;
    9376            8 :     doubleAsteriskRegexFragment: string;
    9377            8 :     replaceWildcardCharacter: (match: string) => string;
    9378            8 : }
    9379            8 : 
    9380            8 : const filesMatcher: WildcardMatcher = {
    9381            8 :     /**
    9382            8 :      * Matches any single directory segment unless it is the last segment and a .min.js file
    9383            8 :      * Breakdown:
    9384            8 :      *  [^./]                   # matches everything up to the first . character (excluding directory separators)
    9385            8 :      *  (\\.(?!min\\.js$))?     # matches . characters but not if they are part of the .min.js file extension
    9386            8 :      */
    9387            8 :     singleAsteriskRegexFragment: "([^./]|(\\.(?!min\\.js$))?)*",
    9388            8 :     /**
    9389            8 :      * Regex for the ** wildcard. Matches any number of subdirectories. When used for including
    9390            8 :      * files or directories, does not match subdirectories that start with a . character
    9391            8 :      */
    9392            8 :     doubleAsteriskRegexFragment: `(/${implicitExcludePathRegexPattern}[^/.][^/]*)*?`,
    9393            8 :     replaceWildcardCharacter: match => replaceWildcardCharacter(match, filesMatcher.singleAsteriskRegexFragment),
    9394            8 : };
    9395            8 : 
    9396            8 : const directoriesMatcher: WildcardMatcher = {
    9397            8 :     singleAsteriskRegexFragment: "[^/]*",
    9398            8 :     /**
    9399            8 :      * Regex for the ** wildcard. Matches any number of subdirectories. When used for including
    9400            8 :      * files or directories, does not match subdirectories that start with a . character
    9401            8 :      */
    9402            8 :     doubleAsteriskRegexFragment: `(/${implicitExcludePathRegexPattern}[^/.][^/]*)*?`,
    9403            8 :     replaceWildcardCharacter: match => replaceWildcardCharacter(match, directoriesMatcher.singleAsteriskRegexFragment),
    9404            8 : };
    9405            8 : 
    9406            8 : const excludeMatcher: WildcardMatcher = {
    9407            8 :     singleAsteriskRegexFragment: "[^/]*",
    9408            8 :     doubleAsteriskRegexFragment: "(/.+?)?",
    9409            8 :     replaceWildcardCharacter: match => replaceWildcardCharacter(match, excludeMatcher.singleAsteriskRegexFragment),
    9410            8 : };
    9411            8 : 
    9412            8 : const wildcardMatchers = {
    9413            8 :     files: filesMatcher,
    9414            8 :     directories: directoriesMatcher,
    9415            8 :     exclude: excludeMatcher,
    9416            8 : };
    9417            8 : 
    9418            8 : /** @internal */
    9419            8 : export function getRegularExpressionForWildcard(specs: readonly string[] | undefined, basePath: string, usage: "files" | "directories" | "exclude"): string | undefined {
    9420            8 :     const patterns = getRegularExpressionsForWildcards(specs, basePath, usage);
    9421            8 :     if (!patterns || !patterns.length) {
    9422            8 :         return undefined;
    9423            8 :     }
    9424            8 : 
    9425            8 :     const pattern = patterns.map(pattern => `(${pattern})`).join("|");
    9426            8 :     // If excluding, match "foo/bar/baz...", but if including, only allow "foo".
    9427            8 :     const terminator = usage === "exclude" ? "($|/)" : "$";
    9428            8 :     return `^(${pattern})${terminator}`;
    9429            8 : }
    9430            8 : 
    9431            8 : /** @internal */
    9432            8 : export function getRegularExpressionsForWildcards(specs: readonly string[] | undefined, basePath: string, usage: "files" | "directories" | "exclude"): readonly string[] | undefined {
    9433            8 :     if (specs === undefined || specs.length === 0) {
    9434            8 :         return undefined;
    9435            8 :     }
    9436            8 : 
    9437            8 :     return flatMap(specs, spec => spec && getSubPatternFromSpec(spec, basePath, usage, wildcardMatchers[usage]));
    9438            8 : }
    9439            8 : 
    9440            8 : /**
    9441            8 :  * An "includes" path "foo" is implicitly a glob "foo/** /*" (without the space) if its last component has no extension,
    9442            8 :  * and does not contain any glob characters itself.
    9443            8 :  *
    9444            8 :  * @internal
    9445            8 :  */
    9446            8 : export function isImplicitGlob(lastPathComponent: string): boolean {
    9447            8 :     return !/[.*?]/.test(lastPathComponent);
    9448            8 : }
    9449            8 : 
    9450            8 : /** @internal */
    9451            8 : export function getPatternFromSpec(spec: string, basePath: string, usage: "files" | "directories" | "exclude") {
    9452            8 :     const pattern = spec && getSubPatternFromSpec(spec, basePath, usage, wildcardMatchers[usage]);
    9453            8 :     return pattern && `^(${pattern})${usage === "exclude" ? "($|/)" : "$"}`;
    9454            8 : }
    9455            8 : 
    9456            8 : /** @internal */
    9457            8 : export function getSubPatternFromSpec(
    9458            8 :     spec: string,
    9459            8 :     basePath: string,
    9460            8 :     usage: "files" | "directories" | "exclude",
    9461            8 :     { singleAsteriskRegexFragment, doubleAsteriskRegexFragment, replaceWildcardCharacter }: WildcardMatcher = wildcardMatchers[usage],
    9462            8 : ): string | undefined {
    9463            8 :     let subpattern = "";
    9464            8 :     let hasWrittenComponent = false;
    9465            8 :     const components = getNormalizedPathComponents(spec, basePath);
    9466            8 :     const lastComponent = last(components);
    9467            8 :     if (usage !== "exclude" && lastComponent === "**") {
    9468            8 :         return undefined;
    9469            8 :     }
    9470            8 : 
    9471            8 :     // getNormalizedPathComponents includes the separator for the root component.
    9472            8 :     // We need to remove to create our regex correctly.
    9473            8 :     components[0] = removeTrailingDirectorySeparator(components[0]);
    9474            8 : 
    9475            8 :     if (isImplicitGlob(lastComponent)) {
    9476            8 :         components.push("**", "*");
    9477            8 :     }
    9478            8 : 
    9479            8 :     let optionalCount = 0;
    9480            8 :     for (let component of components) {
    9481            8 :         if (component === "**") {
    9482            8 :             subpattern += doubleAsteriskRegexFragment;
    9483            8 :         }
    9484            8 :         else {
    9485            8 :             if (usage === "directories") {
    9486            8 :                 subpattern += "(";
    9487            8 :                 optionalCount++;
    9488            8 :             }
    9489            8 : 
    9490            8 :             if (hasWrittenComponent) {
    9491            8 :                 subpattern += directorySeparator;
    9492            8 :             }
    9493            8 : 
    9494            8 :             if (usage !== "exclude") {
    9495            8 :                 let componentPattern = "";
    9496            8 :                 // The * and ? wildcards should not match directories or files that start with . if they
    9497            8 :                 // appear first in a component. Dotted directories and files can be included explicitly
    9498            8 :                 // like so: **/.*/.*
    9499            8 :                 if (component.charCodeAt(0) === CharacterCodes.asterisk) {
    9500            8 :                     componentPattern += "([^./]" + singleAsteriskRegexFragment + ")?";
    9501            8 :                     component = component.substr(1);
    9502            8 :                 }
    9503            8 :                 else if (component.charCodeAt(0) === CharacterCodes.question) {
    9504            8 :                     componentPattern += "[^./]";
    9505            8 :                     component = component.substr(1);
    9506            8 :                 }
    9507            8 : 
    9508            8 :                 componentPattern += component.replace(reservedCharacterPattern, replaceWildcardCharacter);
    9509            8 : 
    9510            8 :                 // Patterns should not include subfolders like node_modules unless they are
    9511            8 :                 // explicitly included as part of the path.
    9512            8 :                 //
    9513            8 :                 // As an optimization, if the component pattern is the same as the component,
    9514            8 :                 // then there definitely were no wildcard characters and we do not need to
    9515            8 :                 // add the exclusion pattern.
    9516            8 :                 if (componentPattern !== component) {
    9517            8 :                     subpattern += implicitExcludePathRegexPattern;
    9518            8 :                 }
    9519            8 : 
    9520            8 :                 subpattern += componentPattern;
    9521            8 :             }
    9522            8 :             else {
    9523            8 :                 subpattern += component.replace(reservedCharacterPattern, replaceWildcardCharacter);
    9524            8 :             }
    9525            8 :         }
    9526            8 : 
    9527            8 :         hasWrittenComponent = true;
    9528            8 :     }
    9529            8 : 
    9530            8 :     while (optionalCount > 0) {
    9531            8 :         subpattern += ")?";
    9532            8 :         optionalCount--;
    9533            8 :     }
    9534            8 : 
    9535            8 :     return subpattern;
    9536            8 : }
    9537            8 : 
    9538            8 : function replaceWildcardCharacter(match: string, singleAsteriskRegexFragment: string) {
    9539            8 :     return match === "*" ? singleAsteriskRegexFragment : match === "?" ? "[^/]" : "\\" + match;
    9540            8 : }

    9580            8 :     return new RegExp(pattern, useCaseSensitiveFileNames ? "" : "i");

    9588            8 : export function matchFiles(path: string, extensions: readonly string[] | undefined, excludes: readonly string[] | undefined, includes: readonly string[] | undefined, useCaseSensitiveFileNames: boolean, currentDirectory: string, depth: number | undefined, getFileSystemEntries: (path: string) => FileSystemEntries, realpath: (path: string) => string): string[] {
    9589            8 :     path = normalizePath(path);
    9590            8 :     currentDirectory = normalizePath(currentDirectory);
    9591            8 : 
    9592            8 :     const patterns = getFileMatcherPatterns(path, excludes, includes, useCaseSensitiveFileNames, currentDirectory);
    9593            8 : 
    9594            8 :     const includeFileRegexes = patterns.includeFilePatterns && patterns.includeFilePatterns.map(pattern => getRegexFromPattern(pattern, useCaseSensitiveFileNames));
    9595            8 :     const includeDirectoryRegex = patterns.includeDirectoryPattern && getRegexFromPattern(patterns.includeDirectoryPattern, useCaseSensitiveFileNames);
    9596            8 :     const excludeRegex = patterns.excludePattern && getRegexFromPattern(patterns.excludePattern, useCaseSensitiveFileNames);
    9597            8 : 
    9598            8 :     // Associate an array of results with each include regex. This keeps results in order of the "include" order.
    9599            8 :     // If there are no "includes", then just put everything in results[0].
    9600            8 :     const results: string[][] = includeFileRegexes ? includeFileRegexes.map(() => []) : [[]];
    9601            8 :     const visited = new Map<string, true>();
    9602            8 :     const toCanonical = createGetCanonicalFileName(useCaseSensitiveFileNames);
    9603            8 :     for (const basePath of patterns.basePaths) {
    9604            8 :         visitDirectory(basePath, combinePaths(currentDirectory, basePath), depth);
    9605            8 :     }
    9606            8 : 
    9607            8 :     return flatten(results);
    9608            8 : 
    9609            8 :     function visitDirectory(path: string, absolutePath: string, depth: number | undefined) {
    9610            8 :         const canonicalPath = toCanonical(realpath(absolutePath));
    9611            8 :         if (visited.has(canonicalPath)) return;
    9612            8 :         visited.set(canonicalPath, true);
    9613            8 :         const { files, directories } = getFileSystemEntries(path);
    9614            8 : 
    9615            8 :         for (const current of sort<string>(files, compareStringsCaseSensitive)) {
    9616            8 :             const name = combinePaths(path, current);
    9617            8 :             const absoluteName = combinePaths(absolutePath, current);
    9618            8 :             if (extensions && !fileExtensionIsOneOf(name, extensions)) continue;
    9619            8 :             if (excludeRegex && excludeRegex.test(absoluteName)) continue;
    9620            8 :             if (!includeFileRegexes) {
    9621            8 :                 results[0].push(name);
    9622            8 :             }
    9623            8 :             else {
    9624            8 :                 const includeIndex = findIndex(includeFileRegexes, re => re.test(absoluteName));
    9625            8 :                 if (includeIndex !== -1) {
    9626            8 :                     results[includeIndex].push(name);
    9627            8 :                 }
    9628            8 :             }
    9629            8 :         }
    9630            8 : 
    9631            8 :         if (depth !== undefined) {
    9632            8 :             depth--;
    9633            8 :             if (depth === 0) {
    9634            8 :                 return;
    9635            8 :             }
    9636            8 :         }
    9637            8 : 
    9638            8 :         for (const current of sort<string>(directories, compareStringsCaseSensitive)) {
    9639            8 :             const name = combinePaths(path, current);
    9640            8 :             const absoluteName = combinePaths(absolutePath, current);
    9641            8 :             if (
    9642            8 :                 (!includeDirectoryRegex || includeDirectoryRegex.test(absoluteName)) &&
    9643            8 :                 (!excludeRegex || !excludeRegex.test(absoluteName))
    9644            8 :             ) {
    9645            8 :                 visitDirectory(name, absoluteName, depth);
    9646            8 :             }
    9647            8 :         }
    9648            8 :     }
    9649            8 : }
    9650            8 : 
    9651            8 : /**
    9652            8 :  * Computes the unique non-wildcard base paths amongst the provided include patterns.
    9653            8 :  */
    9654            8 : function getBasePaths(path: string, includes: readonly string[] | undefined, useCaseSensitiveFileNames: boolean): string[] {
    9655            8 :     // Storage for our results in the form of literal paths (e.g. the paths as written by the user).
    9656            8 :     const basePaths: string[] = [path];
    9657            8 : 
    9658            8 :     if (includes) {
    9659            8 :         // Storage for literal base paths amongst the include patterns.
    9660            8 :         const includeBasePaths: string[] = [];
    9661            8 :         for (const include of includes) {
    9662            8 :             // We also need to check the relative paths by converting them to absolute and normalizing
    9663            8 :             // in case they escape the base path (e.g "..\somedirectory")
    9664            8 :             const absolute: string = isRootedDiskPath(include) ? include : normalizePath(combinePaths(path, include));
    9665            8 :             // Append the literal and canonical candidate base paths.
    9666            8 :             includeBasePaths.push(getIncludeBasePath(absolute));
    9667            8 :         }
    9668            8 : 
    9669            8 :         // Sort the offsets array using either the literal or canonical path representations.
    9670            8 :         includeBasePaths.sort(getStringComparer(!useCaseSensitiveFileNames));
    9671            8 : 
    9672            8 :         // Iterate over each include base path and include unique base paths that are not a
    9673            8 :         // subpath of an existing base path
    9674            8 :         for (const includeBasePath of includeBasePaths) {
    9675            8 :             if (every(basePaths, basePath => !containsPath(basePath, includeBasePath, path, !useCaseSensitiveFileNames))) {
    9676            8 :                 basePaths.push(includeBasePath);
    9677            8 :             }
    9678            8 :         }
    9679            8 :     }
    9680            8 : 
    9681            8 :     return basePaths;
    9682            8 : }
    9683            8 : 
    9684            8 : function getIncludeBasePath(absolute: string): string {
    9685            8 :     const wildcardOffset = indexOfAnyCharCode(absolute, wildcardCharCodes);
    9686            8 :     if (wildcardOffset < 0) {
    9687            8 :         // No "*" or "?" in the path
    9688            8 :         return !hasExtension(absolute)
    9689            8 :             ? absolute
    9690            8 :             : removeTrailingDirectorySeparator(getDirectoryPath(absolute));
    9691            8 :     }
    9692            8 :     return absolute.substring(0, absolute.lastIndexOf(directorySeparator, wildcardOffset));
    9693            8 : }

    9696            8 : export function ensureScriptKind(fileName: string, scriptKind: ScriptKind | undefined): ScriptKind {
    9697            8 :     // Using scriptKind as a condition handles both:
    9698            8 :     // - 'scriptKind' is unspecified and thus it is `undefined`
    9699            8 :     // - 'scriptKind' is set and it is `Unknown` (0)
    9700            8 :     // If the 'scriptKind' is 'undefined' or 'Unknown' then we attempt
    9701            8 :     // to get the ScriptKind from the file name. If it cannot be resolved
    9702            8 :     // from the file name then the default 'TS' script kind is returned.

    9812            8 : /** @internal */
    9813            8 : export function usesExtensionsOnImports({ imports }: SourceFile, hasExtension: (text: string) => boolean = or(hasJSFileExtension, hasTSFileExtension)): boolean {
    9814            8 :     return firstDefined(imports, ({ text }) =>
    9815            8 :         pathIsRelative(text) && !fileExtensionIsOneOf(text, extensionsNotSupportingExtensionlessResolution)
    9816            8 :             ? hasExtension(text)

    9820            8 : /** @internal */
    9821            8 : export function getModuleSpecifierEndingPreference(preference: UserPreferences["importModuleSpecifierEnding"], resolutionMode: ResolutionMode, compilerOptions: CompilerOptions, sourceFile?: SourceFile): ModuleSpecifierEnding {
    9822            8 :     const moduleResolution = getEmitModuleResolutionKind(compilerOptions);
    9823            8 :     const moduleResolutionIsNodeNext = ModuleResolutionKind.Node16 <= moduleResolution && moduleResolution <= ModuleResolutionKind.NodeNext;
    9824            8 :     if (preference === "js" || resolutionMode === ModuleKind.ESNext && moduleResolutionIsNodeNext) {
    9825            8 :         // Extensions are explicitly requested or required. Now choose between .js and .ts.
    9826            8 :         if (!shouldAllowImportingTsExtension(compilerOptions)) {
    9827            8 :             return ModuleSpecifierEnding.JsExtension;
    9828            8 :         }
    9829            8 :         // `allowImportingTsExtensions` is a strong signal, so use .ts unless the file
    9830            8 :         // already uses .js extensions and no .ts extensions.
    9831            8 :         return inferPreference() !== ModuleSpecifierEnding.JsExtension
    9832            8 :             ? ModuleSpecifierEnding.TsExtension
    9833            8 :             : ModuleSpecifierEnding.JsExtension;
    9834            8 :     }
    9835            8 :     if (preference === "minimal") {
    9836            8 :         return ModuleSpecifierEnding.Minimal;
    9837            8 :     }
    9838            8 :     if (preference === "index") {
    9839            8 :         return ModuleSpecifierEnding.Index;
    9840            8 :     }
    9841            8 : 
    9842            8 :     // No preference was specified.
    9843            8 :     // Look at imports and/or requires to guess whether .js, .ts, or extensionless imports are preferred.
    9844            8 :     // N.B. that `Index` detection is not supported since it would require file system probing to do
    9845            8 :     // accurately, and more importantly, literally nobody wants `Index` and its existence is a mystery.
    9846            8 :     if (!shouldAllowImportingTsExtension(compilerOptions)) {
    9847            8 :         // If .ts imports are not valid, we only need to see one .js import to go with that.
    9848            8 :         return sourceFile && usesExtensionsOnImports(sourceFile) ? ModuleSpecifierEnding.JsExtension : ModuleSpecifierEnding.Minimal;
    9849            8 :     }
    9850            8 : 
    9851            8 :     return inferPreference();
    9852            8 : 
    9853            8 :     function inferPreference() {
    9854            8 :         let usesJsExtensions = false;
    9855            8 :         const specifiers = sourceFile?.imports.length ? sourceFile.imports :
    9856            8 :             sourceFile && isSourceFileJS(sourceFile) ? getRequiresAtTopOfFile(sourceFile).map(r => r.arguments[0]) :
    9857            8 :             emptyArray;
    9858            8 :         for (const specifier of specifiers) {
    9859            8 :             if (pathIsRelative(specifier.text)) {
    9860            8 :                 if (
    9861            8 :                     moduleResolutionIsNodeNext &&
    9862            8 :                     resolutionMode === ModuleKind.CommonJS &&
    9863            8 :                     getModeForUsageLocation(sourceFile!, specifier, compilerOptions) === ModuleKind.ESNext
    9864            8 :                 ) {
    9865            8 :                     // We're trying to decide a preference for a CommonJS module specifier, but looking at an ESM import.
    9866            8 :                     continue;
    9867            8 :                 }
    9868            8 :                 if (fileExtensionIsOneOf(specifier.text, extensionsNotSupportingExtensionlessResolution)) {
    9869            8 :                     // These extensions are not optional, so do not indicate a preference.
    9870            8 :                     continue;
    9871            8 :                 }
    9872            8 :                 if (hasTSFileExtension(specifier.text)) {
    9873            8 :                     return ModuleSpecifierEnding.TsExtension;
    9874            8 :                 }
    9875            8 :                 if (hasJSFileExtension(specifier.text)) {
    9876            8 :                     usesJsExtensions = true;
    9877            8 :                 }
    9878            8 :             }
    9879            8 :         }
    9880            8 :         return usesJsExtensions ? ModuleSpecifierEnding.JsExtension : ModuleSpecifierEnding.Minimal;
    9881            8 :     }
    9882            8 : }
    9883            8 : 
    9884            8 : function getRequiresAtTopOfFile(sourceFile: SourceFile): readonly RequireOrImportCall[] {
    9885            8 :     let nonRequireStatementCount = 0;
    9886            8 :     let requires: RequireOrImportCall[] | undefined;
    9887            8 :     for (const statement of sourceFile.statements) {
    9888            8 :         if (nonRequireStatementCount > 3) {
    9889            8 :             break;
    9890            8 :         }
    9891            8 :         if (isRequireVariableStatement(statement)) {
    9892            8 :             requires = concatenate(requires, statement.declarationList.declarations.map(d => d.initializer));
    9893            8 :         }
    9894            8 :         else if (isExpressionStatement(statement) && isRequireCall(statement.expression, /*requireStringLiteralLikeArgument*/ true)) {
    9895            8 :             requires = append(requires, statement.expression);
    9896            8 :         }
    9897            8 :         else {
    9898            8 :             nonRequireStatementCount++;
    9899            8 :         }
    9900            8 :     }
    9901            8 :     return requires || emptyArray;
    9902            8 : }

    9956            8 : 
    9957            8 : /**
    9958            8 :  * Returns the input if there are no stars, a pattern if there is exactly one,
    9959            8 :  * and undefined if there are more.
    9960            8 :  *
