   10151            8 : /**
   10152            8 :  * Converts a bigint literal string, e.g. `0x1234n`,
   10153            8 :  * to its decimal string representation, e.g. `4660`.
   10154            8 :  *
   10155            8 :  * @internal
   10156            8 :  */
   10157            8 : export function parsePseudoBigInt(stringValue: string): string {
   10158            8 :     let log2Base: number;
   10159            8 :     switch (stringValue.charCodeAt(1)) { // "x" in "0x123"
   10160            8 :         case CharacterCodes.b:
   10161            8 :         case CharacterCodes.B: // 0b or 0B
   10162            8 :             log2Base = 1;
   10163            8 :             break;
   10164            8 :         case CharacterCodes.o:
   10165            8 :         case CharacterCodes.O: // 0o or 0O
   10166            8 :             log2Base = 3;
   10167            8 :             break;
   10168            8 :         case CharacterCodes.x:
   10169            8 :         case CharacterCodes.X: // 0x or 0X
   10170            8 :             log2Base = 4;
   10171            8 :             break;
   10172            8 :         default: // already in decimal; omit trailing "n"
   10173            8 :             const nIndex = stringValue.length - 1;
   10174            8 :             // Skip leading 0s
   10175            8 :             let nonZeroStart = 0;
   10176            8 :             while (stringValue.charCodeAt(nonZeroStart) === CharacterCodes._0) {
   10177            8 :                 nonZeroStart++;
   10178            8 :             }
   10179            8 :             return stringValue.slice(nonZeroStart, nIndex) || "0";
   10180            8 :     }
   10181            8 : 
   10182            8 :     // Omit leading "0b", "0o", or "0x", and trailing "n"
   10183            8 :     const startIndex = 2, endIndex = stringValue.length - 1;
   10184            8 :     const bitsNeeded = (endIndex - startIndex) * log2Base;
   10185            8 :     // Stores the value specified by the string as a LE array of 16-bit integers
   10186            8 :     // using Uint16 instead of Uint32 so combining steps can use bitwise operators
   10187            8 :     const segments = new Uint16Array((bitsNeeded >>> 4) + (bitsNeeded & 15 ? 1 : 0));
   10188            8 :     // Add the digits, one at a time
   10189            8 :     for (let i = endIndex - 1, bitOffset = 0; i >= startIndex; i--, bitOffset += log2Base) {
   10190            8 :         const segment = bitOffset >>> 4;
   10191            8 :         const digitChar = stringValue.charCodeAt(i);
   10192            8 :         // Find character range: 0-9 < A-F < a-f
   10193            8 :         const digit = digitChar <= CharacterCodes._9
   10194            8 :             ? digitChar - CharacterCodes._0
   10195            8 :             : 10 + digitChar -
   10196            8 :                 (digitChar <= CharacterCodes.F ? CharacterCodes.A : CharacterCodes.a);
   10197            8 :         const shiftedDigit = digit << (bitOffset & 15);
   10198            8 :         segments[segment] |= shiftedDigit;
   10199            8 :         const residual = shiftedDigit >>> 16;
   10200            8 :         if (residual) segments[segment + 1] |= residual; // overflows segment
   10201            8 :     }
   10202            8 :     // Repeatedly divide segments by 10 and add remainder to base10Value
   10203            8 :     let base10Value = "";
   10204            8 :     let firstNonzeroSegment = segments.length - 1;
   10205            8 :     let segmentsRemaining = true;
   10206            8 :     while (segmentsRemaining) {
   10207            8 :         let mod10 = 0;
   10208            8 :         segmentsRemaining = false;
   10209            8 :         for (let segment = firstNonzeroSegment; segment >= 0; segment--) {
   10210            8 :             const newSegment = mod10 << 16 | segments[segment];
   10211            8 :             const segmentValue = (newSegment / 10) | 0;
   10212            8 :             segments[segment] = segmentValue;
   10213            8 :             mod10 = newSegment - segmentValue * 10;
   10214            8 :             if (segmentValue && !segmentsRemaining) {
   10215            8 :                 firstNonzeroSegment = segment;
   10216            8 :                 segmentsRemaining = true;
   10217            8 :             }
   10218            8 :         }
   10219            8 :         base10Value = mod10 + base10Value;
   10220            8 :     }
   10221            8 :     return base10Value;
   10222            8 : }
   10223            8 : 
   10224            8 : /** @internal */
   10225            8 : export function pseudoBigIntToString({ negative, base10Value }: PseudoBigInt): string {
   10226            8 :     return (negative && base10Value !== "0" ? "-" : "") + base10Value;
   10227            8 : }
   10228            8 : 
   10229            8 : /** @internal */
   10230            8 : export function parseBigInt(text: string): PseudoBigInt | undefined {
   10231            8 :     if (!isValidBigIntString(text, /*roundTripOnly*/ false)) {
   10232            8 :         return undefined;
   10233            8 :     }
   10234            8 :     return parseValidBigInt(text);
   10235            8 : }
   10236            8 : 
   10237            8 : /**
   10238            8 :  * @internal
   10239            8 :  * @param text a valid bigint string excluding a trailing `n`, but including a possible prefix `-`. Use `isValidBigIntString(text, roundTripOnly)` before calling this function.
   10240            8 :  */
   10241            8 : export function parseValidBigInt(text: string): PseudoBigInt {
   10242            8 :     const negative = text.startsWith("-");
   10243            8 :     const base10Value = parsePseudoBigInt(`${negative ? text.slice(1) : text}n`);
   10244            8 :     return { negative, base10Value };
   10245            8 : }
   10246            8 : 
   10247            8 : /**
   10248            8 :  * @internal
   10249            8 :  * Tests whether the provided string can be parsed as a bigint.
   10250            8 :  * @param s The string to test.
   10251            8 :  * @param roundTripOnly Indicates the resulting bigint matches the input when converted back to a string.
   10252            8 :  */
   10253            8 : export function isValidBigIntString(s: string, roundTripOnly: boolean): boolean {
   10254            8 :     if (s === "") return false;
   10255            8 :     const scanner = createScanner(ScriptTarget.ESNext, /*skipTrivia*/ false);
   10256            8 :     let success = true;
   10257            8 :     scanner.setOnError(() => success = false);
   10258            8 :     scanner.setText(s + "n");
   10259            8 :     let result = scanner.scan();
   10260            8 :     const negative = result === SyntaxKind.MinusToken;
   10261            8 :     if (negative) {
   10262            8 :         result = scanner.scan();
   10263            8 :     }
   10264            8 :     const flags = scanner.getTokenFlags();
   10265            8 :     // validate that
   10266            8 :     // * scanning proceeded without error
   10267            8 :     // * a bigint can be scanned, and that when it is scanned, it is
   10268            8 :     // * the full length of the input string (so the scanner is one character beyond the augmented input length)
   10269            8 :     // * it does not contain a numeric seperator (the `BigInt` constructor does not accept a numeric seperator in its input)
   10270            8 :     return success && result === SyntaxKind.BigIntLiteral && scanner.getTokenEnd() === (s.length + 1) && !(flags & TokenFlags.ContainsSeparator)
   10271            8 :         && (!roundTripOnly || s === pseudoBigIntToString({ negative, base10Value: parsePseudoBigInt(scanner.getTokenValue()) }));
   10272            8 : }

   10415            8 :     if (children) {

   10417            8 :             setParent(child, parent);
   10418            8 :         }
   10419            8 :     }
   10420            8 :     return children;
   10421            8 : }
   10422            8 : 
   10423            8 : /**
   10424            8 :  * Bypasses immutability and directly sets the `parent` property of each `Node` recursively.
   10425            8 :  * @param rootNode The root node from which to start the recursion.
   10426            8 :  * @param incremental When `true`, only recursively descends through nodes whose `parent` pointers are incorrect.
   10427            8 :  * This allows us to quickly bail out of setting `parent` for subtrees during incremental parsing.
   10428            8 :  *
   10429            8 :  * @internal
   10430            8 :  */
   10431            8 : export function setParentRecursive<T extends Node>(rootNode: T, incremental: boolean): T;
   10432            8 : /** @internal */
   10433            8 : export function setParentRecursive<T extends Node>(rootNode: T | undefined, incremental: boolean): T | undefined;
   10434            8 : /** @internal */
   10435            8 : export function setParentRecursive<T extends Node>(rootNode: T | undefined, incremental: boolean): T | undefined {
   10436            8 :     if (!rootNode) return rootNode;
   10437            8 :     forEachChildRecursively(rootNode, isJSDocNode(rootNode) ? bindParentToChildIgnoringJSDoc : bindParentToChild);
   10438            8 :     return rootNode;
   10439            8 : 
   10440            8 :     function bindParentToChildIgnoringJSDoc(child: Node, parent: Node): void | "skip" {
   10441            8 :         if (incremental && child.parent === parent) {
   10442            8 :             return "skip";
   10443            8 :         }
   10444            8 :         setParent(child, parent);
   10445            8 :     }
   10446            8 : 
   10447            8 :     function bindJSDoc(child: Node) {
   10448            8 :         if (hasJSDocNodes(child)) {
   10449            8 :             for (const doc of child.jsDoc!) {
   10450            8 :                 bindParentToChildIgnoringJSDoc(doc, child);
   10451            8 :                 forEachChildRecursively(doc, bindParentToChildIgnoringJSDoc);
   10452            8 :             }
   10453            8 :         }
   10454            8 :     }
   10455            8 : 
   10456            8 :     function bindParentToChild(child: Node, parent: Node) {
   10457            8 :         return bindParentToChildIgnoringJSDoc(child, parent) || bindJSDoc(child);
   10458            8 :     }
   10459            8 : }
   10460            8 : 
   10461            8 : function isPackedElement(node: Expression) {
   10462            8 :     return !isOmittedExpression(node);
   10463            8 : }

   10465            8 : /**
   10466            8 :  * Determines whether the provided node is an ArrayLiteralExpression that contains no missing elements.
   10467            8 :  *

   10469            8 :  */
   10470            8 : export function isPackedArrayLiteral(node: Expression) {
   10471            8 :     return isArrayLiteralExpression(node) && every(node.elements, isPackedElement);
   10472            8 : }
   10473            8 : 
   10474            8 : /**
   10475            8 :  * Indicates whether the result of an `Expression` will be unused.
   10476            8 :  *
   10477            8 :  * NOTE: This requires a node with a valid `parent` pointer.
   10478            8 :  *
   10479            8 :  * @internal
   10480            8 :  */
   10481            8 : export function expressionResultIsUnused(node: Expression): boolean {
   10482            8 :     Debug.assertIsDefined(node.parent);
   10483            8 :     while (true) {
   10484            8 :         const parent: Node = node.parent;
   10485            8 :         // walk up parenthesized expressions, but keep a pointer to the top-most parenthesized expression
   10486            8 :         if (isParenthesizedExpression(parent)) {
   10487            8 :             node = parent;
   10488            8 :             continue;
   10489            8 :         }
   10490            8 :         // result is unused in an expression statement, `void` expression, or the initializer or incrementer of a `for` loop
   10491            8 :         if (
   10492            8 :             isExpressionStatement(parent) ||
   10493            8 :             isVoidExpression(parent) ||
   10494            8 :             isForStatement(parent) && (parent.initializer === node || parent.incrementor === node)
   10495            8 :         ) {
   10496            8 :             return true;
   10497            8 :         }
   10498            8 :         if (isCommaListExpression(parent)) {
   10499            8 :             // left side of comma is always unused
   10500            8 :             if (node !== last(parent.elements)) return true;
   10501            8 :             // right side of comma is unused if parent is unused
   10502            8 :             node = parent;
   10503            8 :             continue;
   10504            8 :         }
   10505            8 :         if (isBinaryExpression(parent) && parent.operatorToken.kind === SyntaxKind.CommaToken) {
   10506            8 :             // left side of comma is always unused
   10507            8 :             if (node === parent.left) return true;
   10508            8 :             // right side of comma is unused if parent is unused
   10509            8 :             node = parent;
   10510            8 :             continue;
   10511            8 :         }
   10512            8 :         return false;
   10513            8 :     }
   10514            8 : }

   10521            8 : /** @internal */
   10522            8 : export function getContainingNodeArray(node: Node): NodeArray<Node> | undefined {
   10523            8 :     if (!node.parent) return undefined;
   10524            8 :     switch (node.kind) {
   10525            8 :         case SyntaxKind.TypeParameter:
   10526            8 :             const { parent } = node as TypeParameterDeclaration;
   10527            8 :             return parent.kind === SyntaxKind.InferType ? undefined : parent.typeParameters;
   10528            8 :         case SyntaxKind.Parameter:
   10529            8 :             return (node as ParameterDeclaration).parent.parameters;
   10530            8 :         case SyntaxKind.TemplateLiteralTypeSpan:
   10531            8 :             return (node as TemplateLiteralTypeSpan).parent.templateSpans;
   10532            8 :         case SyntaxKind.TemplateSpan:
   10533            8 :             return (node as TemplateSpan).parent.templateSpans;
   10534            8 :         case SyntaxKind.Decorator: {
   10535            8 :             const { parent } = node as Decorator;
   10536            8 :             return canHaveDecorators(parent) ? parent.modifiers :
   10537            8 :                 undefined;
   10538            8 :         }
   10539            8 :         case SyntaxKind.HeritageClause:
   10540            8 :             return (node as HeritageClause).parent.heritageClauses;
   10541            8 :     }
   10542            8 : 
   10543            8 :     const { parent } = node;
   10544            8 :     if (isJSDocTag(node)) {
   10545            8 :         return isJSDocTypeLiteral(node.parent) ? undefined : node.parent.tags;
   10546            8 :     }
   10547            8 : 
   10548            8 :     switch (parent.kind) {
   10549            8 :         case SyntaxKind.TypeLiteral:
   10550            8 :         case SyntaxKind.InterfaceDeclaration:
   10551            8 :             return isTypeElement(node) ? (parent as TypeLiteralNode | InterfaceDeclaration).members : undefined;
   10552            8 :         case SyntaxKind.UnionType:
   10553            8 :         case SyntaxKind.IntersectionType:
   10554            8 :             return (parent as UnionOrIntersectionTypeNode).types;
   10555            8 :         case SyntaxKind.TupleType:
   10556            8 :         case SyntaxKind.ArrayLiteralExpression:
   10557            8 :         case SyntaxKind.CommaListExpression:
   10558            8 :         case SyntaxKind.NamedImports:
   10559            8 :         case SyntaxKind.NamedExports:
   10560            8 :             return (parent as TupleTypeNode | ArrayLiteralExpression | CommaListExpression | NamedImports | NamedExports).elements;
   10561            8 :         case SyntaxKind.ObjectLiteralExpression:
   10562            8 :         case SyntaxKind.JsxAttributes:
   10563            8 :             return (parent as ObjectLiteralExpressionBase<ObjectLiteralElement>).properties;
   10564            8 :         case SyntaxKind.CallExpression:
   10565            8 :         case SyntaxKind.NewExpression:
   10566            8 :             return isTypeNode(node) ? (parent as CallExpression | NewExpression).typeArguments :
   10567            8 :                 (parent as CallExpression | NewExpression).expression === node ? undefined :
   10568            8 :                 (parent as CallExpression | NewExpression).arguments;
   10569            8 :         case SyntaxKind.JsxElement:
   10570            8 :         case SyntaxKind.JsxFragment:
   10571            8 :             return isJsxChild(node) ? (parent as JsxElement | JsxFragment).children : undefined;
   10572            8 :         case SyntaxKind.JsxOpeningElement:
   10573            8 :         case SyntaxKind.JsxSelfClosingElement:
   10574            8 :             return isTypeNode(node) ? (parent as JsxOpeningElement | JsxSelfClosingElement).typeArguments : undefined;
   10575            8 :         case SyntaxKind.Block:
   10576            8 :         case SyntaxKind.CaseClause:
   10577            8 :         case SyntaxKind.DefaultClause:
   10578            8 :         case SyntaxKind.ModuleBlock:
   10579            8 :             return (parent as Block | CaseOrDefaultClause | ModuleBlock).statements;
   10580            8 :         case SyntaxKind.CaseBlock:
   10581            8 :             return (parent as CaseBlock).clauses;
   10582            8 :         case SyntaxKind.ClassDeclaration:
   10583            8 :         case SyntaxKind.ClassExpression:
   10584            8 :             return isClassElement(node) ? (parent as ClassLikeDeclaration).members : undefined;
   10585            8 :         case SyntaxKind.EnumDeclaration:
   10586            8 :             return isEnumMember(node) ? (parent as EnumDeclaration).members : undefined;
   10587            8 :         case SyntaxKind.SourceFile:
   10588            8 :             return (parent as SourceFile).statements;
   10589            8 :     }
   10590            8 : }

   10592            8 : /** @internal */
   10593            8 : export function hasContextSensitiveParameters(node: FunctionLikeDeclaration) {
   10594            8 :     // Functions with type parameters are not context sensitive.
   10595            8 :     if (!node.typeParameters) {
   10596            8 :         // Functions with any parameters that lack type annotations are context sensitive.
   10597            8 :         if (some(node.parameters, p => !getEffectiveTypeAnnotationNode(p))) {
   10598            8 :             return true;
   10599            8 :         }
   10600            8 :         if (node.kind !== SyntaxKind.ArrowFunction) {
   10601            8 :             // If the first parameter is not an explicit 'this' parameter, then the function has
   10602            8 :             // an implicit 'this' parameter which is subject to contextual typing.
   10603            8 :             const parameter = firstOrUndefined(node.parameters);
   10604            8 :             if (!(parameter && parameterIsThisKeyword(parameter))) {
   10605            8 :                 return true;
   10606            8 :             }
   10607            8 :         }
   10608            8 :     }
   10609            8 :     return false;
   10610            8 : }

   10632            8 : /** @internal */
   10633            8 : export function isNumericLiteralName(name: string | __String) {
   10634            8 :     // The intent of numeric names is that
   10635            8 :     //     - they are names with text in a numeric form, and that
   10636            8 :     //     - setting properties/indexing with them is always equivalent to doing so with the numeric literal 'numLit',
   10637            8 :     //         acquired by applying the abstract 'ToNumber' operation on the name's text.
   10638            8 :     //
   10639            8 :     // The subtlety is in the latter portion, as we cannot reliably say that anything that looks like a numeric literal is a numeric name.
   10640            8 :     // In fact, it is the case that the text of the name must be equal to 'ToString(numLit)' for this to hold.
   10641            8 :     //
   10642            8 :     // Consider the property name '"0xF00D"'. When one indexes with '0xF00D', they are actually indexing with the value of 'ToString(0xF00D)'
   10643            8 :     // according to the ECMAScript specification, so it is actually as if the user indexed with the string '"61453"'.
   10644            8 :     // Thus, the text of all numeric literals equivalent to '61543' such as '0xF00D', '0xf00D', '0170015', etc. are not valid numeric names
   10645            8 :     // because their 'ToString' representation is not equal to their original text.
   10646            8 :     // This is motivated by ECMA-262 sections 9.3.1, 9.8.1, 11.1.5, and 11.2.1.
   10647            8 :     //
   10648            8 :     // Here, we test whether 'ToString(ToNumber(name))' is exactly equal to 'name'.
   10649            8 :     // The '+' prefix operator is equivalent here to applying the abstract ToNumber operation.
   10650            8 :     // Applying the 'toString()' method on a number gives us the abstract ToString operation on a number.
   10651            8 :     //
   10652            8 :     // Note that this accepts the values 'Infinity', '-Infinity', and 'NaN', and that this is intentional.
   10653            8 :     // This is desired behavior, because when indexing with them as numeric entities, you are indexing
   10654            8 :     // with the strings '"Infinity"', '"-Infinity"', and '"NaN"' respectively.
   10655            8 :     return (+name).toString() === name;
   10656            8 : }
   10657            8 : 
   10658            8 : /** @internal */
   10659            8 : export function createPropertyNameNodeForIdentifierOrLiteral(name: string, target: ScriptTarget, singleQuote: boolean, stringNamed: boolean, isMethod: boolean) {
   10660            8 :     const isMethodNamedNew = isMethod && name === "new";
   10661            8 :     return !isMethodNamedNew && isIdentifierText(name, target) ? factory.createIdentifier(name) :
   10662            8 :         !stringNamed && !isMethodNamedNew && isNumericLiteralName(name) && +name >= 0 ? factory.createNumericLiteral(+name) :
   10663            8 :         factory.createStringLiteral(name, !!singleQuote);
   10664            8 : }

   10671            8 : /** @internal */
   10672            8 : export interface NodeModulePathParts {
   10673            8 :     readonly topLevelNodeModulesIndex: number;
   10674            8 :     readonly topLevelPackageNameIndex: number;
   10675            8 :     readonly packageRootIndex: number;
   10676            8 :     readonly fileNameIndex: number;
   10677            8 : }
   10678            8 : /** @internal */
   10679            8 : export function getNodeModulePathParts(fullPath: string): NodeModulePathParts | undefined {
   10680            8 :     // If fullPath can't be valid module file within node_modules, returns undefined.
   10681            8 :     // Example of expected pattern: /base/path/node_modules/[@scope/otherpackage/@otherscope/node_modules/]package/[subdirectory/]file.js
   10682            8 :     // Returns indices:                       ^            ^                                                      ^             ^
   10683            8 : 
   10684            8 :     let topLevelNodeModulesIndex = 0;
   10685            8 :     let topLevelPackageNameIndex = 0;
   10686            8 :     let packageRootIndex = 0;
   10687            8 :     let fileNameIndex = 0;
   10688            8 : 
   10689            8 :     const enum States {
   10690            8 :         BeforeNodeModules,
   10691            8 :         NodeModules,
   10692            8 :         Scope,
   10693            8 :         PackageContent,
   10694            8 :     }
   10695            8 : 
   10696            8 :     let partStart = 0;
   10697            8 :     let partEnd = 0;
   10698            8 :     let state = States.BeforeNodeModules;
   10699            8 : 
   10700            8 :     while (partEnd >= 0) {
   10701            8 :         partStart = partEnd;
   10702            8 :         partEnd = fullPath.indexOf("/", partStart + 1);
   10703            8 :         switch (state) {
   10704            8 :             case States.BeforeNodeModules:
   10705            8 :                 if (fullPath.indexOf(nodeModulesPathPart, partStart) === partStart) {
   10706            8 :                     topLevelNodeModulesIndex = partStart;
   10707            8 :                     topLevelPackageNameIndex = partEnd;
   10708            8 :                     state = States.NodeModules;
   10709            8 :                 }
   10710            8 :                 break;
   10711            8 :             case States.NodeModules:
   10712            8 :             case States.Scope:
   10713            8 :                 if (state === States.NodeModules && fullPath.charAt(partStart + 1) === "@") {
   10714            8 :                     state = States.Scope;
   10715            8 :                 }
   10716            8 :                 else {
   10717            8 :                     packageRootIndex = partEnd;
   10718            8 :                     state = States.PackageContent;
   10719            8 :                 }
   10720            8 :                 break;
   10721            8 :             case States.PackageContent:
   10722            8 :                 if (fullPath.indexOf(nodeModulesPathPart, partStart) === partStart) {
   10723            8 :                     state = States.NodeModules;
   10724            8 :                 }
   10725            8 :                 else {
   10726            8 :                     state = States.PackageContent;
   10727            8 :                 }
   10728            8 :                 break;
   10729            8 :         }
   10730            8 :     }
   10731            8 : 
   10732            8 :     fileNameIndex = partStart;
   10733            8 : 
   10734            8 :     return state > States.NodeModules ? { topLevelNodeModulesIndex, topLevelPackageNameIndex, packageRootIndex, fileNameIndex } : undefined;
   10735            8 : }
